<usx version="3.1">
<book code="PSA" style="id">- unfoldingWord Simplified -</book>
<para style="h">Psalms</para>
<para style="toc1">Psalms</para>
<para style="toc2">Psalms</para>
<para style="mt1">Psalms</para>
<chapter number="1" style="c" sid="PSA 1"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 1:1"/>A joyful person is someone who does not do what evil people tell him to do, who does not imitate sinful people’s behavior, and who does not become like people who enjoy mocking.<verse eid="PSA 1:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 1:2"/>Instead, he delights in what Yahweh teaches, he thoughtfully reads it aloud every day and every night.<verse eid="PSA 1:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 1:3"/>Like having plenty of water causes a well-cultivated tree to produce fruit at the right time, and keeps it from dying, so {his faithfulness to Yahweh} causes everything this person does to prosper.<verse eid="PSA 1:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 1:4"/>That is not what wicked people are like! Instead, like chaff that the wind blows away,<verse eid="PSA 1:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 1:5"/>just so, wicked people will not be able to endure {when Yahweh} judges {the world}. Neither will sinful people {be present when Yahweh} gathers all the righteous people together.<verse eid="PSA 1:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 1:6"/>{All of this is} because Yahweh cares for righteous people, but wicked people keep sinning until {Yahweh} destroys them {forever}.<verse eid="PSA 1:6"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 1"/>
<chapter number="2" style="c" sid="PSA 2"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 2:1"/>Foreign kingdoms are scheming, and people groups are planning, but it is useless.<verse eid="PSA 2:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 2:2"/>Earthly kings prepare to revolt, the rulers plot together to fight against Yahweh and against his chosen king.<verse eid="PSA 2:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 2:3"/>{They shout,} “We should break free from the shackles {that they control us with}. We should throw aside the ropes {that they rule over us with}!”<verse eid="PSA 2:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 2:4"/>But the heavenly ruler sneers at them; the Lord ridicules those rulers.<verse eid="PSA 2:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 2:5"/>Then he speaks to them angrily. He terrifies them by {showing them how} furious he is.<verse eid="PSA 2:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 2:6"/>{Yahweh says,} “It is I who has made my king rule in Zion, {which is} my sacred hill.”<verse eid="PSA 2:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 2:7"/>{Yahweh’s king says,} “I will proclaim what Yahweh has decreed. Yahweh said to me, ‘You are my son; today I have become your father.<verse eid="PSA 2:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 2:8"/>Request {this from} me: {ask to} inherit the nations, {ask to} own the {whole} earth {even the} farthest parts. I will give them to you.<verse eid="PSA 2:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 2:9"/>You will strike them with an iron rod and they will shatter into small pieces as if they were a clay pot.”<verse eid="PSA 2:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 2:10"/>So then, you kings should act wisely! All rulers on the earth should allow Yahweh and his king to correct them!<verse eid="PSA 2:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 2:11"/>Worship Yahweh respectfully. Be joyful and afraid {while you are worshipping him}!<verse eid="PSA 2:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 2:12"/>Swear to be truly loyal to his son otherwise, he may become angry and suddenly kill you because he can become angry quickly. But all those who ask him to protect them are fortunate.<verse eid="PSA 2:12"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 2"/>
<chapter number="3" style="c" sid="PSA 3"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 3:1"/>A psalm written by David when he was fleeing from his son Absalom. Yahweh, I have so many enemies! Many people are deciding to oppose me.<verse eid="PSA 3:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 3:2"/>Many people are saying about me, “God will not rescue him.” Selah<verse eid="PSA 3:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 3:3"/>But Yahweh, you are like a shield that protects me. You greatly honor me, and you encourage me.<verse eid="PSA 3:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 3:4"/>Whenever I cry loudly to Yahweh {for help}, he {comes} from {Zion,} his sacred hill to help me. Selah<verse eid="PSA 3:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 3:5"/>I {can} lie down and sleep, {knowing that} I {will} wake up because Yahweh guards me {all night}.<verse eid="PSA 3:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 3:6"/>There may be thousands {of enemy soldiers} who surround me, but I am not afraid.<verse eid="PSA 3:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 3:7"/>Yahweh, get up! My God, rescue me! You can {insultingly} slap my enemies on their cheeks, and destroy those wicked people’s {power like breaking animals’} teeth,<verse eid="PSA 3:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 3:8"/>Yahweh rescues! Bless your people! Selah<verse eid="PSA 3:8"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 3"/>
<chapter number="4" style="c" sid="PSA 4"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 4:1"/>Righteous God, respond to me when I pray to you. You who have {always} rescued me when I was distressed, act mercifully toward me and pay attention to what I pray.<verse eid="PSA 4:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 4:2"/>How long will you mortal people dishonor me instead of honoring me? How long will you love what is useless, and chase lies? Selah<verse eid="PSA 4:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 4:3"/>You all should know that Yahweh treats people who are faithful to him as special to him. Yahweh will pay attention when I pray to him.<verse eid="PSA 4:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 4:4"/>You should be afraid of Yahweh, and {because of that} stop sinning! While you lie on your bed, examine what you are thinking and stop accusing {me}. Selah<verse eid="PSA 4:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 4:5"/>Instead, offer to Yahweh the proper sacrifices and continually trust him.<verse eid="PSA 4:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 4:6"/>Many people are wishing for something good to happen. Yahweh, please do good things for us!<verse eid="PSA 4:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 4:7"/>You have made me very joyful, even more than {these complainers are} when they have plenty of food and drink.<verse eid="PSA 4:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 4:8"/>I can lie down at night and sleep without worrying because {I know that} it is only you, Yahweh, who keeps me safe.<verse eid="PSA 4:8"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 4"/>
<chapter number="5" style="c" sid="PSA 5"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 5:1"/>Yahweh, listen to what I say! Comprehend my distressed sigh.<verse eid="PSA 5:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 5:2"/>{Since} you are my king and my God, hear and respond when I plead aloud for rescuing, because I am praying to you {only}.<verse eid="PSA 5:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 5:3"/>Yahweh, you will hear me pleading each morning. Every morning I will request that you save me, and I will wait for you to do it.<verse eid="PSA 5:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 5:4"/>You are a God who certainly does not approve of wicked people; evil-doers never stay as your guests.<verse eid="PSA 5:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 5:5"/>Boasters are not allowed to come worship you. You hate everyone who does evil things.<verse eid="PSA 5:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 5:6"/>You kill liars. Yahweh despises murderers and people who deceive others.<verse eid="PSA 5:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 5:7"/>As for me, I will come {worship you} where you live, because you are extremely faithful. I will reverently kneel to worship you at your sacred temple.<verse eid="PSA 5:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 5:8"/>Yahweh, my enemies are watching me {to try to catch me doing something wrong}. Please show me how to do what is right, just as you always do what is right. Make it easy for me to live obediently to you.<verse eid="PSA 5:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 5:9"/>Please do this because my enemies are untrustworthy; one of their strongest desires is to destroy people. They speak things that are vile like the smell of an open grave. They flatter people {to trap and destroy them}.<verse eid="PSA 5:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 5:10"/>O God, declare that they are guilty and punish them. Cause to happen to them the harmful events that they plan to cause to happen to others. Get rid of them because they have sinned often, and rebelled against you.<verse eid="PSA 5:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 5:11"/>But enable all the people who ask you to protect them to be glad; enable them to sing gladly always. Please protect them. Enable everyone who loves it when you are famous to praise you.<verse eid="PSA 5:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 5:12"/>{I ask this} because Yahweh, you always bless those who act righteously; you protect them as if your good acts are like a shield around them.<verse eid="PSA 5:12"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 5"/>
<chapter number="6" style="c" sid="PSA 6"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 6:1"/>Yahweh, do not correct me angrily, do not punish me wrathfully.<verse eid="PSA 6:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 6:2"/>Yahweh, act kindly toward me because I have become weak. Yahweh, heal me because my body shakes fearfully.<verse eid="PSA 6:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 6:3"/>Yahweh, I am greatly troubled in my inner being. How long must I endure this?<verse eid="PSA 6:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 6:4"/>Yahweh, relent from your anger and deliver me! Help me because you always do what you promise!<verse eid="PSA 6:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 6:5"/>{Do this} because {I and} no one {else} who is dead can honor you, {I and} no one {else} can praise you {if we are} in the place where the dead are.<verse eid="PSA 6:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 6:6"/>I am exhausted because of my pain. I cry all night long, so that my tears soak and seem as if they will wash away my bed and my cushions.<verse eid="PSA 6:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 6:7"/>I am very sad and {I cry so much that} I cannot see well. My vision has become weak from {crying because of} all my enemies.<verse eid="PSA 6:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 6:8"/>{I advise} all you people who do evil things to get away from me because Yahweh heard me when I was crying,<verse eid="PSA 6:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 6:9"/>he heard me when I called out for him to help me, and he will answer my prayer.<verse eid="PSA 6:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 6:10"/>{When that happens,} all my enemies will be ashamed and very troubled. They will relent {from attacking me because they will} suddenly {be} ashamed.<verse eid="PSA 6:10"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 6"/>
<chapter number="7" style="c" sid="PSA 7"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 7:1"/>A psalm that David sang to Yahweh because of a Benjamite named Cush. Yahweh my God, I have come to you so that you can protect me. Save me from everyone who is chasing me {in order to harm me}. Rescue me!<verse eid="PSA 7:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 7:2"/>If you do not do that, they will maul me like a lion {does when it attacks the animals it wants to kill}; they shred me and there is not a rescuer.<verse eid="PSA 7:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 7:3"/>My God Yahweh, suppose that I have done these things, that I am really guilty.<verse eid="PSA 7:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 7:4"/>Suppose that I have harmed my ally, {maybe} I {was unfaithful to my ally and instead} rescued an enemy for no reason.<verse eid="PSA 7:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 7:5"/>Then allow my enemies to chase and capture me. Allow them to stomp me into the ground and leave me lying {dead} in the dirt.<verse eid="PSA 7:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 7:6"/>Get up Yahweh! Because you are angry, show that you are greater than what my furious enemies can do! Be alert so you can rescue me by doing what you have said is just!<verse eid="PSA 7:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 7:7"/>The people of all nations gather around you, return to ruling over them all!<verse eid="PSA 7:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 7:8"/>Yahweh, judge the people of all nations! Decide favorably for me, Yahweh, because I am righteous and honorable {before you the} highest judge.<verse eid="PSA 7:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 7:9"/>God, you are righteous and look closely at what people think and want. Please stop evil people from doing wicked things, and make {all of us} who are righteous secure!<verse eid="PSA 7:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 7:10"/>God, you protect me as a shield protects soldiers; you rescue all those who are righteous in their inner being.<verse eid="PSA 7:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 7:11"/>God judges everyone correctly. God condemns {the wicked} constantly.<verse eid="PSA 7:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 7:12"/>Whenever the wicked do not repent, it is as though God sharpens his sword and puts a string on his bow {to get ready to kill them}.<verse eid="PSA 7:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 7:13"/>He prepares his deadly weapons to kill {the wicked}, he makes his arrows have flaming tips.<verse eid="PSA 7:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 7:14"/>Look at the wicked person who is filled with evil intentions, as though pregnant with them, who plans to trouble people like conceiving a child, and who lies as naturally as giving birth.<verse eid="PSA 7:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 7:15"/>If he digs a deep pit to trap others, he will fall into his own trap.<verse eid="PSA 7:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 7:16"/>He experiences the bad things that he wants to cause to others, he hurts himself by the violent things that he wants to do to others.<verse eid="PSA 7:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 7:17"/>I thank Yahweh because he always acts justly, I sing to praise Yahweh, who is the highest judge, and to make him famous.<verse eid="PSA 7:17"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 7"/>
<chapter number="8" style="c" sid="PSA 8"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 8:1"/>A psalm written by David for the choir director, to be accompanied by a stringed instrument; Our Lord Yahweh, people all over the world know how impressive you are! You have made the sky show {everyone} how grand you are {every time anyone looks at it}!<verse eid="PSA 8:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 8:2"/>When {anyone who is weak cries for help like} nursing little children cry {for help} you {listen and} protect them from your enemies, {the ones that want to hurt your people}. In order to protect them, you destroy enemies who want to harm them in return {for what you have justly done to them}.<verse eid="PSA 8:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 8:3"/>I look up at the sky {at night} and see the things that you have made— the moon and the stars that you have set in place.<verse eid="PSA 8:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 8:4"/>It is amazing to me that you think about people, that you are concerned about humans!<verse eid="PSA 8:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 8:5"/>In fact though, you made humans to be just slightly lower than heavenly beings. You made humans to be glorious and majestic {like you}.<verse eid="PSA 8:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 8:6"/>You put humans in charge of everything that you made, you made them rule over all things—<verse eid="PSA 8:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 8:7"/>{over} all {the domestic animals like} sheep, goats, and cattle, the wild animals too,<verse eid="PSA 8:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 8:8"/>the birds in the sky, the fish in the sea, and everything else that swims in the ocean.<verse eid="PSA 8:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 8:9"/>Our Lord Yahweh, people all over the world know how impressive you are!<verse eid="PSA 8:9"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 8"/>
<chapter number="9" style="c" sid="PSA 9"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 9:1"/>A psalm written by David for the choir director, in the ‘Muth Labben’ style; Yahweh, I will praise you with all of my inner being. I will tell others about all the wonderful things that you have done.<verse eid="PSA 9:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 9:2"/>You make me extremely happy, so I will sing to celebrate what you, who are much greater than all other gods, have done.<verse eid="PSA 9:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 9:3"/>When my foes flee {from your righteous anger}, they trip and fall. You kill them just by being near them.<verse eid="PSA 9:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 9:4"/>{You are angry because} you have found my legal case to be righteous {and my enemies’ to be wicked}. You sit on a throne {like a king} judging {everything} rightly.<verse eid="PSA 9:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 9:5"/>You reprimanded the people from other nations, and killed the wicked people; you eradicate them so thoroughly no one will ever remember their names.<verse eid="PSA 9:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 9:6"/>Nothing remains of our enemies except the ruins of their cities which you permanently destroyed. No one even remembers those enemies anymore.<verse eid="PSA 9:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 9:7"/>But Yahweh rules forever. He is prepared to judge from his throne.<verse eid="PSA 9:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 9:8"/>He will judge all the people in the world justly; he will be fair when he judges the people of every nation.<verse eid="PSA 9:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 9:9"/>Let Yahweh be like a fortress for those whom oppressors oppress; like a strong fort for them when they have trouble.<verse eid="PSA 9:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 9:10"/>Those who know your reputation should trust you; because you, Yahweh, never abandon those who come to you {for help}.<verse eid="PSA 9:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 9:11"/>Yahweh rules on Mount Zion; praise him by singing to him! Tell people from every nation the marvelous things that he has done.<verse eid="PSA 9:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 9:12"/>Do this because Yahweh always remembers to repay any person who murders another person. When someone's enemy has oppressed him, and when that person calls to Yahweh to help him, Yahweh does not forget to avenge him.<verse eid="PSA 9:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 9:13"/>Yahweh, act mercifully toward me! You who rescue me when I am almost dead, look at the ways that my enemies have oppressed me.<verse eid="PSA 9:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 9:14"/>{I want to live} in order to tell all your people at the entrance to Jerusalem all the reasons to praise you and to rejoice because you rescued me.<verse eid="PSA 9:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 9:15"/>{When you rescue me} it is like wicked people of many nations had dug a pit for me to fall into, but have fallen into that same pit, or like they hid a net to catch me, but their feet have been caught in that same net.<verse eid="PSA 9:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 9:16"/>So you allow the traps that wicked people make to trap them. Because of that, people can discover that you, Yahweh, are just. <verse eid="PSA 9:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 9:17"/>Wicked people will flee {from you} back to the place where dead people stay. {There are people there} from every nation, people who have forgotten {to worship the true} God.<verse eid="PSA 9:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 9:18"/>This all happens because there is a certainly time when God will remember {to take care of} poor people. It is good for oppressed people to expect him to rescue them because he will do it one day.<verse eid="PSA 9:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 9:19"/>Yahweh, do something! Do not let {evil} people win! {Bring them} to your court and judge them!<verse eid="PSA 9:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 9:20"/>Yahweh, teach them that they must be afraid of you and honor you. Cause {the rulers of} nations to know that they are mortal. <verse eid="PSA 9:20"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 9"/>
<chapter number="10" style="c" sid="PSA 10"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 10:1"/>Yahweh, please do not stay far away from us. Please let us find you when enemies threaten us.<verse eid="PSA 10:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 10:2"/>Wicked people proudly chase people until they can oppress them. Yahweh, please make the bad things they plan to do others to happen to them instead.<verse eid="PSA 10:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 10:3"/>A wicked person even brags about what he strongly wants to do. He praises people who unjustly take things from other people. He curses Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 10:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 10:4"/>The wicked person is so proud that he does not care {about God}. He plans {to do evil things} as if there was no God.<verse eid="PSA 10:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 10:5"/>What he does always prospers. He ignores doing what you say is right. He makes a mocking noise at all his enemies.<verse eid="PSA 10:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 10:6"/>He thinks, “Nothing bad can happen to me! As long as I live, nothing will trouble me.”<verse eid="PSA 10:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 10:7"/>He constantly curses, lies, and threatens others. He is always talking about harming others and doing wrong.<verse eid="PSA 10:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 10:8"/>He hides outside villages to surprise attack people. From his secret spot he kills people who have done nothing wrong. From there he sneakily watches for some unlucky person.<verse eid="PSA 10:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 10:9"/>He hides in a secret spot like a lion, {crouching} in the bushes, waiting for people to catch and oppress. He catches people and drags them away in a net to oppress them.<verse eid="PSA 10:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 10:10"/>The wicked person makes sure everything is properly prepared so he can oppress his unlucky victim.<verse eid="PSA 10:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 10:11"/>He convinces himself, “God is not recording what I do. He is not paying attention; he will never notice.”<verse eid="PSA 10:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 10:12"/>Do something Yahweh! Prove that you are powerful God! Pay attention to oppressed people!<verse eid="PSA 10:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 10:13"/>Do not let wicked people curse you, God! Do not let him believe that you do not care about his evil deeds!<verse eid="PSA 10:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 10:14"/>Surely you see everything! You pay attention to how wicked people hurt and frustrate other people so that you can punish those wicked people. Unlucky people trust that you will protect them. You help orphans.<verse eid="PSA 10:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 10:15"/>Cause people who are always doing very evil things to become powerless! When someone tries to oppress other people may he discover he cannot do it.<verse eid="PSA 10:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 10:16"/>Yahweh reigns eternally! Foreign people no longer occupy his land.<verse eid="PSA 10:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 10:17"/>Yahweh, when oppressed people ask you to help, you listen and encourage them. You pay close attention,<verse eid="PSA 10:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 10:18"/>so you can act justly for the orphans and oppressed people. You will stop any mere human from ever terrifying them again.<verse eid="PSA 10:18"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 10"/>
<chapter number="11" style="c" sid="PSA 11"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 11:1"/>A psalm written by David for the choir director; I trust that Yahweh will protect me. So I do not fly off to the mountains like birds do.<verse eid="PSA 11:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 11:2"/>It is true that wicked people have hidden in the darkness, that they have pulled back their bowstrings and aimed their arrows to shoot them at people who honor Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 11:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 11:3"/>When wicked people do not suffer for disobeying the laws, what can righteous people do?<verse eid="PSA 11:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 11:4"/>But Yahweh is sitting on his throne in his sacred temple in heaven, and he sees everything that people do.<verse eid="PSA 11:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 11:5"/>Yahweh examines what righteous people do and what wicked people do, and he hates those who love to injure others.<verse eid="PSA 11:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 11:6"/>He will send down from the sky flaming coals and burning sulfur on the wicked; he will send scorching hot winds to punish them.<verse eid="PSA 11:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 11:7"/>Yahweh does everything that is right, and he loves those who do what is right; such people will come into his presence.<verse eid="PSA 11:7"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 11"/>
<chapter number="12" style="c" sid="PSA 12"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 12:1"/>A psalm written by David for the choir director; Yahweh, help us! It seems like people who honor you are no more, that those who are loyal to you have all vanished.<verse eid="PSA 12:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 12:2"/>Everyone tells lies to other people; they deceive others by flattering them, but they tell lies.<verse eid="PSA 12:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 12:3"/>Yahweh, we wish that you would cut off their tongues so that they cannot continue to boast.<verse eid="PSA 12:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 12:4"/>They say, “By telling lies we will get what we want; we control what we say, so no one can tell us what we should do!”<verse eid="PSA 12:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 12:5"/>But Yahweh replies, “I have seen the violent things that they have done to helpless people; I have heard those people groaning, so I will arise and rescue the people who are wanting me to help them.”<verse eid="PSA 12:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 12:6"/>Yahweh, you always do what you have promised to do; what you have promised is as precious and pure as silver that has been heated seven times in a furnace to get rid of all the impure material.<verse eid="PSA 12:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 12:7"/>Yahweh, we know that you will protect us who honor you from those wicked people,<verse eid="PSA 12:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 12:8"/>those who strut around proudly, while people praise them for doing evil deeds.<verse eid="PSA 12:8"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 12"/>
<chapter number="13" style="c" sid="PSA 13"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 13:1"/>A psalm written by David for the choir director; Yahweh, how long will you continue to forget about me? Will you hide yourself from me forever?<verse eid="PSA 13:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 13:2"/>How long must I endure anguish within myself? Must I be miserable every day? How long will my enemies continue to defeat me?<verse eid="PSA 13:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 13:3"/>Yahweh my God, look at me and answer me. Restore my strength, or I will die.<verse eid="PSA 13:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 13:4"/>Do not allow my enemies to boast and to say, “We have defeated him!” Do not allow them to defeat me, with the result that they will rejoice about it!<verse eid="PSA 13:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 13:5"/>But I trust that you will faithfully love me; I will rejoice when you rescue me.<verse eid="PSA 13:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 13:6"/>Yahweh, you have done many good things for me, so I will sing to you.<verse eid="PSA 13:6"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 13"/>
<chapter number="14" style="c" sid="PSA 14"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 14:1"/>A psalm written by David for the choir director; Only foolish people say to themselves, “There is no God!” People who say those things only do corrupt deeds; there is not one of them who does what is good.<verse eid="PSA 14:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 14:2"/>From heaven Yahweh looks down at everyone; he looks to see if anyone is very wise, wise enough to desire to know him.<verse eid="PSA 14:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 14:3"/>Everyone turns away from Yahweh. They are depraved and do disgusting, filthy things. No one does what is good.<verse eid="PSA 14:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 14:4"/>Will those evil people never learn what God will do to punish them? They act violently toward Yahweh’s people and want to consume them like one who eats food consumes it, and they never pray to Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 14:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 14:5"/>But some day they will become very terrified because God helps those who act righteously and will punish those who reject him.<verse eid="PSA 14:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 14:6"/>Those who do evil may prevent helpless people from doing what they plan to do, but Yahweh protects them.<verse eid="PSA 14:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 14:7"/>Out of Zion Yahweh will come and rescue the Israelite people! He will make his people free again and will bring them back to their home. On that day all of us Israelite people will rejoice, and we, who are also called the descendants of Jacob, will be happy.<verse eid="PSA 14:7"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 14"/>
<chapter number="15" style="c" sid="PSA 15"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 15:1"/>A psalm written by David; Yahweh, who are allowed to enter your sacred tent? Who are allowed to live on your sacred mountain?<verse eid="PSA 15:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 15:2"/>Only those who always do what is right and do not sin may do that, those who always speak the truth.<verse eid="PSA 15:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 15:3"/>They do not slander others. They do not do to others things that are wrong, and they do not say bad things about anyone.<verse eid="PSA 15:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 15:4"/>People who honor God hate those whom he has rejected, but they respect those who have a fearful respect for Yahweh. They do what they have promised to do even if it causes them trouble to do that.<verse eid="PSA 15:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 15:5"/>They lend money to others without charging interest, and they never accept bribes in order to lie about people who have not done anything wrong. Those who do those things will always live in safety.<verse eid="PSA 15:5"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 15"/>
<chapter number="16" style="c" sid="PSA 16"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 16:1"/>A psalm written by David; God, protect me because I go to you to keep me safe!<verse eid="PSA 16:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 16:2"/>I said to Yahweh, “You are my Lord; all the good things that I have come from you.”<verse eid="PSA 16:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 16:3"/>People who try to be holy who live in this land are wonderful; I delight to be with them.<verse eid="PSA 16:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 16:4"/>Those who choose to worship other gods will have many things that cause them to be sad. I will not join them when they make sacrifices to their gods; I will not even join them in speaking the names of their gods.<verse eid="PSA 16:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 16:5"/>Yahweh, you are the one whom I have chosen, and you give me great blessings. You protect me and control what happens to me.<verse eid="PSA 16:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 16:6"/>Yahweh has given me a wonderful place in which to live; I am delighted with all the things that he has given me.<verse eid="PSA 16:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 16:7"/>I will praise Yahweh, the one who teaches me; even at night he tells my heart what is right for me to do.<verse eid="PSA 16:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 16:8"/>I know that Yahweh is always with me. Nothing will take me from his side.<verse eid="PSA 16:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 16:9"/>Therefore I am glad; I am honored to praise him, and I can rest securely<verse eid="PSA 16:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 16:10"/>because you, Yahweh, will not allow me to remain in the place where the dead people are, and you will not allow me, someone who has been faithful to the covenant, to stay there.<verse eid="PSA 16:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 16:11"/>You will show me the road that leads to where I receive eternal life, and you will make me joyful when I am with you. I will have pleasure forever when I am at your right hand.<verse eid="PSA 16:11"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 16"/>
<chapter number="17" style="c" sid="PSA 17"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 17:1"/>A psalm written by David; Yahweh, listen to me while I plead with you to act justly toward me. Hear me while I call out to you to help me. Pay attention to what I say while I pray because I am speaking honestly.<verse eid="PSA 17:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 17:2"/>You are the one who is able to declare that I am innocent; please agree to do what is right for me.<verse eid="PSA 17:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 17:3"/>If you come to me at night to learn what I think, if you see what I think in my heart, you will know that I have determined to never tell any lies; you will find that I do not think evil things.<verse eid="PSA 17:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 17:4"/>I have not acted like those who do not honor you; I have always acted in the power of what you have instructed me; I have not acted like those who do not know your law.<verse eid="PSA 17:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 17:5"/>I have always done what you told me to do; I have never failed to do those things.<verse eid="PSA 17:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 17:6"/>O God, I am praying to you because you answer me; please listen to what I am saying.<verse eid="PSA 17:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 17:7"/>Continue to show me your love as you promised you would do. By your great power you protect all who trust in you; you keep them safe from their enemies.<verse eid="PSA 17:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 17:8"/>Protect me as carefully as people protect their own eyes; protect me like birds protect their babies under their wings.<verse eid="PSA 17:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 17:9"/>Do not allow wicked people to attack me, those enemies of mine who surround, wanting to kill me.<verse eid="PSA 17:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 17:10"/>They are proud of their riches and success, but they have no mercy on anyone.<verse eid="PSA 17:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 17:11"/>They have hunted for me and found me. They surround me, watching for an opportunity to throw me to the ground and kill me.<verse eid="PSA 17:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 17:12"/>They are like lions that are ready to tear apart the animals that they capture; They are like young lions that are hiding, waiting to jump on their prey.<verse eid="PSA 17:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 17:13"/>Yahweh, arise, attack my enemies, and defeat them! With your sword save me from those wicked people!<verse eid="PSA 17:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 17:14"/>Yahweh, by your power rescue me from those people who are interested only in things here in this world. But you provide plenty of food for those whom you love dearly; their children also have many things that their grandchildren will inherit.<verse eid="PSA 17:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 17:15"/>Yahweh, because I act in the right way, I will be with you one day. When I awake after I die, I will see you face to face, and then I will be happy.<verse eid="PSA 17:15"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 17"/>
<chapter number="18" style="c" sid="PSA 18"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 18:1"/>A psalm written by God’s servant David. He sang it after Yahweh had rescued him from Saul and his other enemies. Yahweh, I love you, the one who enables me to be strong.<verse eid="PSA 18:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 18:2"/>Yahweh is like a huge rock; when I am on top of it, my enemies cannot reach me. He is like a strong fortress; I run into it to be safe. He protects me like a shield protects a soldier; he is the one whom I trust to keep me safe; he defends me by his great power!<verse eid="PSA 18:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 18:3"/>I called out to Yahweh, who deserves for me to praise him, and he rescued me from my enemies.<verse eid="PSA 18:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 18:4"/>All around me were dangerous situations in which I might die; it was as though there were huge waves that almost crashed on me and killed me.<verse eid="PSA 18:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 18:5"/>It was as though the place where dead people are had ropes that were wrapped around me, or it was as though there was a trap that would seize and kill me.<verse eid="PSA 18:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 18:6"/>But when I was very distressed, I called out to Yahweh, and far off in his temple he heard me. He listened to me when I cried out for help.<verse eid="PSA 18:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 18:7"/>Then Yahweh became angry, and the earth quaked, and the mountains shook to their very foundations!<verse eid="PSA 18:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 18:8"/>He was so angry that it was as though smoke poured out from his nostrils, as though burning coals came out of his mouth!<verse eid="PSA 18:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 18:9"/>He opened the sky and came down with a black cloud under his feet.<verse eid="PSA 18:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 18:10"/>He flew, riding on the back of an angel traveling fast, which the wind was blowing along.<verse eid="PSA 18:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 18:11"/>Darkness was all around him like a blanket; dark clouds, full of water moisture, covered him.<verse eid="PSA 18:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 18:12"/>Hailstones and flashes of lightning were around him; hail and burning coals fell down from the sky.<verse eid="PSA 18:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 18:13"/>Then Yahweh shouted loudly from the sky, and to his enemies, it sounded like thunder. Yahweh, the Supreme God, rained hailstones on them and caused lightning to flash against them.<verse eid="PSA 18:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 18:14"/>He shot his arrows at them and caused them to scatter; his flashes of lightning caused them to become very confused.<verse eid="PSA 18:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 18:15"/>The bottom of the ocean became visible, and the water uncovered the foundations of the earth when Yahweh rebuked his enemies with the breath that came in his anger!<verse eid="PSA 18:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 18:16"/>It was as though he reached down from heaven and grabbed me and pulled me up out of the deep ocean.<verse eid="PSA 18:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 18:17"/>He rescued me from my strong enemies who hated me; they were very strong, and I could not defeat them by myself.<verse eid="PSA 18:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 18:18"/>When I was distressed, they attacked me, but Yahweh defended me.<verse eid="PSA 18:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 18:19"/>He made me completely safe; he rescued me because he was pleased with me.<verse eid="PSA 18:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 18:20"/>Yahweh has rewarded me because I do what is right; he has blessed me because I am innocent.<verse eid="PSA 18:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 18:21"/>I have obeyed Yahweh’s laws; I have not abandoned him.<verse eid="PSA 18:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 18:22"/>I have followed his decrees; I have not stopped obeying them.<verse eid="PSA 18:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 18:23"/>He knows that I have not done what is wrong and that I have kept myself from sinning.<verse eid="PSA 18:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 18:24"/>So he rewards me because I do what is right; he knows that I have not committed sins.<verse eid="PSA 18:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 18:25"/>Yahweh, you are faithful to those who faithfully do your covenant; you always do what is good to those who do not do evil.<verse eid="PSA 18:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 18:26"/>You are kind to those who are honest toward others, but you act wisely toward those who act dishonestly.<verse eid="PSA 18:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 18:27"/>You save those who are humble, but you humiliate those who are proud.<verse eid="PSA 18:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 18:28"/>You keep me alive, and you will continue to do so.<verse eid="PSA 18:28"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="29" style="v" sid="PSA 18:29"/>You enable me to be strong, so that I can attack and defeat a line of enemy soldiers; with your help I can scale the walls that surround my enemies’ cities.<verse eid="PSA 18:29"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="30" style="v" sid="PSA 18:30"/>Everything that Yahweh my God does is perfect. We can depend on him to do what he promises. He is like a shield to protect all those who go to him to be safe.<verse eid="PSA 18:30"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="31" style="v" sid="PSA 18:31"/>Yahweh is the only one who is God; only he is like a huge rock on top of which we can be safe.<verse eid="PSA 18:31"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="32" style="v" sid="PSA 18:32"/>God is the one who enables me to be strong and who keeps me safe on the roads that I walk on.<verse eid="PSA 18:32"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="33" style="v" sid="PSA 18:33"/>He enables me to walk swiftly without stumbling as a deer walks in the mountains.<verse eid="PSA 18:33"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="34" style="v" sid="PSA 18:34"/>He teaches me how to use a strong bow in order that I can use it to fight in battles.<verse eid="PSA 18:34"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="35" style="v" sid="PSA 18:35"/>Yahweh, you protect and save me with your shield; you are strong and have therefore kept me safe. I have become strong because you have helped me.<verse eid="PSA 18:35"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="36" style="v" sid="PSA 18:36"/>You have made a safe path for me, with the result that now I do not slip.<verse eid="PSA 18:36"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="37" style="v" sid="PSA 18:37"/>I pursued my enemies and caught them; I did not stop until I had defeated them all.<verse eid="PSA 18:37"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="38" style="v" sid="PSA 18:38"/>When I strike them, they are not able to get up again; they lie on the ground, defeated.<verse eid="PSA 18:38"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="39" style="v" sid="PSA 18:39"/>You have enabled me to be strong in order that I can fight battles and defeat my enemies.<verse eid="PSA 18:39"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="40" style="v" sid="PSA 18:40"/>You delivered my enemies to me, for me to strike them on their necks. I have gotten rid of all those who hated me.<verse eid="PSA 18:40"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="41" style="v" sid="PSA 18:41"/>They shouted for someone to help them, but no one saved them. They shouted out to Yahweh, but he did not help them.<verse eid="PSA 18:41"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="42" style="v" sid="PSA 18:42"/>I crushed them to powder, and they became like the dust that the wind blows away; I threw them out like people throw dirt out into the streets.<verse eid="PSA 18:42"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="43" style="v" sid="PSA 18:43"/>You enabled me to defeat those who fought against me and appointed me to be the ruler of many nations; people whom I did not know about previously are now slaves in my kingdom.<verse eid="PSA 18:43"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="44" style="v" sid="PSA 18:44"/>When foreigners hear about me, they cringe and they obey me.<verse eid="PSA 18:44"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="45" style="v" sid="PSA 18:45"/>They are no longer courageous, and from their holes where they were hiding they come to me trembling.<verse eid="PSA 18:45"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="46" style="v" sid="PSA 18:46"/>Yahweh is alive! Praise the one who is like a huge rock on top of which I am safe! Exalt the God who saves me!<verse eid="PSA 18:46"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="47" style="v" sid="PSA 18:47"/>He enables me to get revenge on my enemies; he causes me to defeat nations and to rule over them.<verse eid="PSA 18:47"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="48" style="v" sid="PSA 18:48"/>it is Yahweh who rescues me from my enemies. He has lifted me up high so that violent men could not reach me and harm me.<verse eid="PSA 18:48"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="49" style="v" sid="PSA 18:49"/>So I praise him, and I tell the nations the great things that he has done.<verse eid="PSA 18:49"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="50" style="v" sid="PSA 18:50"/>He has enabled me, his king, to powerfully defeat my enemies; he faithfully loves me as he promised in his covenant. He loves me, David, the one he has chosen to be king, and he will faithfully love my descendants forever.<verse eid="PSA 18:50"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 18"/>
<chapter number="19" style="c" sid="PSA 19"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 19:1"/>A psalm written by David for the choir director; When people look at everything that God has placed in the skies, they can see that he is very great; they can see the great things that he has created.<verse eid="PSA 19:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 19:2"/>Day after day it is as though the sun proclaims the glory of God, and night after night it is as though the moon and stars say that they know that God made them.<verse eid="PSA 19:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 19:3"/>They do not really speak; they do not say any words. There is no sound from them for anyone to hear.<verse eid="PSA 19:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 19:4"/>But what they declare about God goes throughout the world, and even people who live in the most distant places on earth can know it. The sun is in the skies where God placed it;<verse eid="PSA 19:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 19:5"/>it rises each morning like a bridegroom who is happy as he comes out of his bedroom after his wedding. It is like a strong athlete who is very eager to start running in a race.<verse eid="PSA 19:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 19:6"/>The sun rises at one side of the sky and goes across the sky and sets on the other side; nothing can hide from its heat.<verse eid="PSA 19:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 19:7"/>The instructions that Yahweh has given us are perfect; they revive us. We can be sure that the things that Yahweh has told us will never change, and by learning them people who have not been previously taught will become wise.<verse eid="PSA 19:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 19:8"/>Yahweh’s laws are fair; when we obey them, we become joyful. The commands of Yahweh are clear, and by reading them we start to understand how God wants us to behave.<verse eid="PSA 19:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 19:9"/>It is good for people to revere Yahweh; that is something that they will do forever. What Yahweh has decreed is fair, and it is always right.<verse eid="PSA 19:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 19:10"/>The things that God has decided are more valuable than gold, even the finest gold. They are sweeter than honey that drips from honeycombs.<verse eid="PSA 19:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 19:11"/>Furthermore, by reading them I learn what things are good to do and what things are evil, and they promise a great reward to us who obey them.<verse eid="PSA 19:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 19:12"/>But there is no one who can know all his errors; so Yahweh, forgive me for these things which I do that I do not realize are wrong.<verse eid="PSA 19:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 19:13"/>Keep me from doing things that I know are wrong; do not let me keep doing the evil things I want to do. If you do that, I will no longer be guilty for committing such sins, and I will not commit the great sin of rebelling terribly against you.<verse eid="PSA 19:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 19:14"/>O Yahweh, you are like a huge rock on top of which I can be safe; you are the one who protects me. I hope that the things that I say and what I think will always please you.<verse eid="PSA 19:14"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 19"/>
<chapter number="20" style="c" sid="PSA 20"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 20:1"/>A psalm written by David for the choir director; We desire that Yahweh may help you when you call out to him when you have troubles! We desire that God, whom our ancestor Jacob honored, may keep you safe from your enemies.<verse eid="PSA 20:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 20:2"/>We desire that he may reach out from his sacred temple and help you and aid you from where he lives on Mount Zion.<verse eid="PSA 20:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 20:3"/>We desire that he may accept all the offerings that you give him to be burned on the altar and all your other offerings.<verse eid="PSA 20:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 20:4"/>We desire that he may give to you what you desire in your heart, and that you may be able to accomplish all that you desire to do.<verse eid="PSA 20:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 20:5"/>When you defeat your enemies, we will shout joyfully. We will lift up a banner proclaiming that it is God who has helped you. May Yahweh do for you all that you request him to do.<verse eid="PSA 20:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 20:6"/>I know now that Yahweh rescues me, the one whom he has chosen to be king. From his holy place in heaven he will answer me, and he will save me by his great power.<verse eid="PSA 20:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 20:7"/>Some kings trust that because they have chariots they will be able to defeat their enemies, and some trust that their horses will enable them to defeat their enemies, but we will trust in the power of Yahweh our God.<verse eid="PSA 20:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 20:8"/>Some will stumble and fall down, but we will be strong and not be moved.<verse eid="PSA 20:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 20:9"/>Yahweh, help the king defeat our enemies! Answer us when we call out to you to help us!<verse eid="PSA 20:9"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 20"/>
<chapter number="21" style="c" sid="PSA 21"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 21:1"/>A psalm written by David for the choir director; Yahweh, the man you made king is glad because you have caused him to be strong. He rejoices because you have enabled him to defeat his enemies.<verse eid="PSA 21:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 21:2"/>You have given him everything he most desired, and you have not refused to do what he requested you to do.<verse eid="PSA 21:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 21:3"/>You have done so many wonderful things for him. You placed a gold crown on his head.<verse eid="PSA 21:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 21:4"/>He asked you to let him live for a long time, and you have enabled him to live for a long time.<verse eid="PSA 21:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 21:5"/>His power as king is very great because you have allowed him to win victories over his enemies.<verse eid="PSA 21:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 21:6"/>You will bless him forever, and you have caused him to be joyful in your presence.<verse eid="PSA 21:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 21:7"/>Yahweh, you are God Almighty, and the king trusts in you. Because you faithfully love him, disastrous things will never happen to him.<verse eid="PSA 21:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 21:8"/>You will enable him to kill all his enemies, all those who hate him.<verse eid="PSA 21:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 21:9"/>When you appear, you will throw them into a fiery furnace. Because you are angry with them, you will swallow them up; the fire will burn them up.<verse eid="PSA 21:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 21:10"/>You will remove their children from this earth; their descendants will all disappear.<verse eid="PSA 21:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 21:11"/>They wanted to harm you, but what they plan will never succeed.<verse eid="PSA 21:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 21:12"/>You will cause them to run away by shooting arrows at them.<verse eid="PSA 21:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 21:13"/>Yahweh, show us that you are very strong! When you do that, we will sing and praise you because you are very powerful.<verse eid="PSA 21:13"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 21"/>
<chapter number="22" style="c" sid="PSA 22"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 22:1"/>A psalm written by David for the choir director, to be sung to the tune ‘Doe of the Dawn’ My God, my God, why have you abandoned me? Why do you stay so far from me, and why do you not listent to me? Why do you not hear me when I am suffering and groaning?<verse eid="PSA 22:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 22:2"/>My God, every day I call to you during the daytime, but you do not answer me. I call to you during the night; I am not silent at all.<verse eid="PSA 22:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 22:3"/>But you are holy. You sit on your throne as king, and we the people of Israel praise you.<verse eid="PSA 22:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 22:4"/>Our ancestors trusted in you. Because they trusted in you, you rescued them.<verse eid="PSA 22:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 22:5"/>When they called out to you for help, you saved them. They trusted in you, and they were not disappointed.<verse eid="PSA 22:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 22:6"/>But you have not rescued me! People despise me and consider that I am not a man; they think that I am a worm! Everyone scorns me and despises me.<verse eid="PSA 22:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 22:7"/>Everyone who sees me makes fun of me. They sneer at me and insult me by shaking their heads at me as though I were an evil man. They say,<verse eid="PSA 22:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 22:8"/>“He trusts in Yahweh, so Yahweh should save him! He says that Yahweh is very pleased with him; if that is so, Yahweh should rescue him!”<verse eid="PSA 22:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 22:9"/>You, God, have been with me since I was in my mother’s womb, and you taught me to trust you when I was at my mother’s breasts.<verse eid="PSA 22:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 22:10"/>It was as though you had adopted me right when I was born. You have been my God ever since I was born.<verse eid="PSA 22:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 22:11"/>So do not stay far from me now because enemies who will cause me much trouble are near me, and there is no one else who can help me.<verse eid="PSA 22:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 22:12"/>My enemies surround me like a herd of wild bulls. Fierce people, like those strong bulls that graze on the hills in the region of Bashan, surround me.<verse eid="PSA 22:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 22:13"/>They are like roaring lions that are attacking the animals that they want to eat; they rush toward me to kill me; they are like lions that have their mouths open, ready to chew their victims to pieces.<verse eid="PSA 22:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 22:14"/>I am completely exhausted, and all my bones are out of their joints. I no longer expect that God will save me; I am completely discouraged.<verse eid="PSA 22:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 22:15"/>My strength is all dried up like a broken piece of a clay jar that has dried in the sun. I am so thirsty that my tongue sticks to the roof of my mouth. God, I think that you are about to let my body die and become dust!<verse eid="PSA 22:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 22:16"/>My enemies are like wild dogs that surround me. A group of evil men has encircled me, ready to attack me. They have pierced through my hands and my feet.<verse eid="PSA 22:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 22:17"/>I am so weak and thin that I can count all my bones. My enemies stare at me and gloat about what has happened to me.<verse eid="PSA 22:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 22:18"/>They looked at the clothes that I was wearing and gambled to determine which piece each of them would get.<verse eid="PSA 22:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 22:19"/>Yahweh, be concerned for me! You who are my source of strength, come quickly and help me!<verse eid="PSA 22:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 22:20"/>Rescue me from those who want to kill me with their swords. Save my life from the power of those who are like wild dogs.<verse eid="PSA 22:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 22:21"/>Snatch me away from my enemies who are like lions with jaws open and ready to chew me up! Grab me away from those men who are like wild oxen that attack other animals with their horns!<verse eid="PSA 22:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 22:22"/>If you save me from them, I will declare to my fellow Israelites how great you are. I will praise you among the group of your people gathered together to worship you.<verse eid="PSA 22:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 22:23"/>You people who have an awesome respect for Yahweh, praise him! All you who are descended from Jacob, honor Yahweh! All you Israelite people, revere him!<verse eid="PSA 22:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 22:24"/>He does not despise or ignore those who are suffering; he does not hide his face from them. He has listened to them when they cried out to him for help.<verse eid="PSA 22:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 22:25"/>Yahweh, in the great gathering of your people, I will praise you for what you have done. In the presence of those who have an awesome respect for you, I will offer the sacrifices that I promised.<verse eid="PSA 22:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 22:26"/>The poor people whom I have invited to the meal will eat as much as they want. All who come to worship Yahweh will praise him. I pray that God will enable you all to live a long and happy life!<verse eid="PSA 22:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 22:27"/>I pray that people in all nations, even in the remote areas, will think about Yahweh and turn to him, and that people from all the clans in the world will bow down before him.<verse eid="PSA 22:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 22:28"/>For Yahweh is the king! He rules all the nations.<verse eid="PSA 22:28"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="29" style="v" sid="PSA 22:29"/>All the rich people on the earth will celebrate and bow before him. Some day they will die, for they cannot avoid it, but they will prostrate themselves on the ground in his presence.<verse eid="PSA 22:29"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="30" style="v" sid="PSA 22:30"/>People in the future generations will also serve Yahweh. They will tell their children about what Yahweh has done.<verse eid="PSA 22:30"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="31" style="v" sid="PSA 22:31"/>People who are not yet born, who will live in future years, will learn how Yahweh rescued his people. People will tell them, “Yahweh did it!”<verse eid="PSA 22:31"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 22"/>
<chapter number="23" style="c" sid="PSA 23"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 23:1"/>A psalm written by David; Yahweh, you care for me like a shepherd cares for his sheep, so I have everything that I need.<verse eid="PSA 23:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 23:2"/>You enable me to rest in peace as when a shepherd leads his sheep to places where there is plenty of green grass for them to eat, as when he lets them lie down beside streams where the water is flowing slowly.<verse eid="PSA 23:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 23:3"/>You renew my strength. You show me how to live in the right way, in order that I can honor you.<verse eid="PSA 23:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 23:4"/>Even when I am walking in very dangerous places where I might die, I will not be afraid of anything because you are with me. You protect me like a shepherd protects his sheep.<verse eid="PSA 23:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 23:5"/>You prepare a great feast for me in a place where my enemies can see me. You welcome me as a guest whom you honor. You have given me very many blessings!<verse eid="PSA 23:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 23:6"/>I am certain that you will be good to me and act mercifully toward me as long as I live; then, O Yahweh, I will live in your home forever.<verse eid="PSA 23:6"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 23"/>
<chapter number="24" style="c" sid="PSA 24"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 24:1"/>A psalm written by David; The earth and everything in it belongs to Yahweh; all the people in the world belong to him, too;<verse eid="PSA 24:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 24:2"/>he built the land on the water, above the water that is deep below.<verse eid="PSA 24:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 24:3"/>Who will be allowed to go up onto Mount Zion in Jerusalem, in order to stand and worship in Yahweh’s holy temple?<verse eid="PSA 24:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 24:4"/>Only those whose actions and thoughts are pure, who have not worshiped idols, and who do not tell lies when they have solemnly promised to tell the truth.<verse eid="PSA 24:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 24:5"/>Yahweh will bless them. When God judges them, he will rescue them and say that they have done nothing wrong.<verse eid="PSA 24:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 24:6"/>They are the people who come to God, they are the ones who desire to worship God, and serve the God of Jacob.<verse eid="PSA 24:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 24:7"/>Open up the temple gates in order that our glorious king may enter!<verse eid="PSA 24:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 24:8"/>Do you know who the glorious king is? It is Yahweh, the one who is very strong; It is Yahweh, who conquers all his enemies in battles!<verse eid="PSA 24:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 24:9"/>Open up the temple gates in order that our glorious king may enter!<verse eid="PSA 24:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 24:10"/>Do you know who the glorious king is? It is Yahweh, commander of the angel armies; he is our glorious king!<verse eid="PSA 24:10"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 24"/>
<chapter number="25" style="c" sid="PSA 25"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 25:1"/>A psalm written by David; Yahweh, I give myself to you.<verse eid="PSA 25:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 25:2"/>My God, I trust in you. Do not allow my enemies to defeat me and shame me. Do not allow my enemies to defeat me and rejoice over me.<verse eid="PSA 25:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 25:3"/>Do not allow any of those who trust in you to be ashamed. Cause those who act treacherously toward others to be disgraced.<verse eid="PSA 25:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 25:4"/>Yahweh, show me the way that I should conduct my life, teach me how to act in the manner that you want me to act.<verse eid="PSA 25:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 25:5"/>Teach me to conduct my life by obeying your truth because you are my God, the one who saves me. All during the day I trust in you.<verse eid="PSA 25:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 25:6"/>Yahweh, do not forget how you have acted mercifully to me and have faithfully loved me because of your covenant with me; that is the way that you have acted toward me from long ago.<verse eid="PSA 25:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 25:7"/>Forgive me for all the sinful things I did and the ways that I rebelled against you when I was young; I request this because you faithfully love your people and do good things for them, as you promised in your covenant. Yahweh, do not forget me!<verse eid="PSA 25:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 25:8"/>Yahweh is good and fair, so he shows sinners how they should conduct their lives.<verse eid="PSA 25:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 25:9"/>He shows humble people what is right for them to do and teaches them what he wants them to do.<verse eid="PSA 25:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 25:10"/>He always faithfully loves us and does what he has promised for those who obey his covenant and who do what he requires.<verse eid="PSA 25:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 25:11"/>Yahweh, forgive me for all my sins, which are many, in order that I may honor you.<verse eid="PSA 25:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 25:12"/>To all those who have an awesome respect for you, you show them the right way to conduct their lives.<verse eid="PSA 25:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 25:13"/>They will always be prosperous, and their descendants will continue to live in this land.<verse eid="PSA 25:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 25:14"/>Yahweh is a friend of those who have an awesome respect for him, and he teaches them the covenant that he made with them.<verse eid="PSA 25:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 25:15"/>I always request Yahweh to help me, and he rescues me from danger.<verse eid="PSA 25:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 25:16"/>Yahweh, pay attention to me and be merciful to me because I am alone, and I am greatly distressed because I am suffering.<verse eid="PSA 25:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 25:17"/>I have many troubles that make me afraid; rescue me from them.<verse eid="PSA 25:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 25:18"/>Note that I am distressed and troubled, and forgive me for all my sins.<verse eid="PSA 25:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 25:19"/>Note that I have many enemies; you see that they hate me very much.<verse eid="PSA 25:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 25:20"/>Protect me and rescue me from them; do not allow them to defeat me with the result that I would be ashamed; I have gone to you to get refuge.<verse eid="PSA 25:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 25:21"/>Protect me because I do what is good and honest and because I trust in you.<verse eid="PSA 25:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 25:22"/>God, rescue us Israelite people from all of our troubles!<verse eid="PSA 25:22"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 25"/>
<chapter number="26" style="c" sid="PSA 26"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 26:1"/>A psalm written by David; Yahweh, show that I am innocent. I always do what is right; I have trusted in you and never doubted that you would help me.<verse eid="PSA 26:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 26:2"/>Yahweh, examine what I have done and test me; thoroughly evaluate what I think in my inner being.<verse eid="PSA 26:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 26:3"/>I never forget that you are true to your covenant and faithfully love me; I conduct my life according to your faithfulness.<verse eid="PSA 26:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 26:4"/>I do not spend my time with liars, and I stay away from hypocrites.<verse eid="PSA 26:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 26:5"/>I do not like to be with evil people, and I avoid wicked people.<verse eid="PSA 26:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 26:6"/>Yahweh, I wash my hands to show that I am innocent. As I join with others marching around your altar,<verse eid="PSA 26:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 26:7"/>we sing songs to thank you, and we tell others the wonderful things that you have done.<verse eid="PSA 26:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 26:8"/>Yahweh, I love to be in the house where you live, in the place where your glory appears.<verse eid="PSA 26:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 26:9"/>Do not get rid of me like you get rid of sinners; do not cause me to die like you cause those who murder people to die,<verse eid="PSA 26:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 26:10"/>people who are ready to do wicked things and those who are always taking bribes.<verse eid="PSA 26:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 26:11"/>But as for me, I always try to do what is right. So act kindly toward me and rescue me.<verse eid="PSA 26:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 26:12"/>I stand in places where I am safe, and when all your people gather together, I praise you.<verse eid="PSA 26:12"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 26"/>
<chapter number="27" style="c" sid="PSA 27"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 27:1"/>A psalm written by David; Yahweh is the one who gives me life and the one who saves me, so I do not need to be afraid of anyone. Yahweh is the one to whom I go for refuge, so I will never be afraid.<verse eid="PSA 27:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 27:2"/>When those who do evil come near me to destroy me, they stumble and fall down.<verse eid="PSA 27:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 27:3"/>Even if an army surrounds me, I will not be afraid. Even if they attack me, I will trust in God.<verse eid="PSA 27:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 27:4"/>There is one thing that I have requested from Yahweh; this is the one thing that I desire: that I may worship in Yahweh’s house every day during my life, that I may see how wonderful Yahweh is, and that I may ask him what he wants me to do.<verse eid="PSA 27:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 27:5"/>He will protect me when I have troubles; he will keep me safe in his sacred tent. He will set me safely on a high rock.<verse eid="PSA 27:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 27:6"/>Then I will triumph over my enemies. I will shout joyfully as I offer sacrifices in his sacred tent, and I will praise Yahweh as I sing.<verse eid="PSA 27:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 27:7"/>Yahweh, listen to me while I call to you. Act kindly toward me and answer my prayer.<verse eid="PSA 27:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 27:8"/>Within my inner being I desire to worship you, so, Yahweh, I will come to your temple to pray to you.<verse eid="PSA 27:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 27:9"/>I am your servant; do not be angry with me, or turn away from me. You have always helped me. You are the one who has saved me, so do not abandon me now.<verse eid="PSA 27:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 27:10"/>Even if my father and mother desert me, Yahweh always takes care of me.<verse eid="PSA 27:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 27:11"/>Yahweh, teach me to do what you want me to do, and lead me on a safe path because I have many enemies.<verse eid="PSA 27:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 27:12"/>Do not allow my enemies to do to me what they want; they say many false things about me and threaten to do violent things to me.<verse eid="PSA 27:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 27:13"/>I would have died if I had not trusted you to be good to me as long as I live.<verse eid="PSA 27:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 27:14"/>So trust in Yahweh! Be strong and courageous, and wait expectantly for him to help you!<verse eid="PSA 27:14"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 27"/>
<chapter number="28" style="c" sid="PSA 28"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 28:1"/>A psalm written by David; Yahweh, I call out to you; You are like a huge rock on top of which I am safe. Do not refuse to answer me because if you are silent, I will soon be with those who are in their graves.<verse eid="PSA 28:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 28:2"/>Listen to me when I call out for you to help me, when I lift up my hands as I face your very holy place in your sacred tent.<verse eid="PSA 28:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 28:3"/>Do not drag me away with wicked people, with those who do wicked deeds, with those who pretend to act peacefully toward others while in their inner beings, they hate them.<verse eid="PSA 28:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 28:4"/>Punish those people in the way that they deserve for what they have done; punish them for their evil deeds.<verse eid="PSA 28:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 28:5"/>Yahweh, they do not pay attention to the wonderful things that you have done and that you have created; so get rid of them permanently and do not let them appear again!<verse eid="PSA 28:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 28:6"/>Praise Yahweh because he has heard me when I called out for him to help me!<verse eid="PSA 28:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 28:7"/>Yahweh makes me strong and protects me like a shield; I trust in him, and he helps me. So I was glad in my inner being, and from my inner being I praise him as I sing to him.<verse eid="PSA 28:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 28:8"/>Yahweh causes us to be strong and protects us; he saves me, the one he appointed to be king.<verse eid="PSA 28:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 28:9"/>Yahweh, save your people; bless those who belong to you. Take care of them like a shepherd takes care of his sheep; take care of them forever.<verse eid="PSA 28:9"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 28"/>
<chapter number="29" style="c" sid="PSA 29"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 29:1"/>A psalm written by David; Mighty people, praise Yahweh! Praise him because he is very glorious and powerful.<verse eid="PSA 29:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 29:2"/>Praise Yahweh with the glory his names deserves. Bow down and worship Yahweh because he is holy and his holiness shines out from him with wonderful beauty.<verse eid="PSA 29:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 29:3"/>Yahweh’s voice is heard above the oceans; the glorious God thunders. He appears over the huge oceans.<verse eid="PSA 29:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 29:4"/>His voice is powerful and majestic.<verse eid="PSA 29:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 29:5"/>Yahweh’s voice breaks great cedar trees, the cedars that grow in Lebanon.<verse eid="PSA 29:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 29:6"/>He causes earthquakes to shake the region of Lebanon as a young cow jumps; he causes Sirion (also called Mount Hermon) to shake as a young bull jumps.<verse eid="PSA 29:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 29:7"/>Yahweh’s voice tells the lightning to flash.<verse eid="PSA 29:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 29:8"/>His voice causes the desert to shake; he shakes the wilderness of Kadesh.<verse eid="PSA 29:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 29:9"/>Yahweh’s voice makes the large trees shake, and strips the leaves from the trees while the people in the temple shout, “Praise God!”<verse eid="PSA 29:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 29:10"/>Yahweh rules over the flood that covered the earth; he is our king who will rule forever.<verse eid="PSA 29:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 29:11"/>Yahweh enables his people to be strong, and he blesses them by causing things to go well for them.<verse eid="PSA 29:11"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 29"/>
<chapter number="30" style="c" sid="PSA 30"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 30:1"/>A psalm written by David for the dedication of the temple; Yahweh, I praise you because you rescued me. You did not allow me to die or my enemies to gloat over me.<verse eid="PSA 30:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 30:2"/>Yahweh, my God, I called out for you to help me when I was wounded, and you healed me.<verse eid="PSA 30:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 30:3"/>You saved me from death. I was nearly dead, but you caused me to become healthy again.<verse eid="PSA 30:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 30:4"/>All you who are faithful to the covenant with Yahweh, sing to praise him! Remember what God, the holy one, has done and thank him!<verse eid="PSA 30:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 30:5"/>When he becomes angry, he is angry for only a very short time, but he is good to us all of our lives. We may cry during the night, but the next morning we will be joyful.<verse eid="PSA 30:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 30:6"/>As for me, I was calm when I said to myself, “No one will defeat me!”<verse eid="PSA 30:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 30:7"/>Yahweh, because you were good to me, at first you caused me to be secure as though I were a high mountain. But then I thought that you had turned away from me, and I became afraid.<verse eid="PSA 30:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 30:8"/>So I called out to you, and I pleaded for you to help me.<verse eid="PSA 30:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 30:9"/>I said, “Yahweh, what will you gain if I die? In what way will it benefit you if I go to the place where the dead people are? When I am dead I will certainly not be able to praise you, and I will not be able to tell others that you are trustworthy!<verse eid="PSA 30:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 30:10"/>Yahweh, listen to me, and act mercifully to me! Yahweh, help me!”<verse eid="PSA 30:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 30:11"/>But now you have healed me, and you have changed me from being sad to dancing joyfully. You have taken away the clothes that showed that I was very sad and given me clothes that showed that I was very joyful.<verse eid="PSA 30:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 30:12"/>So I will not be silent; I will sing out and praise you. Yahweh, you are my God, and I will thank you forever.<verse eid="PSA 30:12"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 30"/>
<chapter number="31" style="c" sid="PSA 31"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 31:1"/>A psalm written by David for the choir director; Yahweh, I have come to you to be protected; do not allow me to be defeated and disgraced. Since you always do what is fair, rescue me!<verse eid="PSA 31:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 31:2"/>Listen to me, and save me right now! Be like a huge rock on which I can be safe and like a strong fort in which I will be secure.<verse eid="PSA 31:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 31:3"/>Yes, you are like my huge rock and my fort; guide me and lead me because I worship you.<verse eid="PSA 31:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 31:4"/>You are the one who protects me, so keep me from falling into the hidden traps that my enemies have set for me.<verse eid="PSA 31:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 31:5"/>Yahweh, you are a God whom I can trust, so I put myself into your care because you will rescue me.<verse eid="PSA 31:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 31:6"/>Yahweh, I hate those who worship useless idols, but I trust in you.<verse eid="PSA 31:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 31:7"/>I will be very glad because you faithfully love me. You see me when I have been afflicted, and you know when I have had troubles.<verse eid="PSA 31:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 31:8"/>You have not allowed my enemies to capture me; instead, you have rescued me from danger.<verse eid="PSA 31:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 31:9"/>But now, Yahweh, act kindly toward me because I am distressed. Because I cry so much, I cannot see well, and I am completely exhausted.<verse eid="PSA 31:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 31:10"/>I have become very weak because I am so miserable; my life is getting shorter. I have become weak because of all my troubles; even my bones are becoming weaker.<verse eid="PSA 31:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 31:11"/>All of my enemies make fun of me, and even my neighbors despise me. Even my friends are afraid of me because they think that you are punishing me. When they see me on the streets, they run away.<verse eid="PSA 31:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 31:12"/>People have forgotten me like they forget people who are dead. They think I am as useless as a broken pot.<verse eid="PSA 31:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 31:13"/>I have heard people slandering me, and they have terrified me. My enemies are making plans to kill me.<verse eid="PSA 31:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 31:14"/>But Yahweh, I trust in you. I say confidently that you are the God I worship.<verse eid="PSA 31:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 31:15"/>My whole life is in your hands; save me from my enemies, from those who pursue me.<verse eid="PSA 31:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 31:16"/>Act kindly toward me and rescue me because you always faithfully love me.<verse eid="PSA 31:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 31:17"/>Yahweh, I call out to you, so do not allow others to disgrace me. I wish that wicked people may be disgraced; I wish that they may go down to the place where the people are silent and dead.<verse eid="PSA 31:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 31:18"/>I wish that you may cause people who tell lies to be unable to speak. Do that to people who are proud and to those who arrogantly accuse others.<verse eid="PSA 31:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 31:19"/>You have stored up many great and good things to do for those who have great respect for you. You do good things for those who go to you to be protected; everyone sees you doing that.<verse eid="PSA 31:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 31:20"/>You hide people in your presence where it is safe, and you protect them from others who plot to kill them. You hide them in safe places where their enemies cannot speak evil at them.<verse eid="PSA 31:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 31:21"/>Praise Yahweh! When my enemies surrounded the city in which I was living, he showed me wonderfully that he faithfully loves me.<verse eid="PSA 31:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 31:22"/>I was afraid and cried out in a hurry, “I have been separated from Yahweh!” but you heard me and answered my cry for help.<verse eid="PSA 31:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 31:23"/>You people who belong to Yahweh, love him! He protects those who are loyal to him, but he punishes the proud; he punishes them severely as they deserve.<verse eid="PSA 31:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 31:24"/>You who confidently expect Yahweh to do great things for you, be strong and be courageous!<verse eid="PSA 31:24"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 31"/>
<chapter number="32" style="c" sid="PSA 32"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 32:1"/>A psalm written by David, which will help people to be wise; Those whom God has forgiven for rebelling against him and those whose sin God does not look at, these are the ones who are truly fortunate!<verse eid="PSA 32:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 32:2"/>Those whose record of sins Yahweh has erased and those who no longer do deceitful things, these are the ones who are truly fortunate!<verse eid="PSA 32:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 32:3"/>When I did not confess my sins, my body was very weak and sick, and I groaned all day long.<verse eid="PSA 32:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 32:4"/>Day and night, Yahweh, you punished me severely. My strength disappeared like water that evaporates on a hot summer day.<verse eid="PSA 32:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 32:5"/>Then I confessed my sins to you; I stopped trying to hide them. I said to myself, “I will tell Yahweh the wrong things that I have done.” When I confessed them, you forgave me, so now I am no longer guilty for my sins.<verse eid="PSA 32:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 32:6"/>Therefore the people who honor you should pray to you when they are in great trouble. If they do that, difficulties will not come on them like a great flood.<verse eid="PSA 32:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 32:7"/>You are like a place where I can hide from my enemies; you protect me from troubles and enable me to shout, praising you for saving me from my enemies.<verse eid="PSA 32:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 32:8"/>Yahweh says to me, “I will instruct you about how you should conduct your life. I will teach you and watch over you.<verse eid="PSA 32:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 32:9"/>Do not be stupid like horses and mules that do not understand anything; they need bits so they will go in the direction you want them to go.”<verse eid="PSA 32:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 32:10"/>Wicked people will have many troubles that will make them sad, but those who trust in Yahweh will experience him faithfully loving them all the time.<verse eid="PSA 32:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 32:11"/>So, all you righteous people, rejoice about what Yahweh has done for you; you whose heart are pure, be glad and shout joyfully!<verse eid="PSA 32:11"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 32"/>
<chapter number="33" style="c" sid="PSA 33"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 33:1"/>You righteous people should shout joyfully to Yahweh because that is what he deserves.<verse eid="PSA 33:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 33:2"/>Praise Yahweh as you play songs on the harp. Praise him as you play harps that have ten strings.<verse eid="PSA 33:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 33:3"/>Sing a new song to him; play those instruments well, and shout joyfully as you play them.<verse eid="PSA 33:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 33:4"/>Yahweh always does what he says that he will do; we can trust that everything that he does is right.<verse eid="PSA 33:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 33:5"/>He loves everything that we do that is just and right. Yahweh helps people all over the earth because he always loves them.<verse eid="PSA 33:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 33:6"/>Yahweh created everything in the sky by commanding it. By what he commanded, he created all the stars.<verse eid="PSA 33:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 33:7"/>He gathered all the water into one huge mass like someone scoops liquid into a container.<verse eid="PSA 33:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 33:8"/>Everyone on the earth should honor Yahweh; everyone on the earth should honor him.<verse eid="PSA 33:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 33:9"/>When he spoke, he created the world. Everything started to exist when he commanded it to be.<verse eid="PSA 33:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 33:10"/>Yahweh stops the other nations from doing the things they want to do. He prevents them from doing the evil things that they plan to do.<verse eid="PSA 33:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 33:11"/>But what Yahweh decides to do will last forever. What he plans to do will never change.<verse eid="PSA 33:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 33:12"/>Yahweh blesses our nation, we who worship him; How fortunate are we, the nation that belongs to him forever!<verse eid="PSA 33:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 33:13"/>Yahweh looks down from heaven and sees all people.<verse eid="PSA 33:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 33:14"/>From where he rules, he looks down on all the people who live on the earth.<verse eid="PSA 33:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 33:15"/>He forms our inner beings, and he sees everything that we do.<verse eid="PSA 33:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 33:16"/>It is not because a king has a great army that he is able to win battles, and it is not because a soldier is very strong that he is able to defeat his enemy.<verse eid="PSA 33:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 33:17"/>It is foolish to think that because horses are very strong, they will be able to win a battle and save their riders.<verse eid="PSA 33:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 33:18"/>Do not forget that Yahweh watches over those who honor him, those who confidently expect him to faithfully love them.<verse eid="PSA 33:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 33:19"/>He saves them from dying before they should die; he preserves them when there is a famine.<verse eid="PSA 33:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 33:20"/>We trust Yahweh to help us; he protects us as a shield protects a soldier.<verse eid="PSA 33:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 33:21"/>We rejoice because of what he has done for us; we trust in him because he is holy.<verse eid="PSA 33:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 33:22"/>Yahweh, we pray that you will always faithfully love us while we confidently expect you to do great things for us.<verse eid="PSA 33:22"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 33"/>
<chapter number="34" style="c" sid="PSA 34"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 34:1"/>A psalm written by David when he pretended to be insane in front of King Abimelech so that the king would send him away; I will always thank Yahweh; I will constantly praise him.<verse eid="PSA 34:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 34:2"/>I will praise Yahweh for what he has done. All those who are oppressed should listen to me and rejoice.<verse eid="PSA 34:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 34:3"/>Join with me in telling others that Yahweh is great! You and I should together proclaim how glorious he is!<verse eid="PSA 34:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 34:4"/>I prayed to Yahweh, and he answered my prayer; he rescued me from all those who caused me to be afraid.<verse eid="PSA 34:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 34:5"/>Those who trust that he will help them will be joyful; they will never have to look down in disgrace.<verse eid="PSA 34:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 34:6"/>I was miserable, but I called out to Yahweh, and he heard me. He rescued me from all my troubles.<verse eid="PSA 34:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 34:7"/>An angel from Yahweh guards those who have an awesome respect for him, and the angel rescues them.<verse eid="PSA 34:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 34:8"/>Try for yourself, and you will experience that Yahweh is good to you! How fortunate are those who trust him to protect them.<verse eid="PSA 34:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 34:9"/>All you who belong to him, have an awesome respect for him! Those who do that will always have the things that they need.<verse eid="PSA 34:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 34:10"/>Lions are usually very strong, but sometimes even young lions are hungry and become weak. However, those who trust in Yahweh will have everything that they need.<verse eid="PSA 34:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 34:11"/>You who are my students, come and listen to me, and I will teach you how to have an awesome respect for Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 34:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 34:12"/>If any of you wants to enjoy life and have a good long life,<verse eid="PSA 34:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 34:13"/>do not speak what is evil! Do not tell lies!<verse eid="PSA 34:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 34:14"/>Refuse to do evil; instead, do what is good! Always try hard to enable people to live peacefully with each other!<verse eid="PSA 34:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 34:15"/>Yahweh carefully watches over those who act righteously; he always responds to them when they call to him for help.<verse eid="PSA 34:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 34:16"/>But Yahweh works against those who do what is evil. After they die, people here on earth will forget them completely.<verse eid="PSA 34:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 34:17"/>Yahweh hears righteous people when they call out to him; he rescues them from all their troubles.<verse eid="PSA 34:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 34:18"/>Yahweh is always ready to help those who are discouraged; he rescues those who have no hope for anything good.<verse eid="PSA 34:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 34:19"/>Righteous people may have many troubles, but Yahweh rescues them from all those troubles.<verse eid="PSA 34:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 34:20"/>Yahweh protects them from being harmed; when their enemies attack them, they will not break any bones of those righteous people.<verse eid="PSA 34:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 34:21"/>Disasters will kill the wicked people, and Yahweh will punish those who oppose righteous people.<verse eid="PSA 34:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 34:22"/>Yahweh will save those who serve him. He will not condemn those who trust in him.<verse eid="PSA 34:22"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 34"/>
<chapter number="35" style="c" sid="PSA 35"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 35:1"/>A psalm written by David; Yahweh, fight against those who fight against me! Fight with my enemies when they fight me!<verse eid="PSA 35:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 35:2"/>Be like a shield to protect me and come to help me!<verse eid="PSA 35:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 35:3"/>Lift up your spear and throw it at those who pursue me! Promise me that you will enable me to defeat my enemies.<verse eid="PSA 35:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 35:4"/>Those who are trying to kill me—make others disgrace and dishonor them. Push back and confuse those who are planning to do evil things to me.<verse eid="PSA 35:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 35:5"/>Send your angel to pursue them and to make them disappear like chaff that the wind blows away.<verse eid="PSA 35:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 35:6"/>Cause the path on which they run to be dark and slippery as your angel pursues them!<verse eid="PSA 35:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 35:7"/>Although I did not do anything wrong to them, they dug a deep pit for me to fall into; they hid a net in which they would catch me.<verse eid="PSA 35:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 35:8"/>Cause them to suddenly experience disaster! Cause their own nets to trap them. Cause them to fall into the pits that they have dug for me, and make them die in them!<verse eid="PSA 35:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 35:9"/>Then I will rejoice in what you, Yahweh, have done for me; I will be glad that you have rescued me.<verse eid="PSA 35:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 35:10"/>With my whole inner being I will say, “There is no one like Yahweh! No one else can rescue helpless people from powerful people. No one else can rescue weak and needy people from those who want to rob them.”<verse eid="PSA 35:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 35:11"/>People who tell lies stand in court and accuse me of doing things that I do not know anything about.<verse eid="PSA 35:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 35:12"/>In return for my doing good things for them, they do evil things to me, with the result that I feel that I am alone.<verse eid="PSA 35:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 35:13"/>When they were ill, I showed that I was sad. I did not eat any food, and I bowed my head as I prayed for them.<verse eid="PSA 35:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 35:14"/>I mourned and bowed my head as I prayed as though it were a friend or my mother for whom I was grieving.<verse eid="PSA 35:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 35:15"/>But when I had troubles, they were all happy about it. They unexpectedly gathered around to make fun of me. Strangers kept striking me; they would not stop.<verse eid="PSA 35:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 35:16"/>People who respect no one ridiculed me and snarled at me.<verse eid="PSA 35:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 35:17"/>Lord, how long will you only watch them doing this? Rescue me from their attacks; Save me from being killed by these men who are attacking me as lions attack other animals!<verse eid="PSA 35:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 35:18"/>Then, when many of your people gather, I will praise you, and I will thank you in front of all of them.<verse eid="PSA 35:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 35:19"/>Do not allow my enemies, who tell lies about me, defeat me and then rejoice about it! Do not allow those who hate me when there is no reason to hate me to laugh about how I suffer!<verse eid="PSA 35:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 35:20"/>They do not speak peacefully to people; instead, they look for ways to tell lies about people in our land who do no harm to anyone.<verse eid="PSA 35:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 35:21"/>They shout at me in order to accuse me; they say, “We saw the wrong things that you did!”<verse eid="PSA 35:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 35:22"/>Yahweh, you have seen these things, so do not be silent! Do not stay far from me!<verse eid="PSA 35:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 35:23"/>Arise, my God, plead my case in court, and successfully defend me!<verse eid="PSA 35:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 35:24"/>Yahweh, my God, because you are righteous, prove that I am innocent so that my enemies will not be able to gloat that I was judged to be guilty.<verse eid="PSA 35:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 35:25"/>Do not allow them to be able to say to themselves, “Yes, we have gotten rid of him just like we desired!”<verse eid="PSA 35:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 35:26"/>Cause those who rejoice about my misfortunes to be completely confused and disgraced; cause those who boast that they are much greater than I am to be disgraced and dishonored!<verse eid="PSA 35:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 35:27"/>But cause those who desire that you declare me innocent to be happy and shout joyfully; cause them to always say, “Yahweh is great! He is delighted to cause things to go well for those who serve him.”<verse eid="PSA 35:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 35:28"/>Then I will proclaim that you act in the right way, and I will praise you all the time.<verse eid="PSA 35:28"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 35"/>
<chapter number="36" style="c" sid="PSA 36"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 36:1"/>A psalm written for the choir director by David, a man who served God faithfully; A continual desire to sin is in the inner beings of wicked people. They consider that they do not need to have an awesome respect for God.<verse eid="PSA 36:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 36:2"/>Because they want to believe good things about themselves, they do not think that God knows and hates their sins.<verse eid="PSA 36:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 36:3"/>Everything that they say is deceitful and full of lies; they no longer do what is good and are no longer wise.<verse eid="PSA 36:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 36:4"/>While they are lying on their beds, they plan to do things to harm others; they are determined to do things that are not good, and they never refuse to do what is evil.<verse eid="PSA 36:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 36:5"/>Yahweh, your faithful love for us reaches as high as the heavens; your faithfulness in doing what you have promised extends up to the clouds.<verse eid="PSA 36:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 36:6"/>Your righteous behavior is as permanent as the highest mountains; your acting justly will continue as long as the deepest oceans will continue. You take care of people and you take care of animals.<verse eid="PSA 36:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 36:7"/>God, your faithful love for us is very precious. You protect us like birds protect their baby birds under their wings .<verse eid="PSA 36:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 36:8"/>You provide for us plenty of food from the abundant supply that you have; your great gifts flow to us like a river.<verse eid="PSA 36:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 36:9"/>You are the one who causes everything to live; your light is what enables us to know the truth about you.<verse eid="PSA 36:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 36:10"/>Continue to faithfully love those who are faithful to you, and protect those who act righteously.<verse eid="PSA 36:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 36:11"/>Do not allow proud people to attack me, or allow wicked people to chase me away.<verse eid="PSA 36:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 36:12"/>Look where evil people have fallen on the ground, defeated; they were thrown down, and they will never rise again.<verse eid="PSA 36:12"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 36"/>
<chapter number="37" style="c" sid="PSA 37"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 37:1"/>A psalm written by David; Do not be bothered by what wicked people do. Do not desire to have the things that people who do wrong have<verse eid="PSA 37:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 37:2"/>because they will soon disappear like grass withers in the hot sun and dries up. Just like some green plants come up but die during the hot summer, evil people will soon die also.<verse eid="PSA 37:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 37:3"/>Trust in Yahweh and do what is good. If you do that, then you will live safely in the land he has given you, and that land will be a place where you can be faithful to God as you live your lives.<verse eid="PSA 37:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 37:4"/>Be delighted with all that Yahweh does for you; if you do that, he will give you the things that you desire most.<verse eid="PSA 37:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 37:5"/>Commit to Yahweh all the things that you plan to do; trust in him, and he will do whatever is needed to help you.<verse eid="PSA 37:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 37:6"/>He will show as clearly as the sunlight that you are innocent; he will show as clearly as the sun at noontime that all the things that you have decided are just.<verse eid="PSA 37:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 37:7"/>Be quiet in Yahweh’s presence and wait patiently for him to do what you want him to do. Do not be bothered when what evil men do is successful, when they are able to do the wicked things that they plan.<verse eid="PSA 37:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 37:8"/>Do not be angry about what wicked people do. Do not want to punish them yourself. Do not be envious of such people because you will only harm yourself if you try to do that.<verse eid="PSA 37:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 37:9"/>Someday Yahweh will get rid of wicked people, but those who trust in him will live safely in the land that he has given to them.<verse eid="PSA 37:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 37:10"/>Soon the wicked will disappear. You will look for them, but they will be gone.<verse eid="PSA 37:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 37:11"/>But those who are humble will live safely in their land. They will happily enjoy living peacefully and having the other good things that Yahweh gives them.<verse eid="PSA 37:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 37:12"/>Wicked people plan to harm righteous people; they snarl at them like wild animals.<verse eid="PSA 37:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 37:13"/>But Yahweh laughs at them because he knows that someday he will judge and punish the wicked people.<verse eid="PSA 37:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 37:14"/>Wicked people pull out their swords and they put strings on their bows, ready to kill people who are poor and to slaughter those who live righteously.<verse eid="PSA 37:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 37:15"/>But they will be killed by their own swords, and their bows will be broken.<verse eid="PSA 37:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 37:16"/>It is good to be righteous even if you do not have many possessions, but it is bad to be wicked even if you are very wealthy<verse eid="PSA 37:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 37:17"/>because Yahweh will completely remove the strength of wicked people, but he will sustain people who live righteously.<verse eid="PSA 37:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 37:18"/>Day by day Yahweh protects those who have not done any evil things; the things that Yahweh gives them will last forever.<verse eid="PSA 37:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 37:19"/>They will survive when calamities occur; when there are famines, they will still have plenty to eat.<verse eid="PSA 37:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 37:20"/>But wicked people will die; just as the beautiful wild flowers in the fields die under the hot sun and disappear like smoke, Yahweh will cause his enemies to suddenly disappear.<verse eid="PSA 37:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 37:21"/>The wicked people borrow money, but they are not able to repay it; righteous people, in contrast, have enough money to give generously to others.<verse eid="PSA 37:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 37:22"/>Those whom Yahweh has blessed will live safely in the land that he has given to them, but he will get rid of those people whom he has cursed.<verse eid="PSA 37:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 37:23"/>Yahweh protects those who do what is pleasing to him, and he will enable them to walk confidently wherever they go;<verse eid="PSA 37:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 37:24"/>even if they stumble, they will not fall down because Yahweh holds them by his hand.<verse eid="PSA 37:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 37:25"/>I was young previously, and now I am an old man, but in all those years, I have never seen that righteous people have been abandoned by Yahweh, nor have I seen that their children needed to beg for food.<verse eid="PSA 37:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 37:26"/>Righteous people are generous and happily lend money to others, and their children are a blessing to them.<verse eid="PSA 37:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 37:27"/>Turn away from doing evil, and do what is good. If you do that, you and your descendants will live in your land forever.<verse eid="PSA 37:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 37:28"/>This will happen because Yahweh likes to see people doing what is just, and he will never forsake righteous people. He will protect them forever; but he will get rid of the children of wicked people.<verse eid="PSA 37:28"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="29" style="v" sid="PSA 37:29"/>Righteous people will own the land that Yahweh promised to give to them, and they will live there forever.<verse eid="PSA 37:29"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="30" style="v" sid="PSA 37:30"/>Righteous people give wise advice to others, and they encourage other people to live rightly.<verse eid="PSA 37:30"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="31" style="v" sid="PSA 37:31"/>They fill their minds with God’s laws; they do not stray from walking on God’s path.<verse eid="PSA 37:31"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="32" style="v" sid="PSA 37:32"/>Those who are evil wait in ambush for righteous people in order to kill them as they walk by.<verse eid="PSA 37:32"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="33" style="v" sid="PSA 37:33"/>But Yahweh will not abandon righteous people and let them fall into their enemies’ hands. He will not allow righteous people to be condemned when someone takes them to a judge to be put on trial.<verse eid="PSA 37:33"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="34" style="v" sid="PSA 37:34"/>Be patient and trust that Yahweh will help you, and walk on his paths. If you do that, he will honor you by giving you the land that he promised, and when he gets rid of the wicked, you will see it happen.<verse eid="PSA 37:34"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="35" style="v" sid="PSA 37:35"/>I have seen that wicked people who act like tyrants sometimes prosper like trees that grow well in fertile soil,<verse eid="PSA 37:35"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="36" style="v" sid="PSA 37:36"/>but when I looked later, they were gone! I searched for them, but Yahweh had caused them to disappear.<verse eid="PSA 37:36"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="37" style="v" sid="PSA 37:37"/>Notice the people who have not done evil things, those who act righteously; their descendants will have peace in their inner beings.<verse eid="PSA 37:37"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="38" style="v" sid="PSA 37:38"/>But Yahweh will get rid of the wicked; he will also get rid of their descendants.<verse eid="PSA 37:38"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="39" style="v" sid="PSA 37:39"/>Yahweh rescues righteous people; in times of trouble he protects them.<verse eid="PSA 37:39"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="40" style="v" sid="PSA 37:40"/>Yahweh helps them and saves them; he rescues them from being attacked by wicked people because they go to him to be protected.<verse eid="PSA 37:40"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 37"/>
<chapter number="38" style="c" sid="PSA 38"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 38:1"/>A psalm written by David, asking God not to forget him; Yahweh, when you are angry with me, do not rebuke me and punish me!<verse eid="PSA 38:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 38:2"/>Now it is as though you have shot your arrows at me and wounded me; it is as though you have struck me and knocked me down.<verse eid="PSA 38:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 38:3"/>Because you have been angry with me, I am suffering great pain. Because of my sin, my whole body is diseased.<verse eid="PSA 38:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 38:4"/>All my sins are like a flood that covers my head; they are like a load that is very heavy; I cannot carry them.<verse eid="PSA 38:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 38:5"/>Because I have done foolish things, I have sores that have become worse, and they stink.<verse eid="PSA 38:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 38:6"/>Sometimes I am bent over, and sometimes I lie prostrate; I mourn all day.<verse eid="PSA 38:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 38:7"/>My body is burning with fever, and I am very ill.<verse eid="PSA 38:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 38:8"/>I am completely exhausted, and I have no strength. I am very distressed in my inner being, and I groan with pain.<verse eid="PSA 38:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 38:9"/>Yahweh, you know that I desire you to heal me; you hear me while I am groaning.<verse eid="PSA 38:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 38:10"/>My heart pounds heavily, and all my strength is gone. I am no longer able to see well.<verse eid="PSA 38:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 38:11"/>My friends and neighbors stay away from me because of my sores; even my own family stays far from me.<verse eid="PSA 38:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 38:12"/>Those who want to kill me set traps to catch me; those who want to harm me discuss the ways that they can get rid of me; they plot against me all day.<verse eid="PSA 38:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 38:13"/>Now I act like a deaf man and do not listen to what they say. I act like a man who cannot talk, and I say nothing to reply to them.<verse eid="PSA 38:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 38:14"/>I act like a man who does not answer when people talk to him because he cannot hear anything.<verse eid="PSA 38:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 38:15"/>But Yahweh, I trust in you. My Lord God, you will answer me.<verse eid="PSA 38:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 38:16"/>I said to you, “Do not cause me to die so that my enemies will rejoice! If troubles overwhelm me, my enemies will do very bad things to me!”<verse eid="PSA 38:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 38:17"/>I say that because I am about to fall down, and I constantly have pain.<verse eid="PSA 38:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 38:18"/>I confess the wrong things that I have done; I am very sorry for the sins that I have committed.<verse eid="PSA 38:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 38:19"/>My enemies are healthy and strong; there are many people who hate me for no reason.<verse eid="PSA 38:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 38:20"/>Those who do evil things to me in return for my doing good things to them oppose me because I try to do what is right.<verse eid="PSA 38:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 38:21"/>Yahweh, do not abandon me! My God, do not stay far from me!<verse eid="PSA 38:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 38:22"/>Lord, you are the one who saves me; Quickly come and help me!<verse eid="PSA 38:22"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 38"/>
<chapter number="39" style="c" sid="PSA 39"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 39:1"/>A psalm written by David for Jeduthun, the choir director; I said to myself, “I will be careful not to sin by the things that I say. I will not say anything to complain to you while wicked people are near to me and can hear me.”<verse eid="PSA 39:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 39:2"/>So I was completely silent, and I did not even talk about things that were good; but it was useless because I began to suffer even more.<verse eid="PSA 39:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 39:3"/>I became very anxious in my inner being. As I thought about my troubles, I became more worried. Then finally I said this:<verse eid="PSA 39:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 39:4"/>“Yahweh, show me how long I will live. Tell me when I will die. Tell me how many years I will live!<verse eid="PSA 39:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 39:5"/>It seems that you have caused me to live only a short time; my lifetime seems nothing to you. The time that all we humans live is as short as a puff of air.<verse eid="PSA 39:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 39:6"/>Then we disappear like a shadow does. It seems that all that we do is for nothing. We sometimes get a lot of money, but we do not even know who will get it after we die.<verse eid="PSA 39:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 39:7"/>So now, Yahweh, I can expect to receive nothing from anyone else. You are the only one from whom I confidently expect to receive blessings.<verse eid="PSA 39:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 39:8"/>Deliver me from the sins that I have committed. Do not allow foolish people to make fun of me.<verse eid="PSA 39:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 39:9"/>I did not say anything when you punished me because I knew that you were the one who caused me to suffer.<verse eid="PSA 39:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 39:10"/>But now, please stop punishing me! If you do not do that, I am about to die because of how you make me suffer.<verse eid="PSA 39:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 39:11"/>When you rebuke someone and punish him for the sin that he has committed, you destroy the things he loves like moths eat away at clothing. Our lives disappear like a puff of air.<verse eid="PSA 39:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 39:12"/>Yahweh, listen to me while I pray; pay attention to me while I cry out to you. Help me while I am crying. I am here on the earth for only a short time, like all my ancestors.<verse eid="PSA 39:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 39:13"/>Now please allow me to be alone and do not punish me anymore so that I may smile and be happy for a while before I die.”<verse eid="PSA 39:13"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 39"/>
<chapter number="40" style="c" sid="PSA 40"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 40:1"/>A psalm written by David for the choir director; I waited patiently for Yahweh to help me, and he listened to me when I called out to him.<verse eid="PSA 40:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 40:2"/>When I had many troubles, it was as though I was in a deep pit. But he lifted me up out of the mud and slime of that pit; he set my feet on a solid rock and enabled me to walk safely.<verse eid="PSA 40:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 40:3"/>He has given me a new song to sing, a song to praise him who is our God. Many people will find out what he has done for me, and they will revere and trust him.<verse eid="PSA 40:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 40:4"/>How fortunate are those who trust Yahweh to protect them, those who do not trust in idols or join with those who worship those false gods.<verse eid="PSA 40:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 40:5"/>O Yahweh, my God, you have done many wonderful things! No one can list all the wonderful things that you have planned for us. If I tried to tell others about all those wonderful things, I would not be able to because there would be too many for me to mention.<verse eid="PSA 40:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 40:6"/>Sacrifices and other offerings are not the things that delight you most. But you have enabled me to hear your commands. Animals burned on the altar and other offerings for our sins are not what you require most.<verse eid="PSA 40:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 40:7"/>So I said to you, “Yahweh, here I am, to obey the laws that have been written in the scroll, things that you want me to do.”<verse eid="PSA 40:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 40:8"/>O my God, I enjoy doing what you desire; I am always thinking about your laws within my inner being.<verse eid="PSA 40:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 40:9"/>When all your people were gathered together, I told them about how you do what is right and how you rescue us. Yahweh, you know that I have not refused to tell that to them.<verse eid="PSA 40:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 40:10"/>I have not kept within me the news that you always act justly; when many of your people have gathered together to worship you, I have told them that you are faithful to us and save us. I have not concealed that you faithfully love us and act loyally toward us.<verse eid="PSA 40:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 40:11"/>Yahweh, do not stop acting mercifully toward me. Because you faithfully love me and are loyal to me, protect me always.<verse eid="PSA 40:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 40:12"/>I have many troubles; I cannot count them. I am now suffering the things that happened because I sinned. I can no longer see because of my tears. The sins that I have committed are more than the hairs on my head. I am very discouraged.<verse eid="PSA 40:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 40:13"/>O Yahweh, please save me! Come quickly to help me!<verse eid="PSA 40:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 40:14"/>Humble those who are happy about my troubles, and cause them to be disgraced. Chase away those who are trying to get rid of me.<verse eid="PSA 40:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 40:15"/>I hope that those who make fun of me will be dismayed when you defeat them.<verse eid="PSA 40:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 40:16"/>But I hope that all those who go to worship you will be very joyful. I hope that those who love you because you saved them will shout repeatedly, “Yahweh is great!”<verse eid="PSA 40:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 40:17"/>As for me, I am poor and needy, but I know that the Lord has not forgotten me. O my God, you are the one who saves and helps me, so please come quickly and help me!<verse eid="PSA 40:17"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 40"/>
<chapter number="41" style="c" sid="PSA 41"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 41:1"/>A psalm written by David for the choir director; How fortunate are those who provide for the poor; Yahweh will rescue those people when they have troubles.<verse eid="PSA 41:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 41:2"/>Yahweh will protect them and allow them to live for a long time. He will enable them to be happy in the land of Israel and will rescue them from their enemies.<verse eid="PSA 41:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 41:3"/>When they are sick, Yahweh will strengthen them and will heal them.<verse eid="PSA 41:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 41:4"/>When I was sick, I said, “Yahweh, act mercifully toward me and heal me; I know that I am sick because I have sinned against you.”<verse eid="PSA 41:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 41:5"/>My enemies say cruel things about me; they say, “How soon will he die, and then everyone will forget about him?”<verse eid="PSA 41:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 41:6"/>When my enemies come to me, they pretend to be concerned about me. They eagerly listen to all the bad news about me. Then they go away and tell everyone what is happening to me.<verse eid="PSA 41:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 41:7"/>All those who hate me whisper to others about me, and they hope that very bad things will happen to me.<verse eid="PSA 41:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 41:8"/>They say, “He will soon die because of his being sick; he will never get up from his bed before he dies.”<verse eid="PSA 41:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 41:9"/>Even a very close friend, whom I trusted very much, who often ate with me, has betrayed me.<verse eid="PSA 41:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 41:10"/>But Yahweh, act mercifully to me, and enable me to become healthy again. When you do that, I will be able to pay back my enemies.<verse eid="PSA 41:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 41:11"/>If you enable me to do that, with the result that my enemies do not defeat me, I will know that you are pleased with me.<verse eid="PSA 41:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 41:12"/>I will know that it is because I have done what is right that you have helped me, and I will know that you will enable me to be with you forever.<verse eid="PSA 41:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 41:13"/>Praise Yahweh, the God whom we Israelites worship; Praise him forever! Amen! I desire that it will be so!<verse eid="PSA 41:13"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 41"/>
<chapter number="42" style="c" sid="PSA 42"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 42:1"/>A psalm written by one of the descendants of Korah for the choir director; In the same way that a deer desires to drink water in a dry place, so I desire you, O God.<verse eid="PSA 42:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 42:2"/>I desire to be with you so desperately, O you, the real God. It is as though I am thirsting for water. I say to myself, “I shall certainly return to the temple in Israel and worship in your presence again, O God!”<verse eid="PSA 42:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 42:3"/>Every day and every night I weep, and the only thing I have to drink is my tears. This is because my enemies are always asking me, “Your God will certainly not help you!”<verse eid="PSA 42:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 42:4"/>I am sorrowful, as I remember when I used to go with the large groups of people to the temple where God dwelt in Jerusalem. On our way to the festival, we would all shout joyfully and sing to thank God for what he had done.<verse eid="PSA 42:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 42:5"/>So now I say to myself, “You certainly should not be sad and troubled! Confidently expect for God to rescue you! Then you will once again praise him, because of how he has saved you”<verse eid="PSA 42:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 42:6"/>O my God, I am discouraged, so I think about you. Your presence is refreshing, like the abundant waters of Jordan River that rush down from the peaks of Mount Hermon and from Mount Mizar.<verse eid="PSA 42:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 42:7"/>I am in turmoil like the rush of loud waterfalls. I am troubled as if many waves were crashing over me.<verse eid="PSA 42:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 42:8"/>Yahweh faithfully loves me every day, and so he causes me to sing to him every night a prayer to God, who keeps me alive.<verse eid="PSA 42:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 42:9"/>I say to God, who is like a huge rock on top of which I am safe {from attackers}, “Surely you have forgotten me! I am living sorrowfully because my enemies are afflicting me”<verse eid="PSA 42:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 42:10"/>My foes are always insulting me. They keep saying to me, “Your God will not help you!” When they insult me like that, it is like wounds that break my bones.<verse eid="PSA 42:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 42:11"/>But now I say to myself, “You certainly should not be sad and troubled! Confidently expect for God to rescue you! Then you will once again praise him, because of how he has saved you.”<verse eid="PSA 42:11"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 42"/>
<chapter number="43" style="c" sid="PSA 43"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 43:1"/>O God, announce that I am innocent. Defend me when people try to accuse me of doing evil, people who are unfaithful to you! Rescue me from people who deceive me and lie about me.<verse eid="PSA 43:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 43:2"/>{I expect you to do this} since you are the God who protects me, and yet you have abandoned me! I am living sorrowfully because my enemies are afflicting me.<verse eid="PSA 43:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 43:3"/>Speak words that drive away my oppressors, as light causes darkness to cease. Say truthful words to me! This will allow me to return to your temple on Mount Zion, where you dwell.<verse eid="PSA 43:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 43:4"/>After I come to Zion, I will go to your altar to worship you, O God, who causes me to be very joyful. There I will praise you, the God whom I worship, by playing the harp.<verse eid="PSA 43:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 43:5"/>But now I say to myself, “You certainly should not be sad and troubled! Confidently expect for God to rescue you! Then you will once again praise him, because of how he has saved you.”<verse eid="PSA 43:5"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 43"/>
<chapter number="44" style="c" sid="PSA 44"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 44:1"/>A psalm written by one of the descendants of Korah for the choir director. God, we ourselves have heard what our ancestors told us. They told us about the amazing wonders that you performed long ago.<verse eid="PSA 44:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 44:2"/>They told us about how you powerfully expelled the ungodly people and settled our ancestors in their land, as one plants a plant. They also told us that you punished those ungodly people and brought our ancestors into the land.<verse eid="PSA 44:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 44:3"/>It was not because our ancestors had a strong military that they conquered the people that lived in that land. Similarly, it was not because they were powerful that they were victorious. Rather, it was because you are powerful and desired to favor them that they did those things, for you delighted in them.<verse eid="PSA 44:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 44:4"/>You rule over me like a king, God. Empower your people to defeat our enemies.<verse eid="PSA 44:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 44:5"/>You empower us to defeat our enemies, and because of you we completely overwhelm those who fight against us.<verse eid="PSA 44:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 44:6"/>I do not trust that I can save myself by using my bow and arrows and my sword.<verse eid="PSA 44:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 44:7"/>This is because you have rescued us from our enemies. This is because you have disgraced our adversaries by defeating them.<verse eid="PSA 44:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 44:8"/>We have always been proud about what God has done for us, and we will thank him forever.<verse eid="PSA 44:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 44:9"/>But now you have rejected us and embarrassed us. When our armies march out to fight a battle, you no longer go with them to empower them to be victorious.<verse eid="PSA 44:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 44:10"/>You have caused us to retreat from our enemies, and they robbed anything they wanted from us.<verse eid="PSA 44:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 44:11"/>You have made us helpless victims to our enemies, like sheep that people are about to kill in order to eat. You have spread us out among many foreign peoples.<verse eid="PSA 44:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 44:12"/>You allowed our enemies to take us captive. It is as though you sold us to them for a very small price. You did not gain any profit from selling us!<verse eid="PSA 44:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 44:13"/>You have caused our neighbors to reproach us. They laugh at us and deride us.<verse eid="PSA 44:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 44:14"/>You caused them to make jokes about our country, and to shake their heads to indicate that they despise us.<verse eid="PSA 44:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 44:15"/>People constantly make me think about how I am disgraceful, and I am completely shameful.<verse eid="PSA 44:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 44:16"/>This happens because people speak harshly to me, My enemies and those who want to harm me shame me.<verse eid="PSA 44:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 44:17"/>All of these things have happened to us, even though we have not ceased from worshipping you, and we have not disobeyed the agreement that you made with our ancestors.<verse eid="PSA 44:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 44:18"/>We have continued to be loyal to you, and we have continued doing what you have commanded us to do.<verse eid="PSA 44:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 44:19"/>But it is as though you have destroyed us in battle, so that our bodies are laying in a place where wild animals could eat them. It is also as though you have thrown us into a very dark place.<verse eid="PSA 44:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 44:20"/>If we had stopped worshipping you, our God, and began worshipping a foreign god,<verse eid="PSA 44:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 44:21"/>you surely would have known that. This is because you know even what we secretly think.<verse eid="PSA 44:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 44:22"/>It is surely because you allow our enemies to attack us that they are constantly killing us. They kill us easily, for we are as defenseless as sheep that people kill in order to eat them.<verse eid="PSA 44:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 44:23"/>Defend us, Yahweh! It certainly seems as though you are asleep! Help us! Do not treat us as though we are not your people forever!<verse eid="PSA 44:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 44:24"/>You certainly are not favoring us! You surely are not saving us from our afflicters and oppressors.<verse eid="PSA 44:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 44:25"/>We have fallen down hopelessly, with our bellies on the ground.<verse eid="PSA 44:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 44:26"/>Rescue us! Come and help us! Save us from our enemies, for you promised to love us faithfully.<verse eid="PSA 44:26"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 44"/>
<chapter number="45" style="c" sid="PSA 45"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 45:1"/>A love song written by one of the descendants of Korah for the choir director, to be sung to the tune “Lilies.” In my inner being I am aroused by something beautiful to write about, a song that I will sing to the king. The words of this song will be written by me, a skilled writer.<verse eid="PSA 45:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 45:2"/>O King, you are the most handsome man in the world, and you always speak eloquently! So we know that God has always blessed you.<verse eid="PSA 45:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 45:3"/>You who are a mighty warrior, put on your sword! You are glorious and majestic.<verse eid="PSA 45:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 45:4"/>Ride on like a great king to defend the truth that you speak and the fair decisions that you make! Because you fight in many battles, you will learn to do deeds that your enemies will fear.<verse eid="PSA 45:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 45:5"/>Your arrows are sharp, and they pierce the hearts of your enemies. Soldiers of many nations will fall at your feet.<verse eid="PSA 45:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 45:6"/>The kingdom that God will give to you will remain forever. You rule over people justly.<verse eid="PSA 45:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 45:7"/>You love right actions, and you hate evil actions. Therefore God, your God, has chosen you to be king and has caused you to be happier than any other king.<verse eid="PSA 45:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 45:8"/>The perfume of various spices is on your robes. Musicians entertain you in ivory palaces by playing stringed instruments.<verse eid="PSA 45:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 45:9"/>Among your wives are daughters of other kings. At your right hand stands your bride, the queen, wearing beautiful ornaments of gold that comes from Ophir.<verse eid="PSA 45:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 45:10"/>Now I will say something to your bride: “Listen to me carefully! Forget the people who live in your home country, forget your relatives!<verse eid="PSA 45:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 45:11"/>Because you are very beautiful, the king will desire to be with you. He is your master, so you must obey him.<verse eid="PSA 45:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 45:12"/>The people from the city of Tyre will bring gifts to you; their rich people will try to persuade you to do favors for them.<verse eid="PSA 45:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 45:13"/>You, the king’s bride, enter the palace wearing beautiful robes made from gold thread.”<verse eid="PSA 45:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 45:14"/>O king, while she is wearing a gown that has many colors, her woman servants will lead her to you. She will have many other young women who accompany her.<verse eid="PSA 45:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 45:15"/>They will be very joyful as they are led along to enter your palace.<verse eid="PSA 45:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 45:16"/>Someday, your sons and your grandsons will become kings, just as your ancestors were. You will enable them to become rulers in many countries.<verse eid="PSA 45:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 45:17"/>As for me, I will enable people in every generation to remember the great things that you have done, and people will praise you forever.<verse eid="PSA 45:17"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 45"/>
<chapter number="46" style="c" sid="PSA 46"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 46:1"/>A psalm written by one of the descendants of Korah for the choir director. God is the one who protects us and causes us to be strong; he is always ready to help us when we have troubles.<verse eid="PSA 46:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 46:2"/>So, even if the earth shakes, we will not be afraid. Even if the mountains fall into the middle of the sea,<verse eid="PSA 46:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 46:3"/>and if the water in the sea roars and foams, and if the hills shake violently, we will not be afraid!<verse eid="PSA 46:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 46:4"/>Blessings that come from God are like a river that makes everyone in the city joyful, there where we worship him. It is the city where the temple of God, who is greater than any other god, exists.<verse eid="PSA 46:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 46:5"/>God is in this city, and it will never be destroyed; he will come to help the people in that city at dawn every day.<verse eid="PSA 46:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 46:6"/>Sometimes the people of many nations are terrified; kingdoms are overthrown; God speaks loudly like thunder, and the earth melts.<verse eid="PSA 46:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 46:7"/>But Yahweh, commander of the angel armies, is with us; the God whom Jacob worshiped is our refuge.<verse eid="PSA 46:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 46:8"/>Come and see the things that Yahweh does! Come and see the things he has destroyed all over the earth.<verse eid="PSA 46:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 46:9"/>He stops wars all over the world; he breaks bows and arrows; he destroys spears; he burns up shields.<verse eid="PSA 46:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 46:10"/>God says, “Be quiet and remember that I am God! People of all nations will honor me. People all over the earth will honor me.”<verse eid="PSA 46:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 46:11"/>So never forget that Yahweh, commander of the angel armies, is with us; the God whom Jacob worshiped is our refuge.<verse eid="PSA 46:11"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 46"/>
<chapter number="47" style="c" sid="PSA 47"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 47:1"/>A psalm written by one of the descendants of Korah for the choir director; You people all over the world, clap your hands! Shout joyfully to praise God!<verse eid="PSA 47:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 47:2"/>Yahweh, who is much greater than any other god, is awesome; he is a king who rules over all the world!<verse eid="PSA 47:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 47:3"/>He enabled us to defeat the armies of the people groups that lived in Canaan.<verse eid="PSA 47:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 47:4"/>He chose for us this land where we now live; we Israelite people, whom he loves, are proud that we own this land.<verse eid="PSA 47:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 47:5"/>God has gone up into his temple. The people shouted joyfully and blew trumpets as he went up.<verse eid="PSA 47:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 47:6"/>Sing songs to praise our God! Sing to praise him ! Sing to God, our king!<verse eid="PSA 47:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 47:7"/>God is the one who rules over everything in the world; sing a psalm to him!<verse eid="PSA 47:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 47:8"/>God sits on his sacred throne as he rules over the people of all ethnic groups.<verse eid="PSA 47:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 47:9"/>The rulers of those people groups gather in front of God’s people, the people descended from Abraham. God has more power than the weapons of all the kings on the earth; he is great, and all people everywhere will honor him.<verse eid="PSA 47:9"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 47"/>
<chapter number="48" style="c" sid="PSA 48"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 48:1"/>A psalm written by one of the descendants of Korah; Yahweh is great, and he deserves to be greatly praised in the city where he lives, which is built on Zion, his sacred hill.<verse eid="PSA 48:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 48:2"/>That city on a high hill is beautiful; it is the city where the true God, the great king, lives, and it causes people all over the world to rejoice when they see it.<verse eid="PSA 48:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 48:3"/>God is in the strong towers there, and he shows that he protects the people in that city.<verse eid="PSA 48:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 48:4"/>Many kings gathered with their armies to attack our city,<verse eid="PSA 48:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 48:5"/>but when they saw it, they were amazed; they became terrified, and ran away.<verse eid="PSA 48:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 48:6"/>Because they were very afraid, they trembled like a woman who is about to give birth to a child.<verse eid="PSA 48:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 48:7"/>They shook as ships sailing from Tarshish shake in a strong wind.<verse eid="PSA 48:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 48:8"/>We had heard that this city was glorious, and now we have seen that it is. It is the city in which Yahweh, commander of the angel armies, lives. It is the city that God will preserve forever.<verse eid="PSA 48:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 48:9"/>God, here in your temple we think about how you love us as you promised to do.<verse eid="PSA 48:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 48:10"/>People all over the earth will praise you because you rule powerfully and justly.<verse eid="PSA 48:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 48:11"/>The people who live at Mount Zion should be happy! The people in all the cities of Judah should rejoice because you judge people fairly.<verse eid="PSA 48:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 48:12"/>You Israelite people should walk around Mount Zion and count the towers there;<verse eid="PSA 48:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 48:13"/>notice the walls there and examine their strongest parts so that you can tell your children about them.<verse eid="PSA 48:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 48:14"/>Say to your children, “This is the city of our God, the one who lives forever; he will guide us during all of our lives.”<verse eid="PSA 48:14"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 48"/>
<chapter number="49" style="c" sid="PSA 49"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 49:1"/>A psalm written by one of the descendants of Korah for the choir director. You people of all people groups, listen! You people all over the world,<verse eid="PSA 49:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 49:2"/>important people and unimportant people, rich people and poor people, everyone, listen to what I am saying.<verse eid="PSA 49:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 49:3"/>For what I am thinking is very sensible, and what I say will enable you to become wise.<verse eid="PSA 49:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 49:4"/>I think about wise words to tell you, and while I play my harp, I explain what they mean.<verse eid="PSA 49:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 49:5"/>I do not worry when I am in trouble, when I am surrounded by my enemies.<verse eid="PSA 49:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 49:6"/>These are evil men who trust that things will always go well for them because they are wealthy and who boast about being very rich.<verse eid="PSA 49:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 49:7"/>They may be rich, but no one can pay God money so that he can live forever! No one can pay God enough so that God will allow him to continue to live<verse eid="PSA 49:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 49:8"/>because that cost is too much, and he will never be able to pay enough.<verse eid="PSA 49:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 49:9"/>No one can pay God enough money so that he will live forever and never die and be buried!<verse eid="PSA 49:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 49:10"/>We see that foolish and stupid people die, but we see that wise people also die; they all leave their wealth, and others inherit it.<verse eid="PSA 49:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 49:11"/>They once had houses on land that they owned, but now their graves are their homes forever, the place where they will stay for all time!<verse eid="PSA 49:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 49:12"/>Even if people are great, that cannot prevent them from dying; people all die, the same as the animals do.<verse eid="PSA 49:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 49:13"/>That is what happens to those who foolishly trust in what they have accomplished, to those who are delighted in all that they possess.<verse eid="PSA 49:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 49:14"/>They are certain to die just like sheep when a shepherd leads them away to be slaughtered. In the morning the righteous people will rule over them, and then those wealthy people will die and their bodies will quickly decay in their graves; they will be where dead people are, far from their homes.<verse eid="PSA 49:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 49:15"/>But it is certain that God will rescue me so that I am not held fast in the place of the dead; he will take me to himself.<verse eid="PSA 49:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 49:16"/>So do not be dismayed when someone becomes rich and the houses where they live become more and more luxurious;<verse eid="PSA 49:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 49:17"/>for when he dies, he will take nothing with him; his wealth will not go with him.<verse eid="PSA 49:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 49:18"/>While a rich person is alive, he congratulates himself, and people praise him for being successful,<verse eid="PSA 49:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 49:19"/>but he will die and join his ancestors, who will never see daylight again.<verse eid="PSA 49:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 49:20"/>Even if someone is great, that cannot prevent him from dying; he will die, the same as the animals do.<verse eid="PSA 49:20"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 49"/>
<chapter number="50" style="c" sid="PSA 50"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 50:1"/>A psalm written by Asaph; God, the all-powerful one, speaks; he summons all people, from the east to the west.<verse eid="PSA 50:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 50:2"/>His glory shines from Mount Zion in Jerusalem, an extremely beautiful city.<verse eid="PSA 50:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 50:3"/>Our God comes to us, and he is not silent. A great fire is in front of him, and a storm is around him.<verse eid="PSA 50:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 50:4"/>He comes to judge his people. He shouts to the angels in heaven and to the people on the earth.<verse eid="PSA 50:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 50:5"/>He says, “Summon those who faithfully worship me, those who made a covenant with me by offering sacrifices to me.”<verse eid="PSA 50:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 50:6"/>The angels in heaven declare, “God is righteous, and he is the supreme judge.”<verse eid="PSA 50:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 50:7"/>God says, “My people, listen! You Israelite people, listen, as I, your God, say what you have done that is wrong.<verse eid="PSA 50:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 50:8"/>I am not rebuking you for making sacrifices to me, for the offerings that you always burn on the altar for me.<verse eid="PSA 50:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 50:9"/>But I do not really need the bulls from your barns and the goats from your pens that you sacrifice,<verse eid="PSA 50:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 50:10"/>because all the animals in the forest belong to me, and all the cattle on a thousand hills also belong to me.<verse eid="PSA 50:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 50:11"/>I know and own all the birds in the mountains, and all the creatures that move around in the fields.<verse eid="PSA 50:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 50:12"/>So if I were hungry, I would not tell you to bring me some food because everything in the world belongs to me!<verse eid="PSA 50:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 50:13"/>I do not eat the flesh of the bulls that you sacrifice, and I do not drink the blood of the goats that you offer to me.<verse eid="PSA 50:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 50:14"/>The sacrifice that I really want is that you thank me and do all that you have promised to do.<verse eid="PSA 50:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 50:15"/>Pray to me when you have troubles. If you do that, I will rescue you, and then you will praise me.<verse eid="PSA 50:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 50:16"/>But I say this to the wicked people: Why do you recite my commandments or talk about the covenant that I made with you?<verse eid="PSA 50:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 50:17"/>For you have refused to allow me to discipline you, and you have rejected what I told you to do.<verse eid="PSA 50:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 50:18"/>Every time that you see a thief, you become his friend, and you spend much time with those who commit adultery.<verse eid="PSA 50:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 50:19"/>You are always talking about doing wicked things, and you are always trying to deceive people.<verse eid="PSA 50:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 50:20"/>You are always accusing members of your own family and slandering them.<verse eid="PSA 50:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 50:21"/>You did all those things, and I did not say anything to you, so you thought that I was a sinner just like you. But now I rebuke you and accuse you, right in front of you.<verse eid="PSA 50:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 50:22"/>So, all you who have ignored me, pay attention to this, because if you do not, I will tear you to pieces, and there will be no one to rescue you.<verse eid="PSA 50:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 50:23"/>The sacrifice that truly honors me is to thank me for what I have done; and I will save those who always do the things that I want them to.”<verse eid="PSA 50:23"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 50"/>
<chapter number="51" style="c" sid="PSA 51"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 51:1"/>A psalm written by David for the choir director, concerning the time when the prophet Nathan rebuked David after he had committed adultery with Bathsheba. O God, act mercifully toward me because you love me faithfully; because you are very merciful, forget the ways that I disobeyed you!<verse eid="PSA 51:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 51:2"/>Make me acceptable to you again, even though I did wrong things; forgive the guilt of my sin and accept me.<verse eid="PSA 51:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 51:3"/>I say that because I know the ways that I have disobeyed you; I cannot forget them.<verse eid="PSA 51:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 51:4"/>You, you only, are the one I have really sinned against, and you have seen the evil things that I have done. When you say that I am guilty, you are right, and when you judge me, you justly say that I deserve to be punished.<verse eid="PSA 51:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 51:5"/>I have been a sinner since the day that I was born; truly, I have been like that since my mother conceived me.<verse eid="PSA 51:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 51:6"/>What you desire is that in my inner being I desire what is true in order that you can teach me how to act wisely.<verse eid="PSA 51:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 51:7"/>Forgive the guilt of my sins, and after that happens, I will be completely acceptable to you; if you forgive me, then I will be absolutely right with you.<verse eid="PSA 51:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 51:8"/>Allow me to rejoice again; you have made me immeasurably sad, but now let me rejoice again.<verse eid="PSA 51:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 51:9"/>Do not continue to remember the sins that I have committed; forget the evil things that I have done.<verse eid="PSA 51:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 51:10"/>O God, make me want to do the things that you approve of. Make me want to do only what is right.<verse eid="PSA 51:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 51:11"/>Do not reject me as one of your people, and do not make your holy Spirit leave me.<verse eid="PSA 51:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 51:12"/>Make me happy again by rescuing me from my guilt, and always help me by making me sincerely want to obey you.<verse eid="PSA 51:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 51:13"/>If you do that, I will teach other sinners what you want them to do; they will repent and obey you.<verse eid="PSA 51:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 51:14"/>O God, you are the one who saves me; forgive me for being guilty of causing someone who was not my enemy to die. When you do that, I will sing joyfully about your being very good and righteous.<verse eid="PSA 51:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 51:15"/>O Yahweh, help me to speak in order that I may praise you.<verse eid="PSA 51:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 51:16"/>When people only bring sacrifices to you, that does not please you. If that were enough to please you, I would do the same. But you are not pleased with burnt offerings alone.<verse eid="PSA 51:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 51:17"/>The sacrifice that you really want is for people to be truly humble and sorry for having sinned. O God, you will not refuse that kind of sacrifice.<verse eid="PSA 51:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 51:18"/>O God, be good to the people who live in Jerusalem; make them able to rebuild the city walls.<verse eid="PSA 51:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 51:19"/>When that happens, they will bring you the proper sacrifices: normal animal sacrifices and sacrifices to be completely burned. They will burn young bulls on your altar, and you will be pleased.<verse eid="PSA 51:19"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 51"/>
<chapter number="52" style="c" sid="PSA 52"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 52:1"/>A psalm written by David for the choir director when Doeg went to Saul and said, “David has gone to talk with Ahimelech, the high priest.” You proud man, you think that you are strong; you boast about the trouble that you make for others, but God faithfully protects people from you every day.<verse eid="PSA 52:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 52:2"/>All during the day you plan to get rid of others; what you say is like a sharp blade, and you are always deceiving others.<verse eid="PSA 52:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 52:3"/>You like doing what is evil more than you like doing what is good, and you like telling lies more than you like telling the truth.<verse eid="PSA 52:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 52:4"/>You, the one who says things to deceive people, you like to say things that hurt people!<verse eid="PSA 52:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 52:5"/>But God will get rid of you forever; he will grab you and drag you from your home and take you away from this world where people are alive.<verse eid="PSA 52:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 52:6"/>When righteous people see that, they will be awestruck, and they will laugh at what happened to you, and say,<verse eid="PSA 52:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 52:7"/>“Look what happened to the man who would not ask God to protect him; he trusted that his great wealth would save him; he grew more powerful by wickedly hurting other people.”<verse eid="PSA 52:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 52:8"/>But I am secure because I worship in God’s temple; I am like a strong green olive tree. I trust in God, who faithfully loves us forever.<verse eid="PSA 52:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 52:9"/>God, I will always thank you for everything you have done. I will wait patiently because you are so good, especially when I stand before your faithful people.<verse eid="PSA 52:9"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 52"/>
<chapter number="53" style="c" sid="PSA 53"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 53:1"/>A psalm written by David for the choir director, to be sung using a tune called “Mahalath.” Only foolish people say to themselves, “There is no God!” People who say that are corrupt; they commit terrible sins; there is not one of them who does what is good.<verse eid="PSA 53:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 53:2"/>God looks down from heaven and sees humans; he looks to see if any man is very wise and seeks to know God.<verse eid="PSA 53:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 53:3"/>But everyone has turned away from God. They are depraved and do disgusting, filthy things. No one does what is good.<verse eid="PSA 53:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 53:4"/>Will all these evil people never learn what God will do to them? They hurt Yahweh’s people with terrible violence. They had no guilt in what they did. They had the same expression on their faces as people eating bread at dinner. And what is worse is that they never prayed to Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 53:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 53:5"/>But someday those people will become very terrified, although they have nothing to fear. For God will cause those who attack you to die, and he will scatter their bones. They have rejected God, so he will cause them to be defeated and completely disgraced.<verse eid="PSA 53:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 53:6"/>I wish that God would come and rescue the Israelite people! God, when you bless your people again, all the Israelite people, all the descendants of Jacob, will rejoice.<verse eid="PSA 53:6"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 53"/>
<chapter number="54" style="c" sid="PSA 54"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 54:1"/>A psalm written by David for the choir director, to be accompanied by stringed instruments; it was written when the people of Ziph went to Saul and told him that David was hiding in their area. God, by your power save me from my enemies, and show people that I have not done anything that is wrong!<verse eid="PSA 54:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 54:2"/>God, listen to my prayer; listen to what I say to you<verse eid="PSA 54:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 54:3"/>because strangers are trying to attack me; proud men are wanting to kill me, men who have no respect for you.<verse eid="PSA 54:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 54:4"/>But God is the one who helps me; Yahweh defends me from my enemies.<verse eid="PSA 54:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 54:5"/>He will cause the evil things that they want to do to me to happen to them instead; because you faithfully do what you have promised to me, destroy them.<verse eid="PSA 54:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 54:6"/>Yahweh, I will gladly give an offering to you because I want to, and I will thank you, for you are good to me;<verse eid="PSA 54:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 54:7"/>you have rescued me from all my troubles, and I have seen that you have defeated my enemies.<verse eid="PSA 54:7"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 54"/>
<chapter number="55" style="c" sid="PSA 55"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 55:1"/>A psalm written by David for the choir director, to be accompanied by stringed instruments; God, listen to my prayer, and do not turn away from me while I am pleading with you.<verse eid="PSA 55:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 55:2"/>Listen to me and answer me because I am overwhelmed by all my troubles.<verse eid="PSA 55:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 55:3"/>My enemies terrify me; wicked people oppress me. They cause me to have great troubles; they are angry with me, and they hate me.<verse eid="PSA 55:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 55:4"/>I am terrified, and I am very much afraid that I will die.<verse eid="PSA 55:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 55:5"/>I am very fearful and I tremble; I am completely terrified.<verse eid="PSA 55:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 55:6"/>I said, “I wish that I had wings like a dove! If I had wings, I would fly away and find a place to rest.<verse eid="PSA 55:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 55:7"/>I would fly far away and live in the wilderness.<verse eid="PSA 55:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 55:8"/>I would quickly find a safe place where my enemies could not strike me like a strong wind and rainstorm.”<verse eid="PSA 55:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 55:9"/>Lord, confuse my enemies and cause their plans to fail. I saw them hurting others by their violence and causing riots throughout the city.<verse eid="PSA 55:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 55:10"/>During each day and night they march around on top of its walls, committing crimes and causing trouble.<verse eid="PSA 55:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 55:11"/>They destroy things everywhere. They oppress people and defraud people in the marketplaces.<verse eid="PSA 55:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 55:12"/>If it were an enemy who was making fun of me, I could endure it. If it were someone who hates me, who despises me, I could hide from him.<verse eid="PSA 55:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 55:13"/>But it is someone who is just like me, my companion, someone who was my friend who is doing this to me.<verse eid="PSA 55:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 55:14"/>We previously had many good talks together; we walked around together in God’s temple.<verse eid="PSA 55:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 55:15"/>I desire that my enemies will go down alive to the place where the dead people are. I want this because they do evil things in their homes.<verse eid="PSA 55:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 55:16"/>But I will ask Yahweh, my God, to help me, and he will save me.<verse eid="PSA 55:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 55:17"/>Each morning, noontime, and evening I tell him what I am concerned about, and I moan, and he hears my voice.<verse eid="PSA 55:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 55:18"/>He saves my life and makes me safe when I am fighting a terrible battle against my enemies. There are many enemies coming to fight against me!<verse eid="PSA 55:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 55:19"/>God is the one who has ruled everything forever, and he will put those who fought against me in their place. He will cause my enemies to be defeated and disgraced because they do not change their evil behavior and because they do not have any respect for God.<verse eid="PSA 55:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 55:20"/>My companion, whom I mentioned previously, betrayed his friends and broke the agreement that he made with them.<verse eid="PSA 55:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 55:21"/>What he said was as easy to listen to as butter is easy to swallow, but in his inner being he hated people; his words were as soothing as olive oil, but they hurt people as sharp swords do.<verse eid="PSA 55:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 55:22"/>Put your troubles in Yahweh’s hands, and he will take care of you; he will never allow disaster to destroy righteous people.<verse eid="PSA 55:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 55:23"/>God, you will cause murderers and liars to die before they have lived half as long as they expect to live; but as for me, I will trust in you.<verse eid="PSA 55:23"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 55"/>
<chapter number="56" style="c" sid="PSA 56"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 56:1"/>A psalm written by David for the choir director, concerning the time the Philistines seized David in Gath; to be sung using the tune “Dove on distant oaks.” God, act mercifully toward me because men are attacking me! All day long an enemy presses closer and closer to me because they want to take my life.<verse eid="PSA 56:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 56:2"/>All day long my enemies seek to crush the life from me, there are many enemies attacking me!<verse eid="PSA 56:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 56:3"/>But whenever I am afraid, I trust in you.<verse eid="PSA 56:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 56:4"/>God, I praise you because you do what you have promised; I trust in you, and then I am not afraid. Ordinary humans certainly cannot harm me!<verse eid="PSA 56:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 56:5"/>All day long my enemies claim that I said things that I did not say; they are always thinking of ways to harm me.<verse eid="PSA 56:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 56:6"/>In order to cause trouble for me, they hide and watch everything that I do, waiting for an opportunity to kill me.<verse eid="PSA 56:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 56:7"/>So, God, punish them for the wicked things that they are doing; show that you are angry by defeating those people!<verse eid="PSA 56:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 56:8"/>You have counted all the times that I have been wandering alone; it is as though you have put all my tears in a bottle so that you can see how much I have cried. You have counted my tears and written the number in your book.<verse eid="PSA 56:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 56:9"/>When I call out to you, my God, my enemies will be defeated; I know that will happen because you are fighting for me.<verse eid="PSA 56:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 56:10"/>I praise you that you do what you have promised; Yahweh, I will always praise you for that.<verse eid="PSA 56:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 56:11"/>I trust in you, and as a result, I will not be afraid. I know that humans cannot really harm me!<verse eid="PSA 56:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 56:12"/>I will bring to you the offering that I promised; I will bring an offering to you to thank you<verse eid="PSA 56:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 56:13"/>because you have rescued me from being killed; you have kept me from stumbling. And so I will continue to live with God every day in his light that gives me life.<verse eid="PSA 56:13"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 56"/>
<chapter number="57" style="c" sid="PSA 57"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 57:1"/>A psalm written by David for the choir director, when David went into a cave to escape from Saul; to be sung using the tune “Do not destroy.” God, act mercifully toward me! Act mercifully toward me because I am coming to you to protect me. I request you to protect me as little birds are protected under their mother’s wings until the storm is ended.<verse eid="PSA 57:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 57:2"/>God, you who are greater than all other gods, I cry out to you, the one who enables me to be all that you desire.<verse eid="PSA 57:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 57:3"/>You will answer me from heaven and rescue me, but you will cause those who oppress me to be defeated and disgraced! God will always faithfully love me as he has promised me.<verse eid="PSA 57:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 57:4"/>Sometimes I am surrounded by my enemies, who are as ready to kill me as lions are to kill people; they are like lions that chew to bits the animals that they kill. But my enemies are human, and they have spears and arrows, not teeth; they say false things about me.<verse eid="PSA 57:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 57:5"/>God, show in the heavens that you are very great! Show your glory to people all over the earth!<verse eid="PSA 57:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 57:6"/>It is as if my enemies have spread a net to seize me, and I became very distressed. It is as if they have dug a deep pit along the path where I walk, but they themselves fell into it!<verse eid="PSA 57:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 57:7"/>God, I am very confident in you. I will sing to you, and I will praise you while I sing.<verse eid="PSA 57:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 57:8"/>It is an honor to wake up and praise you. I will arise before the sun rises and praise you while I play my big harp or my lyre.<verse eid="PSA 57:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 57:9"/>Lord, I will thank you among all the people; and I will sing songs of praise about you to many people groups.<verse eid="PSA 57:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 57:10"/>For your love for us is as great as the distance from the earth to the sky, and your faithfulness to us goes up to the clouds.<verse eid="PSA 57:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 57:11"/>God, show in the heavens that you are very great! Show your glory to people all over the earth!<verse eid="PSA 57:11"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 57"/>
<chapter number="58" style="c" sid="PSA 58"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 58:1"/>A psalm written by David for the choir director, to be sung using the tune “Do not destroy.” When you rulers speak, you never say what is right; you people never justly decide disputes.<verse eid="PSA 58:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 58:2"/>No, in your inner beings you think only about doing what is wrong, and you commit violent crimes everywhere in this land of Israel.<verse eid="PSA 58:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 58:3"/>Wicked people do wrong things and tell lies from the time that they are born.<verse eid="PSA 58:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 58:4"/>What wicked people say injures people like the venom of a snake. They refuse to listen to commands; it is as though they were deaf cobras.<verse eid="PSA 58:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 58:5"/>As a result, like a snake that does not respond when a charmer plays a flute or when someone sings magic songs, they do not pay attention when others rebuke them.<verse eid="PSA 58:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 58:6"/>God, as for these enemies who want to attack me like young lions, break the teeth in their mouths!<verse eid="PSA 58:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 58:7"/>Cause them to disappear as water disappears in dry ground! Cause the arrows that they shoot to have no heads!<verse eid="PSA 58:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 58:8"/>Cause them to become like snails that disappear in the slime; cause them to be like a baby that is born dead!<verse eid="PSA 58:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 58:9"/>I hope that you will get rid of them as fast as thornbushes are blown away after they are cut.<verse eid="PSA 58:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 58:10"/>People who do what is right will rejoice when they see God punish the wicked people; they will wash their feet in the blood of wicked people.<verse eid="PSA 58:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 58:11"/>Then people will say, “It is true that there is a reward for righteous people; and there is indeed a God who judges people justly here on the earth!”<verse eid="PSA 58:11"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 58"/>
<chapter number="59" style="c" sid="PSA 59"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 59:1"/>A psalm written by David for the choir director, when Saul, wanting to kill David, sent men to watch David’s house. God, save me from my enemies! Protect me from those who want to attack me!<verse eid="PSA 59:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 59:2"/>Keep me safe from men who want to do what is wicked, from men who are murderers!<verse eid="PSA 59:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 59:3"/>Look! They are waiting to kill me! Fierce men have gathered to assault me. Yahweh, they are doing that even though I have not done what is wrong!<verse eid="PSA 59:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 59:4"/>It is not because I have committed any sin against them that they run and get ready to attack me. Please look at my situation and help me.<verse eid="PSA 59:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 59:5"/>Yahweh my God, commander of the angel armies, the one we Israelites worship, arise and punish the people of all the nations who do not honor you; do not act mercifully toward those wicked people who have acted treacherously toward us.<verse eid="PSA 59:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 59:6"/>They return each evening, snarling like vicious dogs as they prowl around this city.<verse eid="PSA 59:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 59:7"/>They loudly say terrible things; they say things that destroy as much as swords do, because they are saying, “No one will hear us!”<verse eid="PSA 59:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 59:8"/>But Yahweh, you laugh at them. You scoff at the people of the pagan nations.<verse eid="PSA 59:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 59:9"/>God, I have confidence in you because you are very strong; you are my refuge.<verse eid="PSA 59:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 59:10"/>Because you love me, you will come to save me as you have promised; you will allow me to watch while you defeat my enemies.<verse eid="PSA 59:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 59:11"/>But do not kill them immediately; it is good that my people should not forget how you punished them! Instead, Lord, you who are like a shield that protects us, scatter them by your power, and then defeat them.<verse eid="PSA 59:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 59:12"/>Because what they say is sinful, allow them to be trapped for being proud. Because they are always cursing and telling lies,<verse eid="PSA 59:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 59:13"/>because you are angry, get rid of them; destroy them completely so that people will know that you rule over us, your Israelite people, and that you rule over all the earth.<verse eid="PSA 59:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 59:14"/>They return each evening, snarling like vicious dogs as they prowl around this city.<verse eid="PSA 59:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 59:15"/>They roam around, searching for food and if they do not find enough, they growl like dogs.<verse eid="PSA 59:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 59:16"/>But as for me, I will sing about your power; every morning I will sing joyfully about your faithfully loving us. I will sing about how you protected me when I was very distressed.<verse eid="PSA 59:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 59:17"/>God, you are the one who enables me to be strong; you are my refuge; you faithfully love me, just as you have promised in your covenant.<verse eid="PSA 59:17"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 59"/>
<chapter number="60" style="c" sid="PSA 60"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 60:1"/>A psalm written by David for the choir director, a psalm for teaching, to be sung using the tune “Lily of the promise.” David wrote it during the wars in northern Syria, and when Joab’s army, after returning from the battle, killed twelve thousand of the Edom people group in Salt Valley. I prayed, “God, you have rejected us Israelites! Because you have been angry with us, you have enabled our enemies to break through our ranks. Please enable us to be strong again!<verse eid="PSA 60:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 60:2"/>It was as though you made a big earthquake in which the ground split open. So now, make us strong again, because it is as though our country is falling apart.<verse eid="PSA 60:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 60:3"/>You have caused us, your people, to suffer very much; it is as though you had taken away our strength by making us drink strong wine.<verse eid="PSA 60:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 60:4"/>But you have raised a battle flag for those who honor you. They will show your banner when they face the enemies’ arrows.<verse eid="PSA 60:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 60:5"/>Answer our prayers and enable us by your power to defeat our enemies so that we, the people you love, will be saved.”<verse eid="PSA 60:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 60:6"/>Then God answered my prayer and spoke from his temple, saying, “Because I have conquered your enemies, I will divide the city of Shechem, and I will distribute among my people the land in Succoth Valley.<verse eid="PSA 60:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 60:7"/>The region of Gilead is mine; the people of the tribe of Manasseh are mine; the tribe of Ephraim is like my helmet; and the tribe of Judah is like the scepter with which I rule.<verse eid="PSA 60:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 60:8"/>The region of Moab is like my washbasin; I throw my sandal into the region of Edom to show that it belongs to me; I shout triumphantly because I have defeated the people of all the region of Philistia.<verse eid="PSA 60:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 60:9"/>Because I want to defeat the people of Edom, who will lead my army to their capital city that has strong walls around it?”<verse eid="PSA 60:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 60:10"/>So, God, it seems that you have truly abandoned us; it seems that you do not go with us when our armies march out to fight our enemies.<verse eid="PSA 60:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 60:11"/>We need you to help us when we fight against our enemies because the help that humans can give us is worthless.<verse eid="PSA 60:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 60:12"/>But with you helping us, we will win; you will enable us to defeat our enemies.<verse eid="PSA 60:12"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 60"/>
<chapter number="61" style="c" sid="PSA 61"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 61:1"/>A psalm written by David for the choir director, to be accompanied by musical instruments. God, listen to me and answer my prayer.<verse eid="PSA 61:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 61:2"/>While I am discouraged and far from my home, I am calling out to you. Lead me to a place that will be like a high rock on top of which I will be safe.<verse eid="PSA 61:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 61:3"/>You have been my refuge; you have been like a strong tower in which my enemies cannot attack me.<verse eid="PSA 61:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 61:4"/>Allow me to live close to your sacred tent all during my life! Allow me to be safe as a little bird is safe under its mother’s wings.<verse eid="PSA 61:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 61:5"/>God, you heard me when I solemnly promised to give offerings to you; you have given to me the blessings that belong to those who have an awesome respect for you.<verse eid="PSA 61:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 61:6"/>I am the king of Israel; please allow me to live and rule for many years, and allow my descendants to rule also.<verse eid="PSA 61:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 61:7"/>Allow us to rule forever while you observe us; watch over us while you faithfully love us and do for us what you promised.<verse eid="PSA 61:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 61:8"/>If you do that, I will always sing to praise you while I offer to you each day the sacrifices that I promised to give to you.<verse eid="PSA 61:8"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 61"/>
<chapter number="62" style="c" sid="PSA 62"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 62:1"/>A psalm written by David for Jeduthun, the choir leader; God is the only one who can give me peace in my inner being, and he is the one who saves me from my enemies.<verse eid="PSA 62:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 62:2"/>Only he is like a huge rock on which I can be safe; he is like a fortress high up that my enemies cannot climb.<verse eid="PSA 62:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 62:3"/>When will you, my enemies, stop attacking me? I feel that I am as weak against you as a leaning wall or a broken-down fence.<verse eid="PSA 62:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 62:4"/>My enemies plan to remove me from my important position so that people no longer honor me. They delight in telling lies. They bless people by what they say, but in their inner beings they curse those people.<verse eid="PSA 62:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 62:5"/>God is the only one who gives me peace in my inner being; he is the one whom I confidently expect to help me.<verse eid="PSA 62:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 62:6"/>Only he is like a huge rock on which I can be safe; he is like a shelter; my enemies can never reach me there.<verse eid="PSA 62:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 62:7"/>God is the one who saves me and honors me. He is like a huge, strong rock on which I can find shelter.<verse eid="PSA 62:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 62:8"/>You my people, always trust in him. Tell him all your troubles because we go to him for safety.<verse eid="PSA 62:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 62:9"/>People who are considered to be unimportant are as unreliable as a breath of air; people who are considered to be important also really amount to nothing. If you put them all on a scale, it would be as if they weighed less than a puff of air.<verse eid="PSA 62:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 62:10"/>Do not trust in money gained by extorting it from others; do not try to gain anything by robbing others. If you become very wealthy, do not trust in your money.<verse eid="PSA 62:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 62:11"/>I have heard God say more than once that he is the one who really has power,<verse eid="PSA 62:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 62:12"/>and that he is the one who faithfully loves us, as he promised. He rewards every one of us according to the deeds that we do.<verse eid="PSA 62:12"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 62"/>
<chapter number="63" style="c" sid="PSA 63"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 63:1"/>A psalm written by David when he was in the wilderness in Judah. God, you are the God whom I worship. I greatly desire to be with you as a person in a dry hot wilderness greatly desires some water.<verse eid="PSA 63:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 63:2"/>I have been with you in your temple In order to see that you are loving and powerful.<verse eid="PSA 63:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 63:3"/>You always love me, as you promised in your covenant; this is worth more than my entire life, so I will always praise you.<verse eid="PSA 63:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 63:4"/>I will praise you all the time that I live; I will lift up my hands to you while I pray.<verse eid="PSA 63:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 63:5"/>You fill me up and you meet every need I have. My response to you is much like when I eat a delicious banquet of rich foods and the food fills me. I will have great happiness when I praise you with the words that I speak about you.<verse eid="PSA 63:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 63:6"/>While I lie on my bed, I think about you. I think about you all during the night.<verse eid="PSA 63:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 63:7"/>For you have always helped me, and I sing joyfully knowing that you protect me as a bird protects her young under her wings.<verse eid="PSA 63:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 63:8"/>I follow you closely, and your hand protects me.<verse eid="PSA 63:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 63:9"/>But those who are trying to kill me will die and descend into the place of the dead;<verse eid="PSA 63:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 63:10"/>they will be killed in battles and their corpses will be eaten by dogs.<verse eid="PSA 63:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 63:11"/>But I, the king of Israel, will rejoice in what God has done; and all those who ask God to confirm their word will praise him, but he will not allow liars to say anything.<verse eid="PSA 63:11"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 63"/>
<chapter number="64" style="c" sid="PSA 64"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 64:1"/>A psalm written by David for the choir director. God, listen to me as I tell you the things about which I am worried. I am afraid of my enemies; please save me from them.<verse eid="PSA 64:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 64:2"/>Protect me from what wicked men are planning to do to me; protect me from that group of men who do what is evil.<verse eid="PSA 64:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 64:3"/>The hostile things they say are like sharp swords; their cruel words are like arrows.<verse eid="PSA 64:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 64:4"/>They are not afraid of anyone; they lie about people and slander those who have done no wrong. They are like someone who suddenly jumps up from where he is hiding and shoots arrows at his enemies.<verse eid="PSA 64:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 64:5"/>They encourage each other about doing the evil things that they are planning to do; they talk with each other about where they can set traps to catch people. They say, “No one will see what we are doing<verse eid="PSA 64:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 64:6"/>because we have planned very well the things that we are going to do.” What people can think and plan in their inner beings is truly amazing!<verse eid="PSA 64:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 64:7"/>But it will be as though God will shoot his arrows at them, and suddenly they will be wounded.<verse eid="PSA 64:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 64:8"/>Because what they say proves they are guilty, God will get rid of them. Everyone who sees what has happened to them will shake their heads to mock them.<verse eid="PSA 64:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 64:9"/>Then everyone will be afraid to sin because of what might happen to them also; they will tell others what God has done, and they themselves will think much about it.<verse eid="PSA 64:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 64:10"/>Righteous people should rejoice because of what Yahweh has done; they should go to him to find refuge; and all those who honor him will praise him.<verse eid="PSA 64:10"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 64"/>
<chapter number="65" style="c" sid="PSA 65"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 65:1"/>A psalm written by David for the choir director. God, it is right for us to praise you in Jerusalem and to do what we have promised you that we would do<verse eid="PSA 65:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 65:2"/>because you answer our prayers. People everywhere will come to you<verse eid="PSA 65:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 65:3"/>Our many sins are like a very heavy burden to us, but you forgive us.<verse eid="PSA 65:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 65:4"/>How fortunate are those whom you have chosen to always be in your temple courtyards. We will be satisfied with all the blessings that you will give us because we worship you in your sacred temple.<verse eid="PSA 65:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 65:5"/>God, when we pray to you, you answer us and save us by doing awesome deeds; you are the one who rescues us; people who live in very remote places on the earth, on the other side of the oceans, trust in you.<verse eid="PSA 65:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 65:6"/>You are the one who put the mountains in their places, showing that you are very powerful.<verse eid="PSA 65:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 65:7"/>You are the one who calms the seas when they roar, and stop the waves from pounding on the shore; you also calm people when they cause a lot of trouble.<verse eid="PSA 65:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 65:8"/>People who live in very remote places on the earth are awed by the miracles that you perform; because of what you do, people who live far to the west and far to the east shout joyfully.<verse eid="PSA 65:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 65:9"/>You take care of the soil and send rain, causing many good things to grow; you fill the streams with water and cause grain to grow. This is what you have determined would happen.<verse eid="PSA 65:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 65:10"/>You send plenty of rain on the fields that have been plowed, and you fill the furrows with water. With showers you soften the hard clods of soil, and you bless the soil by causing young plants to grow.<verse eid="PSA 65:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 65:11"/>Because you bless the soil, there are very good crops at harvest season; wherever you have gone, good crops are very abundant.<verse eid="PSA 65:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 65:12"/>The pastures in the wilderness are wet with the morning dew, it is as though the hills are singing joyful songs.<verse eid="PSA 65:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 65:13"/>The meadows are covered with sheep and goats, and the valleys are full of grain; it is as though they also sing and shout joyfully.<verse eid="PSA 65:13"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 65"/>
<chapter number="66" style="c" sid="PSA 66"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 66:1"/>A psalm that is a song for the choir director. Tell everyone on the earth that they should sing joyfully to praise God!<verse eid="PSA 66:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 66:2"/>They should sing songs that say that God is very great, and they should tell everyone that he is very glorious!<verse eid="PSA 66:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 66:3"/>They should say to God, “The things that you do are awesome! Your power is very great, with the result that your enemies cringe in front of you.”<verse eid="PSA 66:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 66:4"/>Everyone on the earth will worship God, sing to praise him, and honor him.<verse eid="PSA 66:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 66:5"/>Come and think about what God has done! Think about the awesome things that he has done among people.<verse eid="PSA 66:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 66:6"/>He caused the sea to become dry land, with the result that our ancestors were able to walk right through it. There we rejoiced because of what he had done.<verse eid="PSA 66:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 66:7"/>He rules forever by his power, and he keeps watching all the nations to see what evil things they do. The nations that want to rebel against him should not be proud.<verse eid="PSA 66:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 66:8"/>You people of all nations, praise our God! Praise him loudly in order that people will hear you as you praise him.<verse eid="PSA 66:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 66:9"/>He has kept us alive, and he has not allowed us to fall into disaster.<verse eid="PSA 66:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 66:10"/>God, you have tested us; you have allowed us to experience great difficulties to make our lives become pure as people put precious metals in a hot fire to burn out what is impure.<verse eid="PSA 66:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 66:11"/>It is as if you allowed us to fall into traps, and you forced us to endure difficult things that were like heavy loads to carry on our backs.<verse eid="PSA 66:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 66:12"/>You allowed our enemies to trample on us; we experienced difficulties walking through fires and floods, but now you have made us safe.<verse eid="PSA 66:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 66:13"/>I will bring to your temple offerings that are to be completely burned on the altar; I will offer to you what I promised.<verse eid="PSA 66:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 66:14"/>When I was experiencing much trouble, I said that I would bring offerings to you if you rescued me; and you did rescue me, so I will bring to you what I promised.<verse eid="PSA 66:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 66:15"/>I will bring sheep to be burned on the altar, and I will also sacrifice bulls and goats; when they are burning, you will be pleased as the smoke rises up to you.<verse eid="PSA 66:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 66:16"/>All you people who have a reverential respect for God, come and listen, and I will tell you what he has done for me.<verse eid="PSA 66:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 66:17"/>I called out to him to help me, and I praised him while I was speaking to him.<verse eid="PSA 66:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 66:18"/>If I had ignored the sins that I had committed, the Lord would not have paid any attention to me.<verse eid="PSA 66:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 66:19"/>But because I confessed my sins, God has listened to me and has paid attention to my prayers.<verse eid="PSA 66:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 66:20"/>I praise God because he has not ignored my prayers; he continues to love me as he promised in his covenant to do.<verse eid="PSA 66:20"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 66"/>
<chapter number="67" style="c" sid="PSA 67"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 67:1"/>A psalm for the choir director, to be accompanied by stringed instruments. God, act mercifully toward us and bless us; act kindly toward us.<verse eid="PSA 67:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 67:2"/>Do this in order that everyone in the world may know what you want them to do, and the people of all nations may know that you have the power to save them.<verse eid="PSA 67:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 67:3"/>God, I desire that all people groups may praise you; I want them all to praise you!<verse eid="PSA 67:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 67:4"/>I desire that the people of all nations will be glad and sing joyfully because you judge the people groups equally, and you guide all the nations in the world.<verse eid="PSA 67:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 67:5"/>God, I desire that the people groups may praise you; I want them all to praise you!<verse eid="PSA 67:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 67:6"/>Good crops have grown on our land; God, our God, has blessed us.<verse eid="PSA 67:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 67:7"/>Because God has blessed us, I desire that all people everywhere on the earth may have an awesome respect for him.<verse eid="PSA 67:7"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 67"/>
<chapter number="68" style="c" sid="PSA 68"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 68:1"/>A psalm written by David for the choir director. God, arise and scatter your enemies, and cause those who hate you to run away from you.<verse eid="PSA 68:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 68:2"/>As wind blows smoke away, you chase your enemies away. As wax melts when it is near a fire, may you cause wicked people to disappear.<verse eid="PSA 68:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 68:3"/>But may the righteous people be joyful; may they rejoice when they are in God’s presence; may they be happy and very joyful.<verse eid="PSA 68:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 68:4"/>Sing to God; sing to praise him; sing a song for him who rides in the desert plains; his name is Yahweh; be glad when you are in his presence.<verse eid="PSA 68:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 68:5"/>God, who lives in his sacred temple, is like a father to those who are orphans, and he is the one who protects widows.<verse eid="PSA 68:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 68:6"/>He provides families for those who have no one to live with. He frees prisoners and enables them to be successful, but those who rebel against him will be forced to live in a very hot and dry land.<verse eid="PSA 68:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 68:7"/>God, you led your people out of Egypt, and then you marched with them through the desert.<verse eid="PSA 68:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 68:8"/>After you did that, the earth shook at Mount Sinai when you appeared to your people, and rain poured down from the sky, and your people worshiped you.<verse eid="PSA 68:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 68:9"/>You caused plenty of rain to fall there in the wilderness, and so you enabled good crops to grow again on that land that you gave to us Israelites.<verse eid="PSA 68:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 68:10"/>Your people built homes there; because you were good to them, you provided food for those who were poor.<verse eid="PSA 68:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 68:11"/>The Lord spoke this message, and many people took his message to other places.<verse eid="PSA 68:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 68:12"/>(12-13) They proclaimed, “Many kings and their armies are running away from our army!” When our army brought back to their homes the things that they captured, the women who were at home divided up those things among themselves and among their families. They got statues of pigeons whose wings were covered with silver and whose feathers were covered with pure yellow gold. But some of the people stayed with the sheep and did not go to fight in the battle. Why did you not go?<verse eid="PSA 68:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 68:14"/>When Almighty God scattered the enemy kings and their armies, it reminded me of a snowstorm on Mount Zalmon!<verse eid="PSA 68:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 68:15"/>There is a very high mountain in the Bashan hills, a mountain that has many peaks.<verse eid="PSA 68:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 68:16"/>But the people who live near that mountain should not envy those who live near Mount Zion, the mountain on which God chose to live! Yahweh will live there forever!<verse eid="PSA 68:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 68:17"/>After we defeated all our enemies, it was as though the Lord, surrounded by many thousands of strong chariots, descended from Mount Sinai and came into the sacred temple in Jerusalem.<verse eid="PSA 68:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 68:18"/>He ascended the sacred mountain where his temple is and took with him many people who had been captured in battles; he received gifts from the enemies whom he had defeated. He received gifts even from those who had rebelled against him, and Yahweh, our God, will live there in his sacred temple forever.<verse eid="PSA 68:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 68:19"/>Praise the Lord, who helps us carry our heavy loads every day; he is the one who saves us.<verse eid="PSA 68:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 68:20"/>Our God is the God who saves us; He is Yahweh, our Lord, the one who allows us to escape from dying in battles.<verse eid="PSA 68:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 68:21"/>But God will smash the heads of his enemies, the long-haired skulls of those who continue to behave sinfully.<verse eid="PSA 68:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 68:22"/>The Lord said, “I will bring back the corpses of my enemies who were killed in Bashan, and I will bring back those who sank deep in the ocean and drowned.<verse eid="PSA 68:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 68:23"/>I will do that so that you may wash your feet in their blood, and your dogs can also lap up some of your enemies’ blood.”<verse eid="PSA 68:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 68:24"/>God, many people see you march triumphantly into your sacred temple, celebrating that you have defeated your enemies. You march like a king does, and a large crowd walks with you.<verse eid="PSA 68:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 68:25"/>The singers are in front, and the people who play stringed instruments are at the rear, and young women who are beating their tambourines are between them.<verse eid="PSA 68:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 68:26"/>They are all singing, “You Israelite people, praise God when you gather together; praise Yahweh, all you who are descendants of Jacob!”<verse eid="PSA 68:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 68:27"/>First come the people of the tribe of Benjamin, the smallest tribe, and following them come the leaders of the tribe of Judah and their group, and following them come the leaders of the tribes of Zebulun and Naphtali.<verse eid="PSA 68:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 68:28"/>You people of Israel, God made our tribes very strong. God, help us with your power as you helped us in the past.<verse eid="PSA 68:28"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="29" style="v" sid="PSA 68:29"/>Show us that you are strong, there where you are in your temple in Jerusalem; kings bring gifts to you there.<verse eid="PSA 68:29"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="30" style="v" sid="PSA 68:30"/>Shout as you defeat your enemies, such as those in Egypt, who are like wild animals living in the reeds. Shout as you defeat the powerful nations, who are like herds of bulls. Shame them; make them bow down and give you gifts. Drive away and scatter the people groups who love to attack other nations.<verse eid="PSA 68:30"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="31" style="v" sid="PSA 68:31"/>Then the leaders of Egypt will bring gifts to you. then the people in Ethiopia will rush to lift up their hands to praise you.<verse eid="PSA 68:31"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="32" style="v" sid="PSA 68:32"/>You people who are citizens of kingdoms all over the world, sing to God! Sing praises to Yahweh!<verse eid="PSA 68:32"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="33" style="v" sid="PSA 68:33"/>Sing to the God, the one who rides in the sky, the sky that he created long ago. Listen as he shouts with a very powerful voice.<verse eid="PSA 68:33"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="34" style="v" sid="PSA 68:34"/>Proclaim that God is very powerful; he is the king that rules over Israel, and in the skies he also shows that he is powerful.<verse eid="PSA 68:34"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="35" style="v" sid="PSA 68:35"/>God is awesome as he comes out of his sacred temple; he is the God whom we Israelite people worship. He gives power and strength to his people. Praise God!<verse eid="PSA 68:35"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 68"/>
<chapter number="69" style="c" sid="PSA 69"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 69:1"/>A psalm written by David for the choir director. O God, save me because I am in great danger. It is as though the flood water were up to my neck, and I were about to drown.<verse eid="PSA 69:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 69:2"/>I continue to sink in the deep mud, and there is no solid ground for me to stand on. I am in deep water, and the flood is swirling around me.<verse eid="PSA 69:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 69:3"/>I am exhausted from calling out for help; my throat is very dry. Because I have cried so much as I have waited for God to help me, my eyes are swollen from tears.<verse eid="PSA 69:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 69:4"/>Those who hate me when there is no reason to hate me are more than the number of hairs on my head! Those who want to get rid of me are strong, and they tell lies about me. They demand that I return to them things that I did not steal!<verse eid="PSA 69:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 69:5"/>O God, you see the sins that I have committed. You know that I have foolishly disobeyed your laws.<verse eid="PSA 69:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 69:6"/>O Yahweh God, commander of the angel armies, do not allow the wrong things that I have done cause those who trust in you to be disappointed. O God, whom we Israelite people worship, do not allow me to cause them to be shamed.<verse eid="PSA 69:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 69:7"/>People have insulted me because I am devoted to you. They have thoroughly humiliated me.<verse eid="PSA 69:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 69:8"/>Even my own older brothers act as if they do not know me; they treat me like a foreigner.<verse eid="PSA 69:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 69:9"/>Some people have despised your temple; but because I have tried to keep your temple holy, people have caused trouble for me. So it is as though those who are insulting you are also insulting me.<verse eid="PSA 69:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 69:10"/>When I have humbled myself and fasted to show my sadness about the disgraceful things that they have done to your temple, they just insult me.<verse eid="PSA 69:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 69:11"/>When I put on rough sackcloth to show that I am sad, they laugh at me.<verse eid="PSA 69:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 69:12"/>Even the elders of the city say bad things about me. The drunkards of the city sing disgusting songs about me.<verse eid="PSA 69:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 69:13"/>But Yahweh, I will continue praying to you. At the time that you choose, answer me and rescue me because you faithfully love me, as you have promised to do.<verse eid="PSA 69:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 69:14"/>Do not allow me to sink anymore in the mud. Rescue me from those who hate me! Lift me up out of these deep waters!<verse eid="PSA 69:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 69:15"/>Do not allow the floods to swirl around me; do not allow the deep mud to swallow me; keep me from sinking into the pit of death.<verse eid="PSA 69:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 69:16"/>O Yahweh, answer my prayer and help me because you are good and I can depend on your love for me. You have not punished me for what I deserve. I know you will listen to me!<verse eid="PSA 69:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 69:17"/>Do not hide yourself from me; answer me quickly because I am in great trouble.<verse eid="PSA 69:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 69:18"/>Come near to me and save me; rescue me from my enemies.<verse eid="PSA 69:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 69:19"/>You know that I am insulted and that people shame and dishonor me; you know who all my enemies are.<verse eid="PSA 69:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 69:20"/>Their insults have deeply offended me, and I feel helpless. I searched for someone who would pity me, but there was no one. I wanted someone to encourage me, but there was no one.<verse eid="PSA 69:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 69:21"/>Instead, they gave me food that tasted like poison, and when I was thirsty, they gave me sour wine to drink.<verse eid="PSA 69:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 69:22"/>I hope their own food will kill them; I hope that this will happen when they think that they are completely safe.<verse eid="PSA 69:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 69:23"/>I hope that their eyes become dim so that they cannot see anything and that their backs will become weaker and weaker.<verse eid="PSA 69:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 69:24"/>Show them that you are very angry with them! Because of your great anger, chase them and catch them.<verse eid="PSA 69:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 69:25"/>Cause their towns to become abandoned; may there be no one to live in their tents.<verse eid="PSA 69:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 69:26"/>Do this because they persecute those whom you have punished, they look at how those whom you have punished suffer, and they tell others about it.<verse eid="PSA 69:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 69:27"/>Keep making a record of all their sins, do not fail to punish them for the evil things that they have done.<verse eid="PSA 69:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 69:28"/>Erase their names from the book containing the names of those who have eternal life; do not include them in the list of righteous people.<verse eid="PSA 69:28"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="29" style="v" sid="PSA 69:29"/>As for me, I have pain and am suffering. O God, protect me and rescue me.<verse eid="PSA 69:29"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="30" style="v" sid="PSA 69:30"/>When God does that, I will sing as I praise God, and I will honor him by thanking him.<verse eid="PSA 69:30"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="31" style="v" sid="PSA 69:31"/>My doing that will please Yahweh more than sacrificing oxen, more than offering him full grown bulls.<verse eid="PSA 69:31"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="32" style="v" sid="PSA 69:32"/>Oppressed people will see that God has rescued me, and they will be glad. I desire that all who request God to help them may be encouraged.<verse eid="PSA 69:32"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="33" style="v" sid="PSA 69:33"/>Yahweh listens to those who are needy; he does not ignore those who have suffered for him.<verse eid="PSA 69:33"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="34" style="v" sid="PSA 69:34"/>I desire that everything will praise God— everything that is in heaven and on earth and all the creatures that are in the seas.<verse eid="PSA 69:34"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="35" style="v" sid="PSA 69:35"/>God will rescue the people of Jerusalem from their enemies, and he will rebuild the towns that are in Judah. His people will live there and again possess the land.<verse eid="PSA 69:35"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="36" style="v" sid="PSA 69:36"/>The descendants of his people will inherit it, and those who love him will live there safely.<verse eid="PSA 69:36"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 69"/>
<chapter number="70" style="c" sid="PSA 70"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 70:1"/>A psalm written by David for the choir director, asking God to help David. God, please save me! Yahweh, come quickly to help me!<verse eid="PSA 70:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 70:2"/>Disgrace those who are happy about my troubles, those who are trying to kill me. Chase them away; make everyone shame them, for they want to see me suffer.<verse eid="PSA 70:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 70:3"/>I hope that you will cause them to become dismayed and ashamed because they have been happy about my troubles.<verse eid="PSA 70:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 70:4"/>But I hope that everyone who prays to you will rejoice because of you. I hope that everyone who waits for you to rescue them will say, “God is great!”<verse eid="PSA 70:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 70:5"/>As for me, I am poor and needy; so God, come quickly to help me! Yahweh, you are the one who saves and helps me, so please come quickly!<verse eid="PSA 70:5"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 70"/>
<chapter number="71" style="c" sid="PSA 71"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 71:1"/>Yahweh, I have come to you to be safe; never allow me to become ashamed.<verse eid="PSA 71:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 71:2"/>Because you always do what is right, help me and rescue me; listen to me, and save me!<verse eid="PSA 71:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 71:3"/>Be like a huge rock on top of which I can be safe; be like a strong fortress in which I am safe. You have commanded your angels to rescue me.<verse eid="PSA 71:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 71:4"/>God, rescue me from wicked people, from the power of unjust and evil men.<verse eid="PSA 71:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 71:5"/>Yahweh, my Lord, you are the one whom I confidently expect to help me; I have trusted in you ever since I was young.<verse eid="PSA 71:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 71:6"/>I have depended on you all my life; you have taken care of me since the day that I was born, so I will always praise you.<verse eid="PSA 71:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 71:7"/>The manner in which you have rescued me has been an example to many people because they realize that you have been my strong defender.<verse eid="PSA 71:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 71:8"/>I praise you all during the day, and I proclaim that you are glorious.<verse eid="PSA 71:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 71:9"/>Now when I have become an old man, do not reject me; do not abandon me now when I am not strong anymore.<verse eid="PSA 71:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 71:10"/>My enemies say that they want to kill me; they talk together and plan how they can do that.<verse eid="PSA 71:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 71:11"/>They say, “God has abandoned him; so now we can pursue him and seize him because there is no one who will rescue him.”<verse eid="PSA 71:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 71:12"/>God, do not stay far away from me; hurry to help me!<verse eid="PSA 71:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 71:13"/>Cause those who accuse me to be defeated and destroyed; cause those who want to harm me to be shamed and disgraced.<verse eid="PSA 71:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 71:14"/>But as for me, I will continually and confidently expect you to do great things for me, and I will praise you more and more.<verse eid="PSA 71:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 71:15"/>I will tell people that you do what is right; all during the day I will tell people how you have saved me, although what you have done is more than I can fully understand.<verse eid="PSA 71:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 71:16"/>Yahweh, my Lord, I will praise you for your mighty deeds; I will proclaim that only you always act justly.<verse eid="PSA 71:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 71:17"/>God, you have taught me many things ever since I was young, and I still tell people about your wonderful deeds.<verse eid="PSA 71:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 71:18"/>Now, God, when I am old and my hair is gray, do not abandon me. Stay with me while I continue to proclaim to my children and grandchildren.<verse eid="PSA 71:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 71:19"/>God, you do many righteous deeds; it is as though they extend up to the sky. You have done great things; there is no one like you.<verse eid="PSA 71:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 71:20"/>You have caused us to have many troubles and to suffer much, but you will cause us to become strong again; when I am almost dead, you will keep us alive.<verse eid="PSA 71:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 71:21"/>You will cause me to be greatly honored, and you will encourage me again.<verse eid="PSA 71:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 71:22"/>I will also praise you while I play my harp; I will praise you, my God, for faithfully doing what you have promised to do. I will play hymns to praise you, the holy God whom we Israelites worship.<verse eid="PSA 71:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 71:23"/>I will shout joyfully while I sing; with my entire inner being I will sing because you have rescued me.<verse eid="PSA 71:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 71:24"/>All during the day I will tell people that you act righteously because those who wanted to harm me will have been defeated and disgraced.<verse eid="PSA 71:24"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 71"/>
<chapter number="72" style="c" sid="PSA 72"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 72:1"/>A psalm written by Solomon. O God, enable the king whom you appointed in Israel to rule justly. Show him how to judge matters fairly<verse eid="PSA 72:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 72:2"/>so that he may judge your people fairly and that he may govern your oppressed people justly.<verse eid="PSA 72:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 72:3"/>I desire that all over the country—even on the hills and mountains — people will live peacefully and righteously.<verse eid="PSA 72:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 72:4"/>Help your king to defend the poor people and to rescue needy people and to defeat those who oppress them.<verse eid="PSA 72:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 72:5"/>I desire that your king may live as long as the sun shines, as long as the moon shines, forever.<verse eid="PSA 72:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 72:6"/>I desire that his rule may be enjoyed by the people as they enjoy rain on the growing crops, as they enjoy the showers that fall on the land.<verse eid="PSA 72:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 72:7"/>I hope that people may live righteously during the years that he rules and that the people may live peacefully and prosperously as long as the moon shines.<verse eid="PSA 72:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 72:8"/>I hope that the king of Israel may rule the people in all the area from one sea in the east to another in the west and from the Euphrates River to the most remote places on earth.<verse eid="PSA 72:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 72:9"/>I hope that those who live in the wilderness may bow down before him and that his enemies may throw themselves on the ground in submission to our king.<verse eid="PSA 72:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 72:10"/>I hope that the king of the land of Tarshish and the kings of the islands in the sea may pay taxes to the king of Israel. I hope that the king of Sheba to the south and the king of Seba to the southwest may bring him gifts.<verse eid="PSA 72:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 72:11"/>I hope that all the other kings in the world may bow before the king of Israel and that people of all nations may serve our king.<verse eid="PSA 72:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 72:12"/>He rescues poor people when they cry out for help, and he helps those who are needy and those who have no one to help them.<verse eid="PSA 72:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 72:13"/>He pities those who are weak and needy; he saves the people’s lives.<verse eid="PSA 72:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 72:14"/>Our king rescues people from being oppressed and from being treated cruelly because their lives are precious to our king.<verse eid="PSA 72:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 72:15"/>I hope that our king may live a long time! I hope that he may be given gold from Sheba. I desire that people may always pray for our king and praise him all the time, every day.<verse eid="PSA 72:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 72:16"/>I hope that the fields may produce plenty of grain everywhere, even on the tops of the hills in the land where he rules, like the grain that grows on the hills in Lebanon. I hope that the cities in Israel will be as full of people as the fields are full of grass.<verse eid="PSA 72:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 72:17"/>I desire that the name of the king may never be forgotten. I hope that people may remember him as long as the sun shines. I hope that all people will praise Yahweh, the God of Israel, just as he has blessed the king of Israel.<verse eid="PSA 72:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 72:18"/>Praise Yahweh, the God whom we Israelites worship; he is the only one who does wonderful things.<verse eid="PSA 72:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 72:19"/>Praise him forever! I desire that his glory may fill the whole world! Amen! May it be so!<verse eid="PSA 72:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 72:20"/>This is the end of the prayers written by David, son of Jesse.<verse eid="PSA 72:20"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 72"/>
<chapter number="73" style="c" sid="PSA 73"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 73:1"/>A psalm written by Asaph; God truly is good to us Israelite people, to those who want to do what pleases God.<verse eid="PSA 73:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 73:2"/>As for me, I almost stopped trusting in God; I was almost guilty of committing a great sin against him,<verse eid="PSA 73:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 73:3"/>because I envied those who proudly acted as if they did not need God, when I realized that they prospered even though they were wicked.<verse eid="PSA 73:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 73:4"/>Those people do not suffer; they always have plenty of food to eat.<verse eid="PSA 73:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 73:5"/>They do not experience the difficult things that other people do; they do not experience catastrophes and sicknesses like other people.<verse eid="PSA 73:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 73:6"/>So they are proud and violent. Their being prideful is like a necklace that they show off to others, and they openly display their violent actions like people openly display the clothes they wear.<verse eid="PSA 73:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 73:7"/>Their eyes protrude because their faces are fat, and they are always thinking about more evil things to do.<verse eid="PSA 73:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 73:8"/>They scoff at other people, and wickedly talk about doing unjust things to them; they speak pridefully.<verse eid="PSA 73:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 73:9"/>They exalt themselves and talk as if they are God in heaven, and they go about the earth talking boastfully.<verse eid="PSA 73:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 73:10"/>The result is that people pay attention to them and listen to everything they say.<verse eid="PSA 73:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 73:11"/>Wicked people say to themselves, “God certainly does not care what we do; the Most High certainly will not judge us for what we do!”<verse eid="PSA 73:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 73:12"/>Look at how these wicked people live; their lives are so easy that they never have to worry about anything, and they are always becoming richer.<verse eid="PSA 73:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 73:13"/>{When I saw this I thought that} certainly it is useless that I have thought about things that are pleasing to you, and have not sinned.<verse eid="PSA 73:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 73:14"/>Every day I suffer, and every morning you punish me.<verse eid="PSA 73:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 73:15"/>If I had said these things out loud in front of others, Surely, I would have been sinning against your people.<verse eid="PSA 73:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 73:16"/>When I tried to think about all this, it was very difficult for me to understand it.<verse eid="PSA 73:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 73:17"/>But when I went to the temple where people worship God, then I understood what will happen to wicked people in the future.<verse eid="PSA 73:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 73:18"/>I know that you make their future insecure, you will cause them to be ruined.<verse eid="PSA 73:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 73:19"/>God will suddenly destroy these wicked people; they will die in terrible ways.<verse eid="PSA 73:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 73:20"/>Lord, when you act, you will cause the wicked to quickly vanish; they will vanish like a dream which disappears as soon as a person awakes from their sleep.<verse eid="PSA 73:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 73:21"/>When I was grieved in my inner being, and felt emotionally hurt,<verse eid="PSA 73:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 73:22"/>I was stupid and ignorant; I behaved like an animal toward you.<verse eid="PSA 73:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 73:23"/>Nevertheless I am always with you; you constantly stay close to me.<verse eid="PSA 73:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 73:24"/>You lead me by instructing me, and when I die, you will take me into your glorious presence.<verse eid="PSA 73:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 73:25"/>You are the only one I have in heaven! There is nothing on this earth that I desire more than you.<verse eid="PSA 73:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 73:26"/>My body and my spirit may become very weak, but God enables me to feel encouraged; He is all I need.<verse eid="PSA 73:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 73:27"/>People who abandon you will perish; you will ruin every person who is not loyal to you.<verse eid="PSA 73:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 73:28"/>But for me, the only thing I need is to be close to God. I trust in the Lord Yahweh to keep me safe, so that I may tell others everything you have done for me.<verse eid="PSA 73:28"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 73"/>
<chapter number="74" style="c" sid="PSA 74"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 74:1"/>A psalm written by Asaph; God, it feels like you have abandoned us permanently! I do not understand why you are so angry with us, since we are like sheep in your pasture {and you are like our shepherd}!<verse eid="PSA 74:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 74:2"/>Do not forget your people whom you chose long ago, the people whom you freed {from being slaves in Egypt} and caused to become your tribe. {Do not forget} Jerusalem, which was where you dwelt {on earth}.<verse eid="PSA 74:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 74:3"/>Hurry, come and see everything that has been ruined for so long; our enemies have destroyed everything in the Temple.<verse eid="PSA 74:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 74:4"/>Your enemies have shouted triumphantly in your sacred place; they erected their banners to show they had defeated us.<verse eid="PSA 74:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 74:5"/>They chopped down all the woodwork in the Temple, like woodsmen cut down trees in a forest with their axes.<verse eid="PSA 74:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 74:6"/>They tore down all the carved wood with their axes and hammers.<verse eid="PSA 74:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 74:7"/>Then they burned your temple to the ground; they defiled the place where you dwelled on earth.<verse eid="PSA 74:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 74:8"/>They said to themselves, “We will subdue the Israelites completely.” They have burned down all the other places throughout the land of Israel where people gathered to worship you.<verse eid="PSA 74:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 74:9"/>We no longer see any signs from God’s prophets; there are no prophets any more, and no one among us knows how long this situation will continue.<verse eid="PSA 74:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 74:10"/>God, how long will our enemies make fun of you? Will they insult you forever?<verse eid="PSA 74:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 74:11"/>Why, even though you are powerful, do you refuse to help us? Please stop refusing to help us and come and rescue us by destroying our enemies.<verse eid="PSA 74:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 74:12"/>But still God, you are our king since long ago; and you have rescued us from our enemies here on earth.<verse eid="PSA 74:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 74:13"/>By your power you caused the sea to divide; it was as though you had smashed the heads of the rulers of Egypt who were like huge sea dragons.<verse eid="PSA 74:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 74:14"/>It was as though you crushed the head of the king of Egypt and gave his body to the animals in the desert to eat.<verse eid="PSA 74:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 74:15"/>You caused springs and streams to flow, and you also dried up rivers that had never dried up previously.<verse eid="PSA 74:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 74:16"/>You created the days and the nights, and you put the sun and the moon in their places.<verse eid="PSA 74:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 74:17"/>You determined where the oceans end and the land begins, and you created the summer season and the winter season.<verse eid="PSA 74:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 74:18"/>Yahweh, do not forget that your enemies laugh at you and that it is foolish people who despise you.<verse eid="PSA 74:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 74:19"/>Do not abandon your helpless people into the hands of their cruel enemies; do not forget your suffering people.<verse eid="PSA 74:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 74:20"/>Continue thinking about the covenant that you made with us; remember that there are violent people in every dark place on the earth.<verse eid="PSA 74:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 74:21"/>Do not allow your oppressed people to be disgraced; help those poor and needy people in order that they will again praise you.<verse eid="PSA 74:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 74:22"/>God, arise and defend yourself by defending your people! Do not forget that foolish people laugh at you all during the day!<verse eid="PSA 74:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 74:23"/>Do not forget that your enemies shout angrily at you; the uproar that they make while they oppose you never stops.<verse eid="PSA 74:23"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 74"/>
<chapter number="75" style="c" sid="PSA 75"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 75:1"/>A psalm written by Asaph for the choir director, to be sung using the tune ‘Do not destroy’ We give thanks to you; our God, we thank you. You are close to us, and we proclaim to others the wonderful things that you have done for us.<verse eid="PSA 75:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 75:2"/>You have said, “I have appointed a time when I will judge people, and I will judge everyone fairly.<verse eid="PSA 75:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 75:3"/>When the earth shakes and all the creatures on the earth tremble, I am the one who will keep its foundations steady.<verse eid="PSA 75:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 75:4"/>I say to people who boast, ‘Stop bragging!’ and I say to wicked people, ‘Do not proudly do things to show how great you are!’”<verse eid="PSA 75:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 75:5"/>Do not be arrogant, and do not speak so boastfully!<verse eid="PSA 75:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 75:6"/>The one who judges people does not come from the east or from the west, and he does not come from the desert.<verse eid="PSA 75:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 75:7"/>God is the one who judges people; he shames and punishes some, and he honors others.<verse eid="PSA 75:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 75:8"/>It is as though Yahweh held a cup in his hand; it is filled with wine that has spices mixed in it to cause those who drink it to become more drunk; and when Yahweh pours it out, he will force all the wicked people to drink it; they will drink every drop of it; yes, he will punish them fully.<verse eid="PSA 75:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 75:9"/>But as for me, I will never stop saying what the God whom Jacob worshiped has done; I will never stop singing to praise him.<verse eid="PSA 75:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 75:10"/>He promises this: “I will destroy the power of wicked people, but I will increase the power of righteous people.”<verse eid="PSA 75:10"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 75"/>
<chapter number="76" style="c" sid="PSA 76"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 76:1"/>A psalm written by Asaph for the choir director, to be accompanied by stringed instruments; God has made the people in Judah to know him; the Israelite people honor him.<verse eid="PSA 76:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 76:2"/>In Jerusalem is where he resides; he lives on Mount Zion.<verse eid="PSA 76:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 76:3"/>There he broke the flaming arrows that his enemies shot, and he also broke their shields and swords and other weapons that they used in battles.<verse eid="PSA 76:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 76:4"/>God, you are powerful! You are like a great king as you return from the mountains where you defeated your enemies.<verse eid="PSA 76:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 76:5"/>Their brave soldiers were killed, and then those who killed them took away everything that those soldiers had. Those enemies died; indeed, none of them were able to fight any longer.<verse eid="PSA 76:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 76:6"/>When you, the God whom Jacob worshiped, rebuked your enemies, their horses and their riders fell down dead.<verse eid="PSA 76:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 76:7"/>Truly, you cause everyone to be afraid. When you are angry and you punish people, no one can endure it.<verse eid="PSA 76:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 76:8"/>From heaven you proclaimed that you would judge people, and then everyone on the earth was afraid and did not say anything more<verse eid="PSA 76:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 76:9"/>when you arose to declare that you would punish wicked people and rescue all those whom they had oppressed.<verse eid="PSA 76:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 76:10"/>When you punish those with whom you are angry, your people will praise you, and your enemies who survive will worship you on your festival days.<verse eid="PSA 76:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 76:11"/>So give to Yahweh the offerings that you promised to give to him; all the people of nearby people groups should also bring gifts to him, the one who is awesome.<verse eid="PSA 76:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 76:12"/>He humbles the leaders, and terrifies all the kings.<verse eid="PSA 76:12"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 76"/>
<chapter number="77" style="c" sid="PSA 77"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 77:1"/>A psalm written by Asaph for Jeduthun, the choir director; I will cry out to God; I will cry aloud to him, and he will listen to me.<verse eid="PSA 77:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 77:2"/>At the time that I had trouble, I prayed to the Lord; all during the night I lifted up my hands while I prayed, but nothing could comfort me.<verse eid="PSA 77:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 77:3"/>When I thought about God, I despaired; when I meditated about him, I grew discouraged.<verse eid="PSA 77:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 77:4"/>All during the night he prevented me from sleeping; I was so worried that I did not know what to say.<verse eid="PSA 77:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 77:5"/>I thought about days that had passed; I remembered what had happened in previous years.<verse eid="PSA 77:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 77:6"/>I spent all the night thinking about things; I meditated, and this is what I asked myself:<verse eid="PSA 77:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 77:7"/>“Will the Lord always reject me? Will he never again be pleased with me?<verse eid="PSA 77:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 77:8"/>Has he stopped faithfully loving me? Will he not do for me what he promised to do?<verse eid="PSA 77:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 77:9"/>God promised to act mercifully toward me; has he forgotten that? Because he is angry with me, has he decided not to be kind to me?”<verse eid="PSA 77:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 77:10"/>I said, “What causes me to be sad the most is that it seems that God, who is greater than any other god, is no longer using his power for us.”<verse eid="PSA 77:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 77:11"/>But then, Yahweh, I recall your great deeds; I remember the wonderful things that you did in the past.<verse eid="PSA 77:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 77:12"/>I meditate on all that you have done, and I think about your mighty acts.<verse eid="PSA 77:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 77:13"/>God, everything that you do is amazing; there is certainly no god who is great like you are!<verse eid="PSA 77:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 77:14"/>You are God, the one who performs miracles; you showed to the people of many people groups that you are powerful.<verse eid="PSA 77:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 77:15"/>By your power you rescued your people from Egypt; you saved those who were descendants of Jacob and his son Joseph.<verse eid="PSA 77:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 77:16"/>It was as though the waters saw you and became very afraid, and even the deepest part of the water shook.<verse eid="PSA 77:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 77:17"/>Rain poured down from the clouds; it thundered very loudly, and lightning flashed in all directions.<verse eid="PSA 77:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 77:18"/>Thunder crashed in the whirlwind—your voice! Lightning lit up, and the earth shook violently.<verse eid="PSA 77:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 77:19"/>Then you walked through the sea in a path that you made through the deep water, but your footprints could not be seen.<verse eid="PSA 77:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 77:20"/>You led your people as a shepherd leads his flock of sheep while Moses and Aaron were the leaders of your people.<verse eid="PSA 77:20"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 77"/>
<chapter number="78" style="c" sid="PSA 78"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 78:1"/>A psalm written by Asaph; My friends, listen to what I am going to teach you; pay careful attention to what I will say.<verse eid="PSA 78:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 78:2"/>I am going to give you some sayings that wise people have said. They will be sayings about things that happened long ago, things that were difficult to understand.<verse eid="PSA 78:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 78:3"/>These are things that we have heard and known previously, things that our parents and grandparents told us.<verse eid="PSA 78:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 78:4"/>We will tell these things to our children, but we will also tell our grandchildren about Yahweh’s power and the glorious things that he has done.<verse eid="PSA 78:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 78:5"/>He gave laws and commandments to the Israelite people, those who are the descendants of Jacob, and he told our ancestors to teach them to their children.<verse eid="PSA 78:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 78:6"/>He commanded this so that their children would also know them and so that they would teach them to their own children.<verse eid="PSA 78:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 78:7"/>In that way, they also would trust in God and would not forget the things that he has done; instead, they would obey his commandments.<verse eid="PSA 78:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 78:8"/>They would not be like their ancestors, who were very stubborn and kept rebelling against God; they did not continue firmly trusting in God, and they did not worship him alone.<verse eid="PSA 78:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 78:9"/>The soldiers of the tribe of Ephraim had bows and arrows, but they ran away from their enemies on the day that they fought with their enemies.<verse eid="PSA 78:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 78:10"/>They did not do what they had agreed with God that they would do; they refused to obey his laws.<verse eid="PSA 78:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 78:11"/>They forgot what he had done; they forgot about the miracles that they had seen him perform.<verse eid="PSA 78:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 78:12"/>While our ancestors were watching, God performed miracles in the area around the city of Zoan in Egypt.<verse eid="PSA 78:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 78:13"/>Then he caused the Sea of Reeds to divide, causing the water on each side to pile up like a wall, with the result that our ancestors walked through it on dry ground.<verse eid="PSA 78:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 78:14"/>He led them by a bright cloud during the day and by a fiery light during the night.<verse eid="PSA 78:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 78:15"/>He split rocks open in the wilderness and gave to our ancestors plenty of water from deep inside the earth.<verse eid="PSA 78:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 78:16"/>He caused a stream of water to flow from the rock; the water flowed like a river.<verse eid="PSA 78:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 78:17"/>But our ancestors continued to sin against God; in the wilderness they rebelled against the one who is greater than any other god.<verse eid="PSA 78:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 78:18"/>By demanding that God give them the food that they desired, they tried to find out if he would always do what they requested him to do.<verse eid="PSA 78:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 78:19"/>They insulted God by saying, “Can God supply food for us here in this desert?<verse eid="PSA 78:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 78:20"/>It is true that he struck the rock, with the result that water gushed out, but can he also provide bread and meat for us, his people?”<verse eid="PSA 78:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 78:21"/>So when Yahweh heard that, he became very angry, and he sent a fire to burn up some of his Israelite people.<verse eid="PSA 78:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 78:22"/>He did that because they did not trust in him, and they did not believe that he would rescue them.<verse eid="PSA 78:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 78:23"/>But God spoke to the sky above them and commanded it to open like a door,<verse eid="PSA 78:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 78:24"/>and then food fell down like rain, food that they named “manna.” God gave them grain from heaven.<verse eid="PSA 78:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 78:25"/>So the people ate the food that angels eat, and God gave to them all the manna that they wanted.<verse eid="PSA 78:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 78:26"/>Later, he caused the wind to blow from the east, and by his power he also sent wind from the south,<verse eid="PSA 78:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 78:27"/>and the wind brought birds which were as numerous as the grains of sand on the seashore.<verse eid="PSA 78:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 78:28"/>God caused those birds to fall in the middle of their camp. There were birds all around their tents.<verse eid="PSA 78:28"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="29" style="v" sid="PSA 78:29"/>So the people cooked the birds and ate the meat; their stomachs were full because God had given them what they wanted.<verse eid="PSA 78:29"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="30" style="v" sid="PSA 78:30"/>But they had not yet eaten all that they wanted.<verse eid="PSA 78:30"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="31" style="v" sid="PSA 78:31"/>At that point, God was still very angry with them, and he caused their strongest men to die; he got rid of many of the finest young Israelite men.<verse eid="PSA 78:31"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="32" style="v" sid="PSA 78:32"/>In spite of all this, the people continued to sin; in spite of all the miracles that God had performed, they still did not trust that he would take care of them.<verse eid="PSA 78:32"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="33" style="v" sid="PSA 78:33"/>So he made them terrified all their lives; he made them die young.<verse eid="PSA 78:33"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="34" style="v" sid="PSA 78:34"/>Whenever God caused some of the Israelites to die, the others would repent; they would be sorry and seriously ask God to save them.<verse eid="PSA 78:34"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="35" style="v" sid="PSA 78:35"/>They would remember that God was like a huge rock on which they would be safe, and that he, who was greater than any other god, was the one who protected them.<verse eid="PSA 78:35"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="36" style="v" sid="PSA 78:36"/>But they tried to deceive God by what they said; their words were all lies.<verse eid="PSA 78:36"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="37" style="v" sid="PSA 78:37"/>They were not loyal to him; they ignored the covenant that he had made with them.<verse eid="PSA 78:37"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="38" style="v" sid="PSA 78:38"/>But God acted mercifully toward his people. He forgave them for having sinned and did not get rid of them. Many times he refrained from becoming angry with them and restrained himself from furiously punishing them.<verse eid="PSA 78:38"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="39" style="v" sid="PSA 78:39"/>He remembered that they were only humans who die, humans who disappear as quickly as a wind that blows by and then is gone.<verse eid="PSA 78:39"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="40" style="v" sid="PSA 78:40"/>Many times our ancestors rebelled against God in the wilderness and made him very sad.<verse eid="PSA 78:40"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="41" style="v" sid="PSA 78:41"/>Many times they did evil things to find out if they could do those things without God punishing them. They frequently caused the holy God of Israel to become angry.<verse eid="PSA 78:41"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="42" style="v" sid="PSA 78:42"/>They forgot about his great power, and they forgot about the time when he rescued them from their enemies.<verse eid="PSA 78:42"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="43" style="v" sid="PSA 78:43"/>They forgot about when he performed many miracles in the area near the city of Zoan in Egypt.<verse eid="PSA 78:43"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="44" style="v" sid="PSA 78:44"/>He caused the Nile River to become red like blood so that the people of Egypt had no water to drink.<verse eid="PSA 78:44"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="45" style="v" sid="PSA 78:45"/>He sent among the people of Egypt swarms of flies that bit them, and he sent frogs that ate up everything.<verse eid="PSA 78:45"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="46" style="v" sid="PSA 78:46"/>He sent locusts to eat their crops and the other things that grew in their fields.<verse eid="PSA 78:46"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="47" style="v" sid="PSA 78:47"/>He sent hail that destroyed the grapevines, and he sent more hail that ruined the figs on the sycamore trees.<verse eid="PSA 78:47"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="48" style="v" sid="PSA 78:48"/>He sent hail that killed their cattle and lightning that killed their sheep and cows.<verse eid="PSA 78:48"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="49" style="v" sid="PSA 78:49"/>Because God was fiercely angry with the people of Egypt, he caused them to be very distressed. The disasters that struck them were like a group of angels that destroyed everything.<verse eid="PSA 78:49"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="50" style="v" sid="PSA 78:50"/>He did not lessen his anger with them, and he did not spare their lives; he sent a plague that killed many of them.<verse eid="PSA 78:50"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="51" style="v" sid="PSA 78:51"/>In that plague he caused all the firstborn sons of the people of Egypt to die.<verse eid="PSA 78:51"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="52" style="v" sid="PSA 78:52"/>Then he led his people out of Egypt as a shepherd leads his sheep, and he guided them while they walked through the wilderness.<verse eid="PSA 78:52"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="53" style="v" sid="PSA 78:53"/>He led them safely, and they were not afraid, but their enemies were drowned in the sea.<verse eid="PSA 78:53"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="54" style="v" sid="PSA 78:54"/>Later he brought them to Canaan, his sacred land, to Mount Zion, and by his power he enabled them to conquer the people who were living there.<verse eid="PSA 78:54"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="55" style="v" sid="PSA 78:55"/>He expelled the people groups while his people were advancing; he assigned part of the land for each tribe to possess, and he gave the houses of those people to the Israelites.<verse eid="PSA 78:55"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="56" style="v" sid="PSA 78:56"/>However, the Israelites rebelled against God, who is greater than any other God, and they did many evil things to see if they could do those things without God punishing them; they did not obey his commandments.<verse eid="PSA 78:56"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="57" style="v" sid="PSA 78:57"/>Instead, as their ancestors did, they rebelled against God and were not loyal to him; they were as unreliable as a bow that breaks when you try to shoot with it.<verse eid="PSA 78:57"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="58" style="v" sid="PSA 78:58"/>Because they worshiped carved images of their gods on the tops of hills, they caused God to become angry.<verse eid="PSA 78:58"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="59" style="v" sid="PSA 78:59"/>He saw what they were doing and became very angry, so he rejected the Israelite people.<verse eid="PSA 78:59"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="60" style="v" sid="PSA 78:60"/>He no longer appeared to them at Shiloh in the sacred tent where he had lived among them.<verse eid="PSA 78:60"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="61" style="v" sid="PSA 78:61"/>He allowed their enemies to capture the sacred chest, which was the symbol of his power and his glory.<verse eid="PSA 78:61"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="62" style="v" sid="PSA 78:62"/>Because he was angry with his people, he allowed their enemies to kill them.<verse eid="PSA 78:62"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="63" style="v" sid="PSA 78:63"/>Young men were killed in battles, with the result that the young women had no one to marry.<verse eid="PSA 78:63"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="64" style="v" sid="PSA 78:64"/>Many priests were killed by their enemies’ swords, and the people did not allow the priests’ widows to mourn.<verse eid="PSA 78:64"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="65" style="v" sid="PSA 78:65"/>Later, it was as though the Lord awoke from sleeping; he was like a strong man who became angry because he drank a lot of wine.<verse eid="PSA 78:65"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="66" style="v" sid="PSA 78:66"/>He pushed his enemies back and caused them to be very ashamed for a long time because they had been defeated.<verse eid="PSA 78:66"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="67" style="v" sid="PSA 78:67"/>But he did not set up his tent where the people of the tribe of Ephraim lived; he did not choose their area to do that.<verse eid="PSA 78:67"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="68" style="v" sid="PSA 78:68"/>Instead he chose the area where the tribe of Judah lived; he chose Mount Zion, which he loves.<verse eid="PSA 78:68"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="69" style="v" sid="PSA 78:69"/>He decided to have his temple built there, high up, like his home in heaven; he caused it to be firm, like the earth, and intended that his temple would last forever.<verse eid="PSA 78:69"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="70" style="v" sid="PSA 78:70"/>He chose David, who served him faithfully, and took him from the pastures<verse eid="PSA 78:70"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="71" style="v" sid="PSA 78:71"/>where he was taking care of his father’s sheep, and appointed him to be the leader of the Israelites, the people who would always belong to God.<verse eid="PSA 78:71"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="72" style="v" sid="PSA 78:72"/>David took care of the Israelite people sincerely and wholeheartedly, and he guided them skillfully.<verse eid="PSA 78:72"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 78"/>
<chapter number="79" style="c" sid="PSA 79"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 79:1"/>A psalm written by Asaph; God, other people groups have invaded your own land. They have desecrated your temple, and they have destroyed all the buildings in Jerusalem.<verse eid="PSA 79:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 79:2"/>Instead of burying the corpses of your people whom they killed, they allowed the vultures to eat the flesh of those corpses, and they also allowed wild animals to eat the corpses of your people.<verse eid="PSA 79:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 79:3"/>When they killed your people, your people’s blood flowed like water through the streets of Jerusalem, and there was almost no one left to bury their corpses.<verse eid="PSA 79:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 79:4"/>The people groups that live in countries that surround our land insult us; they laugh at us and mock us.<verse eid="PSA 79:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 79:5"/>Yahweh, how long will this continue? Will you be angry with us forever? Will your anger be like a fire burning within you?<verse eid="PSA 79:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 79:6"/>Instead of being angry with us, be angry with the people groups that do not know you! Be angry with kingdoms whose people do not pray to you<verse eid="PSA 79:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 79:7"/>because they have killed Israelite people and they have ruined your country.<verse eid="PSA 79:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 79:8"/>Do not punish us because of the sins that our ancestors committed! Act mercifully toward us now because we are very discouraged.<verse eid="PSA 79:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 79:9"/>God, you have saved us many times, so help us now; rescue us and forgive us for having sinned so that other people will honor you.<verse eid="PSA 79:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 79:10"/>It is not right that the other people groups say about us, “If their God is very powerful, why does he not help them?” Allow us to see you punishing the people of other nations in return for their shedding our blood and killing many of us, your people.<verse eid="PSA 79:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 79:11"/>Listen to your people groaning while they are in prison, and by your great power, free those whom our enemies say they will certainly execute.<verse eid="PSA 79:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 79:12"/>In return for their having often insulted you, punish them seven times as much!<verse eid="PSA 79:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 79:13"/>After you do that, we, whom you take care of as a shepherd takes care of his sheep, will continue praising you; we will continue to praise you from generation to generation forever.<verse eid="PSA 79:13"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 79"/>
<chapter number="80" style="c" sid="PSA 80"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 80:1"/>A psalm written by Asaph for the choir director, to be sung using the tune ‘Lilies of the covenant’ Yahweh, you who lead us as a shepherd leads his flock of sheep, you who sit on your throne in the Very Holy Place in the temple, above the figures of winged creatures, come and do powerful things for us Israelite people.<verse eid="PSA 80:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 80:2"/>Show yourself to the people of the tribes of Ephraim and Benjamin and Manasseh! Show us that you are powerful and come and rescue us!<verse eid="PSA 80:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 80:3"/>God, cause our nation to be strong like it was before; act kindly toward us so that we may be saved from our enemies!<verse eid="PSA 80:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 80:4"/>Yahweh, commander of the angel armies, how long will you be angry with us, your people, when we pray to you?<verse eid="PSA 80:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 80:5"/>It is as though the only food and drink that you have given us is a cup full of our tears!<verse eid="PSA 80:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 80:6"/>You have allowed the people groups that surround us to argue with each other to decide which part of our land each of them will take; they laugh at us.<verse eid="PSA 80:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 80:7"/>God, Commander of the angel armies, make our nation strong as it was before! Act kindly toward us so that we may be saved!<verse eid="PSA 80:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 80:8"/>Our ancestors were like a grapevine that you brought out of Egypt; you drove out the other people groups from this land, and you put your people in their land.<verse eid="PSA 80:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 80:9"/>As people clear ground to plant a grapevine, you cleared out the people who were living in this land for us to live in it. As the roots of a grapevine go deep down into the ground and spread, you enabled our ancestors to prosper and start living in towns all over this land.<verse eid="PSA 80:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 80:10"/>As huge grapevines cover the hills with their shade and as their branches are taller than big cedar trees,<verse eid="PSA 80:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 80:11"/>your people ruled all of Canaan, from the Mediterranean Sea in the west to the Euphrates River in the east.<verse eid="PSA 80:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 80:12"/>So why have you abandoned us and allowed our enemies to tear down our walls? You are like someone who tears down the fences around his vineyard, so that all the people who pass by can steal the grapes;<verse eid="PSA 80:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 80:13"/>wild pigs can trample the vines, and wild animals can also eat the grapes.<verse eid="PSA 80:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 80:14"/>You who are the commander of the angel armies, turn to us! Look down from heaven and see what is happening to us! Come and rescue us who are like your grapevine,<verse eid="PSA 80:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 80:15"/>who are like the young vine that you planted and caused to grow!<verse eid="PSA 80:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 80:16"/>Our enemies have torn down and burned everything in our land; look at them angrily and get rid of them!<verse eid="PSA 80:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 80:17"/>But strengthen us people whom you have chosen, us Israelite people, whom you previously caused to be very strong.<verse eid="PSA 80:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 80:18"/>When you do that, we will never turn away from you again; revive us, and then we will praise you.<verse eid="PSA 80:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 80:19"/>Yahweh, commander of the angel armies, restore us; act kindly toward us and rescue us from our enemies!<verse eid="PSA 80:19"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 80"/>
<chapter number="81" style="c" sid="PSA 81"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 81:1"/>A psalm written by Asaph for the choir director; Sing songs to praise God, who enables us to be strong when we fight our enemies; shout joyfully to God, whom we descendants of Jacob worship!<verse eid="PSA 81:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 81:2"/>Start playing the music, and beat the tambourines; play nice music on the harps and lyres.<verse eid="PSA 81:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 81:3"/>Blow the trumpets during the festival to celebrate each new moon, each time the moon is full, and during our other festivals.<verse eid="PSA 81:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 81:4"/>Do that because that is a decree for us Israelite people; it is a command that God made for the descendants of Jacob.<verse eid="PSA 81:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 81:5"/>He made it a law at the time when God led the descendants of Joseph out of the land of Egypt. I heard a voice I did not recognize, and it said:<verse eid="PSA 81:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 81:6"/>“After the rulers of Egypt forced you Israelites to work as slaves, I took those heavy burdens off your backs, and I enabled you to lay down those heavy baskets of bricks that you were carrying.<verse eid="PSA 81:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 81:7"/>When you were greatly distressed, you called out to me, and I rescued you; I answered you out of a thundercloud. Later I tested whether you would trust me to give you water when you were in the desert at Meribah.<verse eid="PSA 81:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 81:8"/>You who are my people, listen while I warn you! I wish that you Israelite people would pay attention to what I say to you!<verse eid="PSA 81:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 81:9"/>You must not have any idols of other gods among you; you must never bow to worship any of them!<verse eid="PSA 81:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 81:10"/>I am Yahweh, your God; It was not any of those gods who brought you out of Egypt; I am the one who did it! So request what you want me to do for you, and I will do it.<verse eid="PSA 81:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 81:11"/>But my people would not listen to me; they would not obey me.<verse eid="PSA 81:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 81:12"/>So because they were very stubborn, I allowed them to do whatever they wanted to do.<verse eid="PSA 81:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 81:13"/>I wish that my people would listen to me, that the Israelite people would behave as I want them to do.<verse eid="PSA 81:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 81:14"/>If they did that, I would quickly defeat their enemies; I would strike dead those who are oppressing them.<verse eid="PSA 81:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 81:15"/>Then all those who hate me would cringe before me, and then I would punish them forever.<verse eid="PSA 81:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 81:16"/>But I would give you Israelites very good wheat, and I would fill your stomachs with wild honey.”<verse eid="PSA 81:16"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 81"/>
<chapter number="82" style="c" sid="PSA 82"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 82:1"/>A psalm written by Asaph; God stands in heaven in a meeting of all the spirits whom he has placed in charge of what he created. He tells them that he has decided this:<verse eid="PSA 82:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 82:2"/>“You must stop judging people unfairly; you must no longer make decisions that favor wicked people!<verse eid="PSA 82:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 82:3"/>You must defend people who are poor and orphans; you must act fairly toward those who are needy and those who have no one to help them.<verse eid="PSA 82:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 82:4"/>Rescue them from the power of the wicked people!”<verse eid="PSA 82:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 82:5"/>Those rulers do not know or understand anything! They are very corrupt, and as a result of their corrupt behavior, it is as though the foundation of the world is being shaken!<verse eid="PSA 82:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 82:6"/>I previously said to them, “You think you are gods! It is as though you are all my sons,<verse eid="PSA 82:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 82:7"/>but you will die as people do; your lives will end as the lives of all rulers end.”<verse eid="PSA 82:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 82:8"/>God, arise and judge everyone on the earth because all the people groups belong to you!<verse eid="PSA 82:8"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 82"/>
<chapter number="83" style="c" sid="PSA 83"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 83:1"/>A psalm which is a song written by Asaph; God, do not continue to be silent! Do not be quiet and say nothing<verse eid="PSA 83:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 83:2"/>because your enemies are rioting against you; those who hate you are rebelling against you!<verse eid="PSA 83:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 83:3"/>They are secretly planning to do things to harm us, your people; they are conspiring together against the people whom you protect.<verse eid="PSA 83:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 83:4"/>They say, “Come, we must destroy their nation so that no one will remember that Israel ever existed!”<verse eid="PSA 83:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 83:5"/>They have agreed on what they want to do to destroy Israel, and they have agreed to attack you together.<verse eid="PSA 83:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 83:6"/>Your enemies are the people who live in the tents of Edom— the Ishmaelites, Moab and the Hagrites, they conspire together with<verse eid="PSA 83:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 83:7"/>the people of Gebal, and the Ammonites, and the Amalekites, and the Philistines, and the people of the city of Tyre.<verse eid="PSA 83:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 83:8"/>The people of Assyria have joined them; they are strong allies of the Moab and Ammon people groups, who are descendants of Abraham’s nephew Lot.<verse eid="PSA 83:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 83:9"/>God, do to those people things as you did to the Midian people group, as you did to Sisera and Jabin at the river Kishon.<verse eid="PSA 83:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 83:10"/>You destroyed them at the town of Endor, and their corpses lay on the ground and decayed.<verse eid="PSA 83:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 83:11"/>Do to them things like you did to kings Oreb and Zeeb; defeat their leaders like you defeated Zebah and Zalmunna,<verse eid="PSA 83:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 83:12"/>who said, “We will take for ourselves the land that the Israelites say belongs to God!”<verse eid="PSA 83:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 83:13"/>My God, cause them to disappear quickly like whirling dust, like chaff that the wind blows away!<verse eid="PSA 83:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 83:14"/>As a fire completely burns a forest and as flames burn in the mountains,<verse eid="PSA 83:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 83:15"/>expel them with your storms and cause them to be terrified by your big storms!<verse eid="PSA 83:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 83:16"/>Cause them to be very ashamed so that they will admit that you are very powerful.<verse eid="PSA 83:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 83:17"/>Cause them to be forever disgraced because of being defeated, and cause them to die while they are still disgraced.<verse eid="PSA 83:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 83:18"/>Cause them to know that you, whose name is Yahweh, are the supreme ruler over everything on the earth.<verse eid="PSA 83:18"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 83"/>
<chapter number="84" style="c" sid="PSA 84"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 84:1"/>A psalm written by one of the descendants of Korah for the choir director; Yahweh, commander of the angel armies, your temple is very beautiful!<verse eid="PSA 84:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 84:2"/>I would like to be there; Yahweh, I desire that very much. With all my inner being I sing joyfully to you, the all-powerful God.<verse eid="PSA 84:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 84:3"/>Even sparrows and swallows have built nests near your temple; they take care of their young babies near the altars where people offer sacrifices to you, Commander of the angel armies, my king and my God.<verse eid="PSA 84:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 84:4"/>How fortunate are those who are always in your temple, constantly singing to praise you.<verse eid="PSA 84:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 84:5"/>How fortunate are those whom you make strong, those who desire very much to make the trip up to Mount Zion.<verse eid="PSA 84:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 84:6"/>While they travel through the dryValley of Tears, you cause it to become a place where there are springs of water, where the rains in the autumn fill the valley with water, a blessing from you.<verse eid="PSA 84:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 84:7"/>As a result, those who travel through there become stronger knowing that they will appear in your presence on Mount Zion.<verse eid="PSA 84:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 84:8"/>Yahweh, commander of the angel armies, listen to my prayer; God, whom we descendants of Jacob worship, hear what I am saying!<verse eid="PSA 84:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 84:9"/>God, act kindly toward our king, the one who protects us, the one whom you have chosen to rule us.<verse eid="PSA 84:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 84:10"/>For me, spending one day in your temple is better than spending a thousand days somewhere else; standing at the entrance to your temple, ready to go inside, is better than living in the tents where wicked people live.<verse eid="PSA 84:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 84:11"/>Yahweh our God is like the sun that shines on us and like a shield that protects us; he acts favorably toward us and honors us. Yahweh does not refuse to give any good thing to those who do what is right.<verse eid="PSA 84:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 84:12"/>Yahweh, commander of the angel armies, how fortunate are those who trust in you!<verse eid="PSA 84:12"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 84"/>
<chapter number="85" style="c" sid="PSA 85"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 85:1"/>A psalm written by one of the descendants of Korah for the choir director; Yahweh, you have acted kindly toward us people who live in this land; you have enabled us Israelite people to become prosperous again.<verse eid="PSA 85:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 85:2"/>You forgave us, your people, for the sins that we had committed; you pardoned us for all our sins.<verse eid="PSA 85:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 85:3"/>You stopped being angry with us and turned away from severely punishing us.<verse eid="PSA 85:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 85:4"/>Now, God, the only one who can save us, stop being angry with us and help us.<verse eid="PSA 85:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 85:5"/>Will you continue to be angry with us forever?<verse eid="PSA 85:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 85:6"/>Please enable us to prosper again so that we, your people, will rejoice about what you have done for us.<verse eid="PSA 85:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 85:7"/>Yahweh, by rescuing us from our troubles, show us that you faithfully love us.<verse eid="PSA 85:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 85:8"/>I want to listen to what Yahweh our God says because he promises that he will enable us, his people, to live peacefully if we do not return to doing foolish things.<verse eid="PSA 85:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 85:9"/>He is surely ready to save those who have an awesome respect for him, so that his glory will remain in our land.<verse eid="PSA 85:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 85:10"/>When that happens, he will both faithfully love us and faithfully do for us what he promised to do; we will act righteously, and he will give us peace, which will be like a kiss that he gives us.<verse eid="PSA 85:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 85:11"/>Here on earth, we will be loyal to God, and from heaven, God will act justly toward us.<verse eid="PSA 85:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 85:12"/>Yes, Yahweh will do good things for us, and there will be great harvests in our land.<verse eid="PSA 85:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 85:13"/>Yahweh always acts righteously; he acts righteously wherever he goes.<verse eid="PSA 85:13"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 85"/>
<chapter number="86" style="c" sid="PSA 86"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 86:1"/>A prayer written by David; Yahweh, listen to what I say and answer me because I am weak and needy.<verse eid="PSA 86:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 86:2"/>Prevent me from dying now because I am loyal to you; save me because I serve you and I trust in you, my God.<verse eid="PSA 86:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 86:3"/>Lord, act kindly toward me because I cry out to you all during each day.<verse eid="PSA 86:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 86:4"/>Lord, cause me to be glad, because I pray to you.<verse eid="PSA 86:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 86:5"/>Lord, you are good to us, and you forgive us; you faithfully love very much all those who pray to you.<verse eid="PSA 86:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 86:6"/>Yahweh, listen to my prayer; hear me when I cry out to you to help me.<verse eid="PSA 86:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 86:7"/>When I have troubles, I call out to you because you answer me.<verse eid="PSA 86:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 86:8"/>Lord, among all the gods whom the heathen nations worship, there is no one like you; not one of them has done the great things that you have done.<verse eid="PSA 86:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 86:9"/>Lord, someday people from all the nations that you have established will come and bow down in front of you, and they will praise you.<verse eid="PSA 86:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 86:10"/>You are great, and you do wonderful things; only you are God.<verse eid="PSA 86:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 86:11"/>Yahweh, teach me what you want me to do so that I may conduct my life according to what you say, all of which is right. Cause me to have an awesome respect for you with all my inner being.<verse eid="PSA 86:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 86:12"/>Lord, my God, I will thank you with all my inner being, and I will praise you forever.<verse eid="PSA 86:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 86:13"/>You faithfully love me very much as you have promised; you have prevented me from dying and going to the place where dead people are.<verse eid="PSA 86:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 86:14"/>But God, proud men are trying to attack me; a gang of cruel men are wanting to kill me; they are men who do not have any respect for you.<verse eid="PSA 86:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 86:15"/>But Lord, you always act mercifully and kindly; you do not become angry quickly; you faithfully love us very much and always do for us what you have promised to do.<verse eid="PSA 86:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 86:16"/>Look down toward me and act mercifully to me; cause me to be strong and save me, the one who serves you faithfully as my mother did.<verse eid="PSA 86:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 86:17"/>Yahweh, do something to show me that you are being good to me so that those who hate me will see that you have encouraged me and helped me; as a result, they will be ashamed.<verse eid="PSA 86:17"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 86"/>
<chapter number="87" style="c" sid="PSA 87"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 87:1"/>A psalm written by one of the descendants of Korah; The city is established on his holy mountain.<verse eid="PSA 87:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 87:2"/>Yahweh loves that city, Jerusalem, more than he loves any other place in Israel.<verse eid="PSA 87:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 87:3"/>All you people in Jerusalem, other people say wonderful things about your city.<verse eid="PSA 87:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 87:4"/>And Yahweh said, “I will talk of Rahab and Babyon and the people there who know me. There are some who know me among the people of Egypt and Babylonia, and they live in the lands of Philistia and Tyre and Ethiopia, and they will say, ‘Our home is Jerusalem and our land is Zion.’”<verse eid="PSA 87:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 87:5"/>Concerning Zion, people will say, “All of these people who were born far away, they call Jerusalem their home, and Almighty God will cause that city to remain strong.”<verse eid="PSA 87:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 87:6"/>Yahweh will write a list of the names of the people of various groups who belong to him, and he will say that he considers them all to be citizens of Jerusalem.<verse eid="PSA 87:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 87:7"/>They will all dance and sing, saying, “Jerusalem is the source of all our blessings.”<verse eid="PSA 87:7"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 87"/>
<chapter number="88" style="c" sid="PSA 88"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 88:1"/>A psalm that expresses sadness, written for the choir director by Zerah’s son Heman, one of the descendants of Korah; Yahweh God, you who rescue me, all during each day I call out to you to help me, and I cry out to you during each night also.<verse eid="PSA 88:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 88:2"/>Listen to my prayer while I cry out to you for help!<verse eid="PSA 88:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 88:3"/>I have experienced many troubles, and I am about to die and go where dead people are.<verse eid="PSA 88:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 88:4"/>Because I have no more strength, other people believe that I will soon die.<verse eid="PSA 88:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 88:5"/>I am like a corpse that has been abandoned; I am like dead people who lie in their graves, people who have been completely forgotten because you do not take care of them anymore.<verse eid="PSA 88:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 88:6"/>It is as though you have thrown me into a deep, dark pit, into a place where they throw corpses.<verse eid="PSA 88:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 88:7"/>It seems as though you are very angry with me, and it is as though you have crushed me as ocean waves crash down on people.<verse eid="PSA 88:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 88:8"/>You have caused my friends to avoid me; I have become repulsive to them. It is as though I were in a prison and cannot escape.<verse eid="PSA 88:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 88:9"/>My eyes cannot see well because I cry very much. Yahweh, every day I call out to you to help me; I lift up my hands to you while I pray.<verse eid="PSA 88:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 88:10"/>You certainly do not perform miracles for dead people! Their spirits do not arise to praise you!<verse eid="PSA 88:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 88:11"/>Corpses in the grave certainly do not tell about your faithfully loving us, and in the place where people are finally destroyed, no one tells about what you faithfully do for us.<verse eid="PSA 88:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 88:12"/>No one in the deep, dark pit ever sees the miracles that you perform, and no one in the place where people have been completely forgotten tells about your being good to us.<verse eid="PSA 88:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 88:13"/>But as for me, Yahweh, I cry out to you to help me; each morning I pray to you.<verse eid="PSA 88:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 88:14"/>Yahweh, why do you reject me? Why do you turn away from me?<verse eid="PSA 88:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 88:15"/>All the time since I was young, I have suffered and have often almost died; I am in despair because of enduring the terrible things that you have done to me.<verse eid="PSA 88:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 88:16"/>I feel that you have crushed me because of your being angry with me; the terrible things that you are doing to me are almost destroying me.<verse eid="PSA 88:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 88:17"/>It is as though they surround me like a flood; they are closing in on me from all sides.<verse eid="PSA 88:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 88:18"/>You have caused even my friends and others whom I love to avoid me, and it is as though the only friend that I have is darkness.<verse eid="PSA 88:18"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 88"/>
<chapter number="89" style="c" sid="PSA 89"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 89:1"/>A song written by Ethan, from the clan of Ezra; Yahweh, I will sing forever about the ways you faithfully love me; people not yet born will hear that you faithfully do all that you have promised.<verse eid="PSA 89:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 89:2"/>I will tell people that you will faithfully love us forever, and that your being faithful to do what you have promised is as permanent as the sky.<verse eid="PSA 89:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 89:3"/>Yahweh said, “I have made an agreement with David, whom I chose to serve me. I have made this solemn agreement with him:<verse eid="PSA 89:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 89:4"/>‘I will enable various ones of your descendants to always be kings; the line of kings descended from you will never end.’”<verse eid="PSA 89:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 89:5"/>Yahweh, I desire that all those beings who are in heaven will praise you for the wonderful things that you do, and that all your holy angels will sing about how you faithfully do what you promise.<verse eid="PSA 89:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 89:6"/>There is no one in heaven who can be compared with you, Yahweh. There are no angels in heaven who are equal to you.<verse eid="PSA 89:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 89:7"/>When your holy angels gather together, they declare that you must be revered; they say that you are more awesome than all the angels that surround your throne!<verse eid="PSA 89:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 89:8"/>O Yahweh God, commander of the angel armies, there is no one who is as powerful as you are; your faithfully doing all that you promise is like a cloak that always surrounds you.<verse eid="PSA 89:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 89:9"/>You rule over the powerful seas; when their waves rise up, you calm them.<verse eid="PSA 89:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 89:10"/>You are the one who crushed and killed the great sea monster named Rahab. You defeated and scattered your enemies with your great power.<verse eid="PSA 89:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 89:11"/>The heavens are yours, and the earth is yours; everything on the earth is yours because you created it all.<verse eid="PSA 89:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 89:12"/>You created everything from the north to the south. Mount Tabor and Mount Hermon joyfully praise you .<verse eid="PSA 89:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 89:13"/>You are very powerful; you are extremely strong.<verse eid="PSA 89:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 89:14"/>You rule over people fairly and justly; you are always faithfully loving us and doing what you promised.<verse eid="PSA 89:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 89:15"/>Yahweh, how fortunate are those who worship you with joyful shouts in their festivals, who live knowing that you are always watching over them.<verse eid="PSA 89:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 89:16"/>Every day, throughout the day, they rejoice in what you have done, and they praise you for being very good to them.<verse eid="PSA 89:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 89:17"/>You give us your glorious strength; because you act in our favor, we defeat our enemies.<verse eid="PSA 89:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 89:18"/>Yahweh, you gave us the one who protects us; you, the holy God whom we Israelites worship, he gave us our king.<verse eid="PSA 89:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 89:19"/>Long ago you spoke in a vision to one of your servants, saying, “I have crowned a famous soldier; I chose him from among all the people to be a king.<verse eid="PSA 89:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 89:20"/>That man is David, the one who will serve me faithfully, and I anointed him with sacred olive oil to make him king.<verse eid="PSA 89:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 89:21"/>My strength will always be with him; with my power, I will make him strong.<verse eid="PSA 89:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 89:22"/>His enemies will never find ways to outwit him, and wicked people will never defeat him.<verse eid="PSA 89:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 89:23"/>I will crush his enemies in front of him and get rid of those who hate him.<verse eid="PSA 89:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 89:24"/>I will always be loyal to him and faithfully love him and enable him to defeat his enemies.<verse eid="PSA 89:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 89:25"/>I will cause his kingdom to include all the land from the Mediterranean Sea to the Euphrates River.<verse eid="PSA 89:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 89:26"/>He will say to me, ‘You are my Father, my God, the one who protects and saves me.’<verse eid="PSA 89:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 89:27"/>I will give him the rights as my firstborn son; he will be the greatest king on the earth.<verse eid="PSA 89:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 89:28"/>I will always be loyal to him, and my agreement to bless him will last forever.<verse eid="PSA 89:28"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="29" style="v" sid="PSA 89:29"/>I will establish a line of his descendants that will never end, various ones of his descendants will always be kings.<verse eid="PSA 89:29"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="30" style="v" sid="PSA 89:30"/>But if some of his descendants disobey my laws and do not behave as my commands say that they should,<verse eid="PSA 89:30"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="31" style="v" sid="PSA 89:31"/>if they disregard my requirements and do not do the right things that I have told them to do,<verse eid="PSA 89:31"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="32" style="v" sid="PSA 89:32"/>I will punish them severely and cause them to suffer for doing wrong.<verse eid="PSA 89:32"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="33" style="v" sid="PSA 89:33"/>But I will not stop faithfully loving David, and I will always do what I promised him.<verse eid="PSA 89:33"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="34" style="v" sid="PSA 89:34"/>I will not break the agreement that I made with him; I will not change even one word that I spoke to him.<verse eid="PSA 89:34"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="35" style="v" sid="PSA 89:35"/>Once I made a solemn promise to David, and that will never change; because I am God, I will never lie to David.<verse eid="PSA 89:35"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="36" style="v" sid="PSA 89:36"/>I promised that the line of kings descended from him will go on forever; it will last as long as the sun shines.<verse eid="PSA 89:36"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="37" style="v" sid="PSA 89:37"/>That line will be as permanent as the moon that is always watching everything here on earth.”<verse eid="PSA 89:37"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="38" style="v" sid="PSA 89:38"/>But Yahweh, now you have rejected him! You are very angry with the king whom you appointed.<verse eid="PSA 89:38"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="39" style="v" sid="PSA 89:39"/>It seems that you have broken the agreement that you made with your servant, David; it seems as though you have thrown his crown into the dust.<verse eid="PSA 89:39"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="40" style="v" sid="PSA 89:40"/>You have torn down the walls that protect his city and allowed all his forts to become ruins.<verse eid="PSA 89:40"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="41" style="v" sid="PSA 89:41"/>All those who pass by plunder his possessions; his neighbors laugh at him.<verse eid="PSA 89:41"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="42" style="v" sid="PSA 89:42"/>You have enabled his enemies to defeat him; you have made them all happy.<verse eid="PSA 89:42"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="43" style="v" sid="PSA 89:43"/>You have caused his sword to become useless, and you have not helped him in his battles.<verse eid="PSA 89:43"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="44" style="v" sid="PSA 89:44"/>You have caused his splendor to end and knocked his throne to the ground.<verse eid="PSA 89:44"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="45" style="v" sid="PSA 89:45"/>You have caused him to become old when he is still young and caused him to be very shamed.<verse eid="PSA 89:45"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="46" style="v" sid="PSA 89:46"/>O Yahweh, how long will this continue? Will you hide yourself from us forever? How long will your anger against us burn like a fire?<verse eid="PSA 89:46"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="47" style="v" sid="PSA 89:47"/>Do not forget that life is very short; Do not forget that you have created all of us to die uselessly.<verse eid="PSA 89:47"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="48" style="v" sid="PSA 89:48"/>No one can keep on living and never die; no one can bring himself back from the place of the dead.<verse eid="PSA 89:48"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="49" style="v" sid="PSA 89:49"/>Yahweh, you promised long ago that you would faithfully love me; why are you not doing that? You solemnly promised this to David!<verse eid="PSA 89:49"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="50" style="v" sid="PSA 89:50"/>Yahweh, do not forget that people insult us! Heathen people curse me!<verse eid="PSA 89:50"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="51" style="v" sid="PSA 89:51"/>Yahweh, your enemies insult your chosen king! They insult him wherever he goes.<verse eid="PSA 89:51"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="52" style="v" sid="PSA 89:52"/>I hope that Yahweh will be praised forever! Amen! May it be so!<verse eid="PSA 89:52"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 89"/>
<chapter number="90" style="c" sid="PSA 90"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 90:1"/>A prayer by the prophet Moses; Lord, you have always been like a home for us.<verse eid="PSA 90:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 90:2"/>Before you created the mountains, before you formed the earth and everything that is in it, you were eternally God, and you will be God forever.<verse eid="PSA 90:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 90:3"/>When people die, you cause their corpses to become soil again; you change their corpses to become dirt like that from which the first man was created.<verse eid="PSA 90:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 90:4"/>When you consider time, a thousand years are as short as one day that passes; you consider that they are as short as a few hours in the night.<verse eid="PSA 90:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 90:5"/>You cause people to die suddenly; they live only a short time as a dream lasts only a short time. They are like grass that grows up.<verse eid="PSA 90:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 90:6"/>In the morning the grass sprouts and grows well, but in the evening it dries up and completely withers.<verse eid="PSA 90:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 90:7"/>Similarly, because of the sins that we commit, you become angry with us; you terrify us and then you destroy us.<verse eid="PSA 90:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 90:8"/>It is as though you place our sins in front of you; you spread out even our secret sins where you can see them.<verse eid="PSA 90:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 90:9"/>Because you are angry with us, you cause our lives to end; the years that we live pass as quickly as a sigh does.<verse eid="PSA 90:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 90:10"/>People live for only seventy years; if they are strong, some of them live for eighty years. But even during good years we have much pain and troubles; our lives soon end, and we die.<verse eid="PSA 90:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 90:11"/>No one has really experienced the powerful things you can do to them when you are angry with them, and people are not afraid that you will punish them because of your being angry with them.<verse eid="PSA 90:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 90:12"/>So teach us to realize that we live for only a short time in order that we may use our time wisely.<verse eid="PSA 90:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 90:13"/>Yahweh, how long will you be angry with us? Pity us who serve you.<verse eid="PSA 90:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 90:14"/>Each morning, show us that it is enough for us if you love us faithfully as you have promised you would do. Show us this so that we may shout joyfully and be happy all during the years that we live.<verse eid="PSA 90:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 90:15"/>Cause us to be now as happy for as many years as you afflicted us and we experienced troubles.<verse eid="PSA 90:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 90:16"/>Enable us to see the great things that you do, and enable our descendants to see your glorious power also.<verse eid="PSA 90:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 90:17"/>Lord, our God, give us your blessings and enable us to be successful; yes, cause us to be successful in everything that we do!<verse eid="PSA 90:17"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 90"/>
<chapter number="91" style="c" sid="PSA 91"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 91:1"/>Those who live under the protection of God Almighty, will be able to rest safely under his care.<verse eid="PSA 91:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 91:2"/>I will declare to Yahweh, “You protect me; you are like a fort in which I am safe. You are my God, the one in whom I trust.”<verse eid="PSA 91:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 91:3"/>He will rescue you from all hidden traps and save you from deadly diseases.<verse eid="PSA 91:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 91:4"/>He will shield you as a bird protects her young under her wings. You will be safe in his care. His faithfully doing what he has promised is like a shield that will protect you.<verse eid="PSA 91:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 91:5"/>You will not be afraid of things that happen during the night that could terrorize you or of arrows that your enemies will shoot at you during the day.<verse eid="PSA 91:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 91:6"/>You will not be afraid of plagues that demons cause when they attack people at night or of other evil forces that kill people at midday.<verse eid="PSA 91:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 91:7"/>Even if a thousand people fall dead alongside you, even if ten thousand people are dying around you, you will not be harmed.<verse eid="PSA 91:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 91:8"/>Look and see that wicked people are being punished!<verse eid="PSA 91:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 91:9"/>Yahweh protects me; trust God Almighty to shelter you, too.<verse eid="PSA 91:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 91:10"/>If you do, nothing evil will happen to you; no plague will come near your house<verse eid="PSA 91:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 91:11"/>because Yahweh will command his angels to protect you in whatever you are doing.<verse eid="PSA 91:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 91:12"/>They will hold you up with their hands so that you will not hurt your foot on a big stone.<verse eid="PSA 91:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 91:13"/>You will be kept safe from being harmed by your enemies; it will be as though you were killing strong lions and poisonous snakes by stepping on them!<verse eid="PSA 91:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 91:14"/>Yahweh says, “I will rescue those who love me; I will protect them because they acknowledge that I am Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 91:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 91:15"/>When they call out to me, I will answer them. I will help them when they are experiencing trouble; I will rescue them and honor them.<verse eid="PSA 91:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 91:16"/>I will reward them by enabling them to live a long time, and I will save them.”<verse eid="PSA 91:16"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 91"/>
<chapter number="92" style="c" sid="PSA 92"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 92:1"/>A psalm that is to be sung on Sabbath days. Yahweh, it is good for people to thank you and to sing praise to you who are greater than any other god.<verse eid="PSA 92:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 92:2"/>It is good to proclaim every morning that you faithfully love us and to sing songs each night that declare that you always do what you have promised to do,<verse eid="PSA 92:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 92:3"/>accompanied by musicians playing harps that have ten strings and by the sounds made by a lyre.<verse eid="PSA 92:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 92:4"/>Yahweh, you have caused me to be glad; I sing joyfully because of what you have done.<verse eid="PSA 92:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 92:5"/>Yahweh, the things that you do are great! But it is difficult to understand all that you think.<verse eid="PSA 92:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 92:6"/>There are things that you do that foolish people cannot know about, things that stupid people cannot understand.<verse eid="PSA 92:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 92:7"/>They do not understand that although the number of wicked people increases as blades of grass do and that those who do what is evil prosper, they will be completely destroyed.<verse eid="PSA 92:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 92:8"/>But Yahweh, you will be king forever.<verse eid="PSA 92:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 92:9"/>Yahweh, your enemies will certainly die, and those who do wicked things will be defeated.<verse eid="PSA 92:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 92:10"/>But you have caused me to be as strong as a wild ox; you have caused me to be very joyful.<verse eid="PSA 92:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 92:11"/>I have seen you defeat my enemies, and I have heard those evil men wail while they were being slaughtered.<verse eid="PSA 92:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 92:12"/>But righteous people will prosper like palm trees that grow well, like the cedar trees that grow in Lebanon.<verse eid="PSA 92:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 92:13"/>They are like the trees that people plant at the temple of Yahweh in Jerusalem, the trees that are close to the courtyard of the temple of our God.<verse eid="PSA 92:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 92:14"/>Even when righteous people become old, they do many things that please God. They remain strong and full of energy like trees that remain full of sap.<verse eid="PSA 92:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 92:15"/>That shows that Yahweh is just; he is like a huge rock on which I am safe, and he never does anything that is wicked.<verse eid="PSA 92:15"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 92"/>
<chapter number="93" style="c" sid="PSA 93"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 93:1"/>Yahweh, you have become the King! The majesty and the power that you have are like robes that a king wears. You put the world firmly in place, and it will never be moved out of its place.<verse eid="PSA 93:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 93:2"/>You started to rule as king a very long time ago; you have always existed.<verse eid="PSA 93:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 93:3"/>Yahweh, when you created the world, you separated the water from the chaotic mass and formed oceans, and the waves of the waters of those oceans still roar,<verse eid="PSA 93:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 93:4"/>but you are greater than the roar of those oceans, more powerful than the ocean waves! You are Yahweh, the one who is greater than any other god!<verse eid="PSA 93:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 93:5"/>Yahweh, your laws never change, and your temple has always been holy. That will be true forever.<verse eid="PSA 93:5"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 93"/>
<chapter number="94" style="c" sid="PSA 94"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 94:1"/>Yahweh, you are able to get revenge on your enemies. So show them that you are going to punish them!<verse eid="PSA 94:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 94:2"/>You are the one who judges all people on the earth; so arise and give them what they deserve.<verse eid="PSA 94:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 94:3"/>Yahweh, how long will those wicked people be glad? It is not right that they continue being glad!<verse eid="PSA 94:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 94:4"/>They do evil things, and they boast about doing them; how long will they be allowed to continue doing that?<verse eid="PSA 94:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 94:5"/>Yahweh, it is as though those wicked people were crushing us, your people; they oppress the nation that you have made and that belongs to you alone.<verse eid="PSA 94:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 94:6"/>They murder widows and orphans and people from other countries who think it is safe to live in our land.<verse eid="PSA 94:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 94:7"/>Those wicked people say, “Yahweh does not see anything; the God whom those Israelites worship does not see the evil things that we do.”<verse eid="PSA 94:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 94:8"/>You evil people who rule Israel, you are foolish and stupid; when will you become wise?<verse eid="PSA 94:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 94:9"/>God made our ears; do you think that he cannot hear what you say? He created our eyes; do you think that he cannot see the evil things that you do?<verse eid="PSA 94:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 94:10"/>He corrects the leaders of other nations; do you think that he will not punish you? He is the one who knows everything; why do you think that he does not know what you do?<verse eid="PSA 94:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 94:11"/>Yahweh knows everything that people are thinking; he knows that what they think is evil and useless.<verse eid="PSA 94:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 94:12"/>Yahweh, how fortunate are those who allow you to discipline them, those who want you to teach them your laws.<verse eid="PSA 94:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 94:13"/>When those people have had troubles, you cause those troubles to cease, and someday it will be as though you will dig pits for the wicked people, and that they will fall into those pits and die.<verse eid="PSA 94:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 94:14"/>Yahweh will not abandon his people; he will not desert those who belong to him .<verse eid="PSA 94:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 94:15"/>Someday judges will decide matters fairly for people, and all honest people will be pleased about that.<verse eid="PSA 94:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 94:16"/>But when wicked people oppressed me, no one defended me! No one stood up to testify for me against those evil people.<verse eid="PSA 94:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 94:17"/>If Yahweh had not helped me at that time, I would have been executed; my life would have gone to the place where dead people say nothing.<verse eid="PSA 94:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 94:18"/>I said, “I am falling into disaster,” but, Yahweh, you held me up by faithfully loving me.<verse eid="PSA 94:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 94:19"/>Whenever I am very worried, you comfort me and cause me to be happy.<verse eid="PSA 94:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 94:20"/>You have nothing to do with wicked judges, those who establish laws that allow people to do what is not right.<verse eid="PSA 94:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 94:21"/>They plan to get rid of righteous people, and they declare that innocent people must be executed.<verse eid="PSA 94:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 94:22"/>But Yahweh has become like my fortress; my God is like a huge rock on which I am protected.<verse eid="PSA 94:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 94:23"/>He will punish those wicked leaders in return for the things that they have done; he will get rid of them because of the sins that they have committed; yes, Yahweh our God will wipe them out.<verse eid="PSA 94:23"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 94"/>
<chapter number="95" style="c" sid="PSA 95"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 95:1"/>Come, sing to Yahweh; sing joyfully to the one who protects us and saves us!<verse eid="PSA 95:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 95:2"/>We should thank him as we come before him and sing joyful songs as we praise him.<verse eid="PSA 95:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 95:3"/>Because Yahweh is a great God, he is a great king who rules over all other gods.<verse eid="PSA 95:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 95:4"/>He rules over the whole earth from the deepest places to the highest mountains.<verse eid="PSA 95:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 95:5"/>The seas are his because he made them. He is the one who made the dry land.<verse eid="PSA 95:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 95:6"/>We should come, worship, and bow down before him. We should kneel before Yahweh, the one who made us.<verse eid="PSA 95:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 95:7"/>He is our God, and we are the people whom he protects, like sheep that a shepherd takes care of. I desire that today you may hear what Yahweh is saying to you.<verse eid="PSA 95:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 95:8"/>He says, “Do not become stubborn as your ancestors did at Meribah, and as they did at Massah in the wilderness.<verse eid="PSA 95:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 95:9"/>There your ancestors wanted to see if they could do evil things without my punishing them. Even though they had seen me perform many miracles, they tested whether I would continue to be patient with them.<verse eid="PSA 95:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 95:10"/>For forty years I was angry with those people, and I said, ‘Those people are unreliable. They refuse to obey my commands.’<verse eid="PSA 95:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 95:11"/>So because I was very angry; I solemnly said about them, ‘They will never enter the land of Canaan where I would have allowed them to rest!’”<verse eid="PSA 95:11"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 95"/>
<chapter number="96" style="c" sid="PSA 96"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 96:1"/>Sing to Yahweh a new song! You people throughout the earth, sing to Yahweh!<verse eid="PSA 96:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 96:2"/>Sing to Yahweh and praise him! Every day proclaim to others that he has saved us.<verse eid="PSA 96:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 96:3"/>Tell about his glory to all people groups; tell all people groups the marvelous things that he has done.<verse eid="PSA 96:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 96:4"/>Yahweh is great, and he deserves to be praised very much; he should be revered more than all the gods.<verse eid="PSA 96:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 96:5"/>All the gods the other people groups worship are only idols, but Yahweh is truly great; he created the skies!<verse eid="PSA 96:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 96:6"/>God shows his splendor and majesty; they shine out from where he rules. Strength and beauty are in his holy house.<verse eid="PSA 96:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 96:7"/>You people in nations all over the earth, praise Yahweh! Praise Yahweh for his glorious power!<verse eid="PSA 96:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 96:8"/>Praise Yahweh as he deserves to be praised; bring an offering and come to his temple.<verse eid="PSA 96:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 96:9"/>Bow down before Yahweh because his holiness shines out from him with wonderful beauty. Everyone on earth should be very afraid in his presence, because he is good and powerful, completely different than us.<verse eid="PSA 96:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 96:10"/>Say to all the people groups, “Yahweh is the king! He put the world in its place, and nothing will ever be able to move it. He will judge all the people groups fairly.”<verse eid="PSA 96:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 96:11"/>All the beings that are in the heavens should be glad, and all the people on the earth should rejoice. The oceans and all the creatures that are in the oceans should roar to praise Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 96:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 96:12"/>The fields and everything that grows in them should rejoice. When they do that, it will be as though all the trees in the forests are singing joyfully<verse eid="PSA 96:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 96:13"/>in front of Yahweh. That will happen when he comes to judge everyone on the earth. He will judge all the people fairly according to what he knows is true.<verse eid="PSA 96:13"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 96"/>
<chapter number="97" style="c" sid="PSA 97"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 97:1"/>Yahweh is the king! I want everyone on the earth to be glad and the people who live on the islands in the oceans to also rejoice about that!<verse eid="PSA 97:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 97:2"/>There are very dark clouds around him; he rules completely, justly, and fairly.<verse eid="PSA 97:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 97:3"/>He sends fire in front of him, and he completely burns all his enemies in that fire.<verse eid="PSA 97:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 97:4"/>All around the world he sends lightning to flash; people on the earth see it, and it causes them to be afraid and to tremble.<verse eid="PSA 97:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 97:5"/>The mountains melt like wax in front of Yahweh, in front of the one who is the Lord, who rules over all the earth.<verse eid="PSA 97:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 97:6"/>The angels in heaven proclaim that he acts righteously, and all the people groups see his glory.<verse eid="PSA 97:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 97:7"/>Everyone who worships idols should be ashamed; all those who are proud of their false gods should realize that their gods are useless. All those gods will bow down to worship Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 97:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 97:8"/>The people of Jerusalem heard that God is just, and they rejoiced; people in the other cities in Judah also rejoiced because Yahweh judges and punishes wicked people.<verse eid="PSA 97:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 97:9"/>Yahweh is the supreme King over all the earth; he has very great power, and none of the other gods has any power.<verse eid="PSA 97:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 97:10"/>Yahweh loves those who hate what people do that is evil; he protects the lives of his people, and he rescues them when the wicked people try to harm them.<verse eid="PSA 97:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 97:11"/>He makes the righteous people truly live; he causes those who are righteous in their inner beings to rejoice.<verse eid="PSA 97:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 97:12"/>You righteous people, rejoice about what Yahweh has done, and thank him, our holy God!<verse eid="PSA 97:12"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 97"/>
<chapter number="98" style="c" sid="PSA 98"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 98:1"/>A psalm. Sing to Yahweh a new song because he has done wonderful things! By his power he has defeated his enemies.<verse eid="PSA 98:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 98:2"/>Yahweh has declared to people that he has defeated his enemies; he has revealed that he has punished his enemies, and people in all the world have seen that he has done it.<verse eid="PSA 98:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 98:3"/>As he promised to us Israelite people, he has faithfully loved us and been loyal to us. People who live in very remote places in all the earth have seen that our God has defeated his enemies.<verse eid="PSA 98:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 98:4"/>All you people everywhere should sing joyfully to Yahweh; praise him while you sing and shout joyfully!<verse eid="PSA 98:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 98:5"/>Praise Yahweh while you play the lyres, playing delightful music.<verse eid="PSA 98:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 98:6"/>Some of you should blow trumpets and other horns while others shout joyfully to Yahweh, our king.<verse eid="PSA 98:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 98:7"/>The oceans and all the creatures that are in the oceans should roar to praise Yahweh. Everyone on the earth should sing!<verse eid="PSA 98:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 98:8"/>It should seem as though the rivers were clapping their hands to praise Yahweh and that the hills were singing together joyfully in front of Yahweh<verse eid="PSA 98:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 98:9"/>because he will come to judge everyone on the earth! He will judge all the people groups in the world justly and fairly.<verse eid="PSA 98:9"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 98"/>
<chapter number="99" style="c" sid="PSA 99"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 99:1"/>Yahweh is the supreme king, so all the people groups should tremble in his presence! He sits on his throne in the temple above the statues of winged creatures, so the earth should quake!<verse eid="PSA 99:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 99:2"/>Yahweh is a mighty king in Jerusalem; he is also the supreme ruler of all the people groups.<verse eid="PSA 99:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 99:3"/>They should praise him because he is very great; he is holy!<verse eid="PSA 99:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 99:4"/>He is a mighty king who loves what is just; he has acted justly and fairly in Israel.<verse eid="PSA 99:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 99:5"/>Praise Yahweh, our God! Worship him in front of his footstool, the sacred chest in his temple, where he rules people. He is holy!<verse eid="PSA 99:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 99:6"/>Moses and Aaron were two of his priests; Samuel also was someone who prayed to him. Those three cried out to Yahweh to help them, and he answered them.<verse eid="PSA 99:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 99:7"/>He spoke to Moses and Aaron from the cloud that was like a huge pillar; they obeyed all the laws and commandments that he gave to them.<verse eid="PSA 99:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 99:8"/>Yahweh, our God, you answered your people when they cried out to you to help them; you are a God who forgave them for the sins that they had committed, even though you punished them for the things that they did that were wrong.<verse eid="PSA 99:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 99:9"/>Praise Yahweh, our God, and worship him at the temple on his sacred hill; it is right to do that because Yahweh, our God, is holy!<verse eid="PSA 99:9"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 99"/>
<chapter number="100" style="c" sid="PSA 100"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 100:1"/>A psalm of thanksgiving; Everyone in the world should shout joyfully to Yahweh!<verse eid="PSA 100:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 100:2"/>We should worship Yahweh gladly! We should come before him singing joyful songs.<verse eid="PSA 100:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 100:3"/>We should acknowledge that Yahweh is God; it is he who made us, and so we belong to him. We are the people that he takes care of; we are like sheep that their shepherd cares for.<verse eid="PSA 100:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 100:4"/>Enter the gates of his temple thanking him; enter the courtyard of the temple singing songs to praise him! Thank him and praise him<verse eid="PSA 100:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 100:5"/>because Yahweh always does good things for us. He faithfully loves us as he promised us, and he is faithful.<verse eid="PSA 100:5"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 100"/>
<chapter number="101" style="c" sid="PSA 101"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 101:1"/>A psalm written by David; Yahweh, I will sing to you! I will sing about your faithful and just loyalty to us.<verse eid="PSA 101:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 101:2"/>I promise that while I rule people, I will behave in such a way that no one will be able to criticize me. Yahweh, when will you come to help me? I will do things that are right.<verse eid="PSA 101:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 101:3"/>I will not allow anyone who does what is evil to come to me. I hate the deeds of those who turn away from you; I will completely avoid those people.<verse eid="PSA 101:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 101:4"/>I will not be dishonest, and I will not have anything to do with evil.<verse eid="PSA 101:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 101:5"/>I will get rid of anyone who secretly slanders someone else, and I will not let anyone near me who is proud and arrogant.<verse eid="PSA 101:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 101:6"/>I will approve of people in this land who are loyal to God, and I will allow them to live with me. I will allow to serve me those who behave in such a way that no one can criticize them.<verse eid="PSA 101:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 101:7"/>I will not allow anyone who deceives others to work in my palace, and no one who tells lies will be allowed to continually come to work for me.<verse eid="PSA 101:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 101:8"/>Every day I will try to get rid of all the wicked people in this land; I will expel them from this city, which is Yahweh’s city.<verse eid="PSA 101:8"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 101"/>
<chapter number="102" style="c" sid="PSA 102"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 102:1"/>A prayer written by someone who was afflicted, when he was discouraged and pleaded for Yahweh to help. Yahweh, listen to what I am praying; hear me while I cry out to you!<verse eid="PSA 102:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 102:2"/>Do not turn away! Listen to me, and answer me quickly now when I am calling out to you!<verse eid="PSA 102:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 102:3"/>My life is ending like smoke that disappears; I have a big fever which burns my body as a fire burns.<verse eid="PSA 102:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 102:4"/>I feel as though I am drying up like grass that has been mown, and I do not even think about eating any food.<verse eid="PSA 102:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 102:5"/>I groan loudly, and my bones can be seen under my skin because I have become very thin.<verse eid="PSA 102:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 102:6"/>I am like a lonely and despised vulture in the desert, like an owl by itself in the abandoned ruins of a building.<verse eid="PSA 102:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 102:7"/>I lie awake at night; because there is no one to comfort me, I am like a lonely bird sitting on a housetop.<verse eid="PSA 102:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 102:8"/>All during each day my enemies insult me; those who make fun of me mention my name and say, “May you be like him” when they curse people.<verse eid="PSA 102:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 102:9"/>(9-10) Because you are very angry with me, I sit in ashes while I am suffering greatly; those ashes fall on the bread that I eat, and what I drink has my tears mixed with it. It is as though you have picked me up and thrown me away!<verse eid="PSA 102:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 102:11"/>My time to remain alive is short like an evening shadow that will soon be gone. I am withering as grass withers in the hot sun.<verse eid="PSA 102:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 102:12"/>But Yahweh, you are our king who rules forever; people who are not yet born will remember you.<verse eid="PSA 102:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 102:13"/>You will arise and act mercifully toward the people of Jerusalem; it is now time for you to do that; this is the time for you to be kind to them.<verse eid="PSA 102:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 102:14"/>Even though the city has been destroyed, we who serve you still love the stones that were formerly in the city walls; because now there is rubble everywhere, we, your people, are very sad when we see it.<verse eid="PSA 102:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 102:15"/>Yahweh, someday the people of other nations will have an awesome respect for you; all the kings on the earth will see that you are very glorious.<verse eid="PSA 102:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 102:16"/>You will rebuild Jerusalem, and you will appear there with your glory.<verse eid="PSA 102:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 102:17"/>You will listen to the prayers of your people who are homeless, and you will not ignore them when they plead with you to help them.<verse eid="PSA 102:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 102:18"/>Yahweh, I want to write these words so that people in future years will know what you have done, in order that people who are not born yet will praise you.<verse eid="PSA 102:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 102:19"/>They will know that you looked down from your own place in heaven and saw what was happening on the earth.<verse eid="PSA 102:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 102:20"/>They will know that you hear prisoners groaning and that you will set free those who have been told, “You will be executed.”<verse eid="PSA 102:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 102:21"/>As a result, people in Jerusalem will praise you for what you have done.<verse eid="PSA 102:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 102:22"/>Many people from other people groups and those who are citizens of other kingdoms will gather to worship you.<verse eid="PSA 102:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 102:23"/>But now you have caused me to become weak while I am still young; I think that I will not remain alive very long.<verse eid="PSA 102:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 102:24"/>I say to you, “My God, do not take me away from the earth now before I become old! You, on the other hand, live forever!<verse eid="PSA 102:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 102:25"/>You created the world long ago, and you made the heavens with your own hands.<verse eid="PSA 102:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 102:26"/>The earth and the heavens will disappear, but you will remain. They will wear out as clothes wear out. You will get rid of them as people get rid of old clothes, and they will no longer exist.<verse eid="PSA 102:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 102:27"/>But you are not like the things that you created because you are always the same; you never die.<verse eid="PSA 102:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 102:28"/>Someday our children will live safely in Jerusalem, and their descendants will be protected as they live in your presence.”<verse eid="PSA 102:28"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 102"/>
<chapter number="103" style="c" sid="PSA 103"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 103:1"/>A psalm written by David. I tell myself that I should praise Yahweh. I will praise him because he is holy.<verse eid="PSA 103:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 103:2"/>I tell myself that I should praise Yahweh and never forget all the kind things he has done for me.<verse eid="PSA 103:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 103:3"/>He forgives all my sins, and he heals me from all my diseases;<verse eid="PSA 103:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 103:4"/>he keeps me from dying, and he blesses me by faithfully loving me and acting mercifully to me as he promised to do.<verse eid="PSA 103:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 103:5"/>He gives me good things during my entire life. He makes me feel young and strong like eagles.<verse eid="PSA 103:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 103:6"/>Yahweh judges justly all those who have been treated unfairly.<verse eid="PSA 103:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 103:7"/>Long ago he revealed to Moses what he planned to do; he showed to the ancestors of us Israelites the mighty things that he was able to do.<verse eid="PSA 103:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 103:8"/>Yahweh acts mercifully and kindly; he does not quickly get angry when we sin; he is always showing us that he faithfully loves us.<verse eid="PSA 103:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 103:9"/>He will not keep rebuking us, and he will not remain angry forever.<verse eid="PSA 103:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 103:10"/>He has not punished us for our sins as we deserved.<verse eid="PSA 103:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 103:11"/>The skies are very high above the earth, and Yahweh’s faithful love for all those who revere him is just as great.<verse eid="PSA 103:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 103:12"/>He has taken away the guilt for our sins and put it as far from us as the east is from the west.<verse eid="PSA 103:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 103:13"/>Just as parents act mercifully toward their children, Yahweh is kind to those who revere him.<verse eid="PSA 103:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 103:14"/>He knows what our bodies are like; he remembers that he created us from dust and that we therefore quickly fail to do what pleases him .<verse eid="PSA 103:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 103:15"/>We humans do not live forever; we are like grass which withers and dies. We are like wild flowers that bloom for a short while;<verse eid="PSA 103:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 103:16"/>but then the hot wind blows over them, and they disappear; no one sees them again.<verse eid="PSA 103:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 103:17"/>But Yahweh will faithfully keep loving forever all those who revere him, as he promised. He will act fairly to our children and to their children;<verse eid="PSA 103:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 103:18"/>he will act that way to all those who obey the covenant he made with them to bless them if they did what he told them to do, to all those who obey what he has commanded.<verse eid="PSA 103:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 103:19"/>Yahweh has taken his seat in the heavens where he rules as king; from there he rules over everything.<verse eid="PSA 103:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 103:20"/>You angels who belong to Yahweh, praise him! You are powerful creatures who do what he tells you to do; you obey what he commands.<verse eid="PSA 103:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 103:21"/>Praise Yahweh, you armies of angels who serve him and do what he desires.<verse eid="PSA 103:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 103:22"/>All you things that Yahweh has created, praise him; praise him in every place where he rules, everywhere! I also will praise Yahweh!<verse eid="PSA 103:22"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 103"/>
<chapter number="104" style="c" sid="PSA 104"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 104:1"/>I tell myself that I should praise Yahweh. Yahweh, my God, you are very great! As a king has on his royal robes, you have honor and majesty all around you!<verse eid="PSA 104:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 104:2"/>You created light and you hide behind it. You spread out the whole sky as someone sets up a tent.<verse eid="PSA 104:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 104:3"/>You built your palace on the clouds. You made the clouds to be like chariots to carry you.<verse eid="PSA 104:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 104:4"/>You caused the winds to be like your messengers, and flames of fire to be like your servants.<verse eid="PSA 104:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 104:5"/>You placed the world firmly on its foundation so that it can never be moved.<verse eid="PSA 104:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 104:6"/>Later, you covered the earth with a flood, like a blanket; and the water covered the mountains.<verse eid="PSA 104:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 104:7"/>But when you rebuked the water, the oceans receded; your voice spoke like thunder, and then the waters rushed away.<verse eid="PSA 104:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 104:8"/>Mountains rose up from the water, and the valleys sank down to the levels that you had determined for them.<verse eid="PSA 104:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 104:9"/>Then you set a boundary for the oceans, a boundary that they cannot cross; their water will never again cover the whole earth.<verse eid="PSA 104:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 104:10"/>You make springs to pour water into ravines; their water flows down between the mountains.<verse eid="PSA 104:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 104:11"/>Those streams provide water for all the animals to drink; the wild donkeys drink the water and are no longer thirsty.<verse eid="PSA 104:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 104:12"/>Birds make their nests alongside the streams, and they sing among the branches of the trees.<verse eid="PSA 104:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 104:13"/>From the heavens you send rain down on the mountains, and you fill the earth with many good things that you create.<verse eid="PSA 104:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 104:14"/>You make grass to grow for the cattle to eat, and you make plants to grow for people. In that way, animals and people get their food from what grows in the soil.<verse eid="PSA 104:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 104:15"/>We get grapes to make wine to drink and to make us cheerful; we get olives to make our face shine, and we get grain to make bread to give us strength.<verse eid="PSA 104:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 104:16"/>Yahweh, you send plenty of rain to water your trees, the cedar trees that you planted in Lebanon.<verse eid="PSA 104:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 104:17"/>Birds make their nests in those trees, and storks make their nests in pine trees.<verse eid="PSA 104:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 104:18"/>High up in the mountains the wild goats live, and hyraxes live in the rocks.<verse eid="PSA 104:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 104:19"/>Yahweh, you made the moon to indicate the times for our festivals, and you made the sun that knows when to go down.<verse eid="PSA 104:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 104:20"/>You bring darkness, and it becomes night when all the animals in the forest prowl around looking for food.<verse eid="PSA 104:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 104:21"/>At night the young lions roar as they seek their prey, but they depend on you to give them food.<verse eid="PSA 104:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 104:22"/>At dawn, they go back to their dens and lie down.<verse eid="PSA 104:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 104:23"/>During the daytime, people go to their work; they work until it is evening.<verse eid="PSA 104:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 104:24"/>Yahweh, you have made so many different kinds of things! You were very wise as you made them all. The earth is full of the creatures that you made.<verse eid="PSA 104:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 104:25"/>We see the ocean which is very vast! It is full of many kinds of living creatures, big ones and little ones.<verse eid="PSA 104:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 104:26"/>We see the ships which sail along! We see the huge sea monster which you made to splash around in the sea.<verse eid="PSA 104:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 104:27"/>All of these creatures depend on you to give them the food that they need.<verse eid="PSA 104:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 104:28"/>When you give them the food that they need, they gather it. You give them what you have in your hand, and they eat it and are satisfied.<verse eid="PSA 104:28"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="29" style="v" sid="PSA 104:29"/>But if you refuse to give food to them, they become terrified. When you cause them to stop breathing, they die; their bodies decay and become soil again.<verse eid="PSA 104:29"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="30" style="v" sid="PSA 104:30"/>When you cause newborn creatures to begin to breathe, they start to live; You give new life to all the living creatures on the earth.<verse eid="PSA 104:30"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="31" style="v" sid="PSA 104:31"/>May the glory of Yahweh last forever. May he rejoice about all the things that he has created.<verse eid="PSA 104:31"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="32" style="v" sid="PSA 104:32"/>He makes the earth shake just by looking at it! By merely touching the mountains he makes them pour out fire and smoke!<verse eid="PSA 104:32"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="33" style="v" sid="PSA 104:33"/>I will sing to Yahweh as long as I live. I will praise my God until the day that I die.<verse eid="PSA 104:33"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="34" style="v" sid="PSA 104:34"/>May Yahweh be pleased by all these things that I have thought about him because I rejoice about knowing him.<verse eid="PSA 104:34"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="35" style="v" sid="PSA 104:35"/>However, may sinners disappear from the earth; may there be no more wicked people! But as for me, I will praise Yahweh! Praise him!<verse eid="PSA 104:35"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 104"/>
<chapter number="105" style="c" sid="PSA 105"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 105:1"/>Give thanks to Yahweh; worship him and pray to him. Tell everyone in the world what he has done!<verse eid="PSA 105:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 105:2"/>Sing to him; praise him as you sing to him; tell others about his wonderful miracles.<verse eid="PSA 105:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 105:3"/>Be proud of Yahweh, who alone is God. You people who worship Yahweh, rejoice!<verse eid="PSA 105:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 105:4"/>Ask Yahweh to help you and give you his strength, and always seek to be with him!<verse eid="PSA 105:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 105:5"/>(5-6) You people who are descendants of God’s servant Abraham, you descendants of Jacob, the people whom God has chosen, think about all the wonderful things that he has done; he performed miracles, and he punished all our enemies.<verse eid="PSA 105:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 105:7"/>He is Yahweh, our God. He rules and judges people throughout the earth.<verse eid="PSA 105:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 105:8"/>He never forgets the covenant that he made; he made a promise that will last for a thousand generations.<verse eid="PSA 105:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 105:9"/>That is the covenant that he made with Abraham, and he repeated that covenant with Isaac.<verse eid="PSA 105:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 105:10"/>Later he confirmed it again to Jacob as a covenant for the Israelite people that would last forever.<verse eid="PSA 105:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 105:11"/>What he said was, “I will give you the region of Canaan; it will belong to you and your descendants forever.”<verse eid="PSA 105:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 105:12"/>He said that to them when there were only a few of them, a tiny group of people who were living in that land like strangers.<verse eid="PSA 105:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 105:13"/>They continued to wander from one place to another, from one kingdom to another.<verse eid="PSA 105:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 105:14"/>But he did not allow others to oppress them. He warned those kings by saying to them,<verse eid="PSA 105:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 105:15"/>“Do not do harm to the people whom I have chosen! Do not harm my prophets!”<verse eid="PSA 105:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 105:16"/>He sent a famine to Canaan, and as a result all the people had no food to eat.<verse eid="PSA 105:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 105:17"/>So his people went to Egypt, but first he sent someone there. He sent Joseph, who had been sold to be a slave.<verse eid="PSA 105:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 105:18"/>Later, while Joseph was in prison in Egypt, they put his legs in shackles that hurt his feet, and they put an iron collar around his neck.<verse eid="PSA 105:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 105:19"/>Joseph was in prison until the time the events he predicted came to pass. This was how Yahweh tested Joseph.<verse eid="PSA 105:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 105:20"/>The king of Egypt sent servants, who set him free; this ruler released Joseph from prison.<verse eid="PSA 105:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 105:21"/>Then he appointed him to take care of everything in the king’s household, to take care of everything that the king possessed.<verse eid="PSA 105:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 105:22"/>Joseph was permitted to command the king’s important servants to do anything that Joseph wanted them to do, and even to tell the king’s advisors the things that they should do for the people of Egypt.<verse eid="PSA 105:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 105:23"/>Later, Joseph’s father Jacob arrived in Egypt. He lived like a foreigner in the land that belonged to the descendants of Ham.<verse eid="PSA 105:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 105:24"/>Years later Yahweh caused the descendants of Jacob to become very numerous. As a result, their enemies, the Egyptians, considered that the Israelites were too strong.<verse eid="PSA 105:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 105:25"/>So Yahweh caused the rulers of Egypt to turn against the Israelite people, and they began to oppress his people.<verse eid="PSA 105:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 105:26"/>But then Yahweh sent his servant Moses along with Moses’ older brother Aaron, whom Yahweh had also chosen to be his servant.<verse eid="PSA 105:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 105:27"/>Those two performed amazing miracles among the people of Egypt in that land where the descendants of Ham lived.<verse eid="PSA 105:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 105:28"/>Yahweh sent darkness so that the people of Egypt could not see anything, but the rulers of Egypt refused to obey when Moses and Aaron commanded them to let the Israelite people leave Egypt.<verse eid="PSA 105:28"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="29" style="v" sid="PSA 105:29"/>Yahweh caused all the water in Egypt to become blood, and his doing that caused all the fish to die.<verse eid="PSA 105:29"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="30" style="v" sid="PSA 105:30"/>Then he caused the land to become full of frogs; the king and his officials even had frogs in their bedrooms.<verse eid="PSA 105:30"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="31" style="v" sid="PSA 105:31"/>Then Yahweh commanded that flies come, and swarms of them descended on the people of Egypt, and gnats also swarmed across the whole country.<verse eid="PSA 105:31"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="32" style="v" sid="PSA 105:32"/>Yahweh sent rain, rain that became hail that fell upon them, and he sent wild fires that burned throughout their land.<verse eid="PSA 105:32"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="33" style="v" sid="PSA 105:33"/>The hail ruined their grapevines and fig trees and shattered all the other trees.<verse eid="PSA 105:33"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="34" style="v" sid="PSA 105:34"/>He commanded locusts to come, and hordes of them came; so many came that they could not be counted.<verse eid="PSA 105:34"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="35" style="v" sid="PSA 105:35"/>The locusts ate every green plant in the land, ruining all the crops.<verse eid="PSA 105:35"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="36" style="v" sid="PSA 105:36"/>Then Yahweh killed the oldest son in every house of the people of Egypt.<verse eid="PSA 105:36"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="37" style="v" sid="PSA 105:37"/>Then he brought the Israelite people out from Egypt; they were carrying heavy loads of jewelry made of silver and gold that the people of Egypt had given to them. No one was left behind because of being sick.<verse eid="PSA 105:37"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="38" style="v" sid="PSA 105:38"/>The people of Egypt were glad when the Israelite people left because they had become very afraid of the Israelites.<verse eid="PSA 105:38"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="39" style="v" sid="PSA 105:39"/>Then Yahweh spread a cloud to cover the Israelites; and at night it became a big fire in the sky to give them light.<verse eid="PSA 105:39"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="40" style="v" sid="PSA 105:40"/>Later the Israelites asked for meat to eat, and Yahweh sent flocks of quail to them, and he gave them plenty of manna, food from the sky, each morning.<verse eid="PSA 105:40"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="41" style="v" sid="PSA 105:41"/>One day he caused a rock to open up, and water poured out for them to drink; it was like a river flowing in that desert.<verse eid="PSA 105:41"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="42" style="v" sid="PSA 105:42"/>He did that because he kept thinking about the sacred promise that he had given to his servant, Abraham.<verse eid="PSA 105:42"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="43" style="v" sid="PSA 105:43"/>So his people were joyful as he brought them out from Egypt; these people whom he had chosen were shouting joyfully as they went.<verse eid="PSA 105:43"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="44" style="v" sid="PSA 105:44"/>He gave to them the land that belonged to the people groups that lived there in Canaan, and the Israelites took all their wealth.<verse eid="PSA 105:44"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="45" style="v" sid="PSA 105:45"/>Yahweh did all these things so that his people would do all the things that he had commanded them to do. Praise Yahweh!<verse eid="PSA 105:45"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 105"/>
<chapter number="106" style="c" sid="PSA 106"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 106:1"/>Praise Yahweh! Praise Yahweh because everything he does is good; he faithfully loves us forever as he promised us!<verse eid="PSA 106:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 106:2"/>Because Yahweh has done many great things, no one can tell all the great things that Yahweh has done, and no one can praise him enough.<verse eid="PSA 106:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 106:3"/>How fortunate are those who act fairly, those who always do what is right.<verse eid="PSA 106:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 106:4"/>Yahweh, be kind to me when you help your people; help me when you rescue them.<verse eid="PSA 106:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 106:5"/>Allow me to see your people become prosperous again and to see all the people of your nation, Israel, become happy again; allow me to be happy with them! I want to praise you along with all those others who belong to you.<verse eid="PSA 106:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 106:6"/>We and our ancestors have sinned; we have done what is wicked and evil.<verse eid="PSA 106:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 106:7"/>When our ancestors were in Egypt, they did not pay attention to the wonderful things that Yahweh did; they forgot about the many times that he showed that he faithfully loved them. Instead, when they were at the Sea of Reeds, they rebelled against God, who is greater than any other god.<verse eid="PSA 106:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 106:8"/>But he rescued them for the sake of his own reputation so that he could show that he is very powerful.<verse eid="PSA 106:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 106:9"/>He rebuked the Sea of Reeds and it became dry, and then while he led our ancestors, they walked through it as though it were as dry as a desert.<verse eid="PSA 106:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 106:10"/>In that way he rescued them from the power of their enemies.<verse eid="PSA 106:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 106:11"/>Then their enemies were drowned in the water of the Sea of Reeds; not one of them was left.<verse eid="PSA 106:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 106:12"/>When that happened, our ancestors believed that Yahweh had truly done for them what he had promised to do, and they sang to praise him.<verse eid="PSA 106:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 106:13"/>But they soon forgot what he had done for them; they did things without waiting to find out what Yahweh wanted them to do.<verse eid="PSA 106:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 106:14"/>They intensely wanted food like they formerly ate in Egypt. They did evil things to find out whether God would punish them or not.<verse eid="PSA 106:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 106:15"/>So he gave them what they requested, but he sent a horrible disease upon them.<verse eid="PSA 106:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 106:16"/>Later when some of the men became jealous of Moses and his older brother Aaron, who was dedicated to serve Yahweh by being a priest,<verse eid="PSA 106:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 106:17"/>the ground opened up and swallowed Dathan and also buried Abiram and his family.<verse eid="PSA 106:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 106:18"/>God sent down from heaven a fire which burned up all the wicked people who supported them.<verse eid="PSA 106:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 106:19"/>Then the Israelite leaders made a gold statue of a calf at Mount Sinai and worshiped it.<verse eid="PSA 106:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 106:20"/>Instead of worshiping our glorious God, they started to worship a statue of an ox that eats grass!<verse eid="PSA 106:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 106:21"/>They forgot about God, who had rescued them by the great miracles that he performed in Egypt.<verse eid="PSA 106:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 106:22"/>They forgot about the wonderful things that he did for them in Egypt and the amazing things that he did for them at the Sea of Reeds.<verse eid="PSA 106:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 106:23"/>Because of that, God said that he would get rid of the Israelites; but Moses, whom God had chosen to serve him, stood up to persuade God not to do that. As a result, God did not destroy them.<verse eid="PSA 106:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 106:24"/>Later, our ancestors refused to enter the beautiful land of Canaan because they did not believe that God would do as he promised and would enable them to take the land from the people who were living there.<verse eid="PSA 106:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 106:25"/>They stayed in their tents and grumbled and would not pay attention to what Yahweh said that they should do.<verse eid="PSA 106:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 106:26"/>So he solemnly told them that he would cause them to die there in the wilderness,<verse eid="PSA 106:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 106:27"/>that he would scatter their descendants among the people of other nations and groups who did not believe in him, and that he would allow them to die in those lands.<verse eid="PSA 106:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 106:28"/>Later the Israelite people started to worship the idol of Baal at Mount Peor, and they ate meat that had been sacrificed to Baal and those other lifeless gods.<verse eid="PSA 106:28"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="29" style="v" sid="PSA 106:29"/>Yahweh became very angry because of what they had done, so again he sent a terrible disease to attack them.<verse eid="PSA 106:29"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="30" style="v" sid="PSA 106:30"/>But Phinehas stood up and punished the ones who had sinned greatly, and as a result the plague ended.<verse eid="PSA 106:30"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="31" style="v" sid="PSA 106:31"/>People have remembered that righteous deed that Phinehas did, and in future years people will remember it.<verse eid="PSA 106:31"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="32" style="v" sid="PSA 106:32"/>Then at the springs of Meribah our ancestors caused Yahweh to become angry again, and as a result Moses had trouble.<verse eid="PSA 106:32"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="33" style="v" sid="PSA 106:33"/>They caused Moses to become very angry, and he said things that were foolish.<verse eid="PSA 106:33"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="34" style="v" sid="PSA 106:34"/>Our ancestors did not destroy the other people groups as he told them to do.<verse eid="PSA 106:34"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="35" style="v" sid="PSA 106:35"/>Instead, the men took women from those people groups, and they started to do the evil things that those people did.<verse eid="PSA 106:35"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="36" style="v" sid="PSA 106:36"/>Our ancestors worshiped the idols of those people, which resulted in their being destroyed.<verse eid="PSA 106:36"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="37" style="v" sid="PSA 106:37"/>Some of the Israelites sacrificed their sons and daughters to the demons that those idols represented.<verse eid="PSA 106:37"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="38" style="v" sid="PSA 106:38"/>They killed children who had done nothing wrong, and offered them as sacrifices to the idols in Canaan. As a result, the land of Canaan was polluted by those murders.<verse eid="PSA 106:38"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="39" style="v" sid="PSA 106:39"/>So by their deeds they made it impossible for God to accept them; because they did not faithfully worship only God, they became like women who sleep with other men instead of sleeping only with their husbands.<verse eid="PSA 106:39"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="40" style="v" sid="PSA 106:40"/>So Yahweh became very angry with his people; he was completely disgusted with them.<verse eid="PSA 106:40"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="41" style="v" sid="PSA 106:41"/>As a result, he allowed people groups who did not believe in him to conquer them, so those who hated our ancestors started to rule over them.<verse eid="PSA 106:41"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="42" style="v" sid="PSA 106:42"/>Their enemies oppressed them and completely controlled them.<verse eid="PSA 106:42"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="43" style="v" sid="PSA 106:43"/>Many times Yahweh rescued his people, but they continued to rebel against him, and they were finally destroyed because of the sins that they committed.<verse eid="PSA 106:43"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="44" style="v" sid="PSA 106:44"/>However, Yahweh always heard them when they cried out to him, and he listened to them when they were distressed.<verse eid="PSA 106:44"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="45" style="v" sid="PSA 106:45"/>For their sake, he thought about the covenant that he had made to bless them; because he never stopped loving them very much, he changed his mind about punishing them more.<verse eid="PSA 106:45"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="46" style="v" sid="PSA 106:46"/>He caused all those who had taken the Israelites to Babylonia to feel sorry for them.<verse eid="PSA 106:46"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="47" style="v" sid="PSA 106:47"/>Yahweh our God, rescue us and bring us back to Israel from among those people groups so that we may thank you and joyfully praise you.<verse eid="PSA 106:47"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="48" style="v" sid="PSA 106:48"/>Praise Yahweh, the God whom we Israelites worship, praise him now and forever! All the people should agree! Praise Yahweh!<verse eid="PSA 106:48"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 106"/>
<chapter number="107" style="c" sid="PSA 107"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 107:1"/>Give thanks to Yahweh because he always does good things for us! His faithful love for us lasts forever, as he has promised us!<verse eid="PSA 107:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 107:2"/>Those whom Yahweh has saved should tell others that he has rescued them from their enemies.<verse eid="PSA 107:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 107:3"/>He has gathered those of you who were exiled to many lands; he has gathered you together from the east and the west, from the north and from the south.<verse eid="PSA 107:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 107:4"/>Some of those who returned from those countries wandered in the desert; they were lost and had no homes to live in.<verse eid="PSA 107:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 107:5"/>They were hungry and thirsty, and they even collapsed in exhaustion.<verse eid="PSA 107:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 107:6"/>When they were in trouble, they called out to Yahweh, and he rescued them from being distressed.<verse eid="PSA 107:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 107:7"/>He led them along a straight road where they walked safely to cities in Canaan where they could live.<verse eid="PSA 107:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 107:8"/>They should praise Yahweh for loving them faithfully and for the wonderful things that he does for people.<verse eid="PSA 107:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 107:9"/>He gives thirsty people plenty of water to drink, and he gives hungry people plenty of good things to eat.<verse eid="PSA 107:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 107:10"/>Some of them were in very dark prisons; they were prisoners, suffering because of chains fastened to their hands and feet.<verse eid="PSA 107:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 107:11"/>They were in prison because they had rebelled against the message of God; they were there because they had despised the advice given by God, who is greater than all other gods.<verse eid="PSA 107:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 107:12"/>That is why God made them suffer hardships so that they would no longer be proud; when they got into trouble, there was no one who would help them.<verse eid="PSA 107:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 107:13"/>When they were in trouble, they called out to Yahweh, and he rescued them from being distressed.<verse eid="PSA 107:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 107:14"/>He broke the chains that were on their hands and feet and brought them out of those very dark prisons.<verse eid="PSA 107:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 107:15"/>(15-16) He broke down the prison gates that were made of bronze; he cut through the prison bars that were made of iron. They should praise Yahweh for loving them faithfully and for the wonderful things that he does for people.<verse eid="PSA 107:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 107:17"/>Some of them foolishly rebelled against God, so they suffered for their sins.<verse eid="PSA 107:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 107:18"/>They did not want to eat any food, and they almost died.<verse eid="PSA 107:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 107:19"/>When they were in trouble, they called out to Yahweh, and he rescued them from being distressed.<verse eid="PSA 107:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 107:20"/>When he commanded that they be healed, they were healed; he saved them from dying.<verse eid="PSA 107:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 107:21"/>They should praise Yahweh for loving them faithfully and for the wonderful things that he does for people.<verse eid="PSA 107:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 107:22"/>They should give offerings to him to show that they are thankful, and they should sing joyfully about the miracles that he has performed.<verse eid="PSA 107:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 107:23"/>Some of them sailed in ships; they were selling things in cities far away.<verse eid="PSA 107:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 107:24"/>As they were sailing, they also saw the miracles that Yahweh performed, the wonderful things that he did when they were on very deep seas.<verse eid="PSA 107:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 107:25"/>He gave orders to the winds, and they became strong and stirred up high waves.<verse eid="PSA 107:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 107:26"/>The ships in which they were sailing were tossed high in the air, and then they sank into the troughs between the high waves; then the sailors were terrified at the danger.<verse eid="PSA 107:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 107:27"/>They stumbled about and staggered like drunken men, and they did not know what to do.<verse eid="PSA 107:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 107:28"/>When they were in trouble, they called out to Yahweh, and he rescued them from being distressed.<verse eid="PSA 107:28"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="29" style="v" sid="PSA 107:29"/>He calmed the storm and he stilled the waves.<verse eid="PSA 107:29"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="30" style="v" sid="PSA 107:30"/>They were very glad when it became calm; and Yahweh brought them safely into a harbor as they wished.<verse eid="PSA 107:30"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="31" style="v" sid="PSA 107:31"/>They should praise Yahweh for loving them faithfully and for the wonderful things that he does for people.<verse eid="PSA 107:31"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="32" style="v" sid="PSA 107:32"/>They should praise him among the Israelite people when they have gathered together, and they should praise him in front of the leaders of the country.<verse eid="PSA 107:32"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="33" style="v" sid="PSA 107:33"/>Sometimes Yahweh causes rivers to become dry, with the result that the land becomes a wilderness, and springs of water become dry land.<verse eid="PSA 107:33"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="34" style="v" sid="PSA 107:34"/>Sometimes he causes land that has produced lots of crops to become salty wastelands, with the result that they do not produce crops. He does that because the people who live there are very wicked.<verse eid="PSA 107:34"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="35" style="v" sid="PSA 107:35"/>But sometimes he causes pools of water to appear in deserts, and he causes springs to flow in very dry ground.<verse eid="PSA 107:35"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="36" style="v" sid="PSA 107:36"/>He brings hungry people into that land, to live there and to build cities there.<verse eid="PSA 107:36"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="37" style="v" sid="PSA 107:37"/>They plant seeds in their fields, and they plant grapevines that produce large crops of grapes.<verse eid="PSA 107:37"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="38" style="v" sid="PSA 107:38"/>He blesses the people, and the women give birth to many children, and they have large herds of cattle.<verse eid="PSA 107:38"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="39" style="v" sid="PSA 107:39"/>When the number of people became smaller and they were humiliated by their enemies by being oppressed and caused to suffer,<verse eid="PSA 107:39"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="40" style="v" sid="PSA 107:40"/>Yahweh shows contempt for the leaders who oppress them, and makes them to wander in a wilderness where there are no roads.<verse eid="PSA 107:40"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="41" style="v" sid="PSA 107:41"/>But he rescues poor people from being in misery and causes their families to increase in number like flocks of sheep.<verse eid="PSA 107:41"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="42" style="v" sid="PSA 107:42"/>People who live rightly see God do these things, and they rejoice; wicked people hear about these things, too, but they have nothing to say against Yahweh in reply.<verse eid="PSA 107:42"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="43" style="v" sid="PSA 107:43"/>Those who are wise should think carefully about these things; they should consider all the things that Yahweh has done to show that he faithfully loves them.<verse eid="PSA 107:43"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 107"/>
<chapter number="108" style="c" sid="PSA 108"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 108:1"/>A psalm written by David; God, I am very confident in you. I will sing to praise you. It is an honor to wake up and praise you.<verse eid="PSA 108:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 108:2"/>I will arise before the sun rises, and I will praise you while I play my harp and my lyre.<verse eid="PSA 108:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 108:3"/>I prayed, “Yahweh, I will thank you among all the people groups; I will sing to praise you among the nations<verse eid="PSA 108:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 108:4"/>because your faithful love for us reaches up to the heavens, and you are as faithful in keeping your promises as the clouds are high above the earth.<verse eid="PSA 108:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 108:5"/>Yahweh, show in the heavens that you are very great! Show your glory to people all over the earth!<verse eid="PSA 108:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 108:6"/>Answer our prayers and, by your power help us to defeat our enemies so that we, the people whom you love, may be saved.”<verse eid="PSA 108:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 108:7"/>Yahweh answered our prayers and spoke from his temple, saying, “Because I have conquered your enemies, I will joyfully divide the city of Shechem, and I will distribute among my people the land in the Valley of Succoth.<verse eid="PSA 108:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 108:8"/>The region of Gilead is mine; the people of the tribe of Manasseh are mine; and the tribe of Judah is like my scepter.<verse eid="PSA 108:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 108:9"/>The region of Moab is like my washbasin; I throw my sandal over the region of Edom to show that it belongs to me; I shout triumphantly because I have defeated the people of the region of Philistia.”<verse eid="PSA 108:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 108:10"/>Because we want to attack the people of Edom, who will lead my army to their capital city that has strong walls around it?<verse eid="PSA 108:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 108:11"/>God, we do not want you to abandon us; we want you to go with us when our army marches out to fight our enemies.<verse eid="PSA 108:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 108:12"/>We need you to help us when we fight against our enemies because the help that humans can give us is worthless.<verse eid="PSA 108:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 108:13"/>But with you helping us, we shall win; you will enable us to defeat our enemies.<verse eid="PSA 108:13"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 108"/>
<chapter number="109" style="c" sid="PSA 109"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 109:1"/>A psalm written by David for the choir director. God, you are the one whom I praise, so please answer my prayer<verse eid="PSA 109:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 109:2"/>because wicked people slander me and tell lies about me.<verse eid="PSA 109:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 109:3"/>They are constantly saying that they hate me, and they harm me for no reason.<verse eid="PSA 109:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 109:4"/>I show them that I love them and that I pray for them, but instead of being kind to me, they say that I have done evil things.<verse eid="PSA 109:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 109:5"/>In return for my doing good things for them and loving them, they do evil things to me and hate me.<verse eid="PSA 109:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 109:6"/>So appoint a wicked judge who will judge my enemy, and bring in one of his enemies who will stand up and accuse him.<verse eid="PSA 109:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 109:7"/>When the trial ends, cause the judge to declare that he is guilty and cause even his plea for mercy to be considered a sin.<verse eid="PSA 109:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 109:8"/>Then cause him to die soon; bring someone else to take over his work.<verse eid="PSA 109:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 109:9"/>Cause his children not to have a father anymore, and cause his wife to become a widow.<verse eid="PSA 109:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 109:10"/>Cause his children to leave the ruined homes that they have been living in and to wander around begging for food.<verse eid="PSA 109:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 109:11"/>Cause all the people to whom he owed money to seize his property; cause strangers to take away everything that he worked to acquire.<verse eid="PSA 109:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 109:12"/>Make sure that no one acts with any loyalty toward his memory for the sake of your covenant; make sure that no one pities his children.<verse eid="PSA 109:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 109:13"/>Cause all his children to die, so that no one will live to carry on his name.<verse eid="PSA 109:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 109:14"/>Yahweh, remember and do not forgive his ancestors for the evil things that they did, and do not even forgive the sins that his mother committed.<verse eid="PSA 109:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 109:15"/>Think about his sins continually, but cause everyone living to completely forget who he was.<verse eid="PSA 109:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 109:16"/>I pray these things because that man, my enemy, never acted toward anyone as your covenant says we must; he persecuted poor and needy people and even killed helpless people.<verse eid="PSA 109:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 109:17"/>He liked to curse people. So those terrible things that he requested to happen to others—cause them to happen to him! He did not want to bless others, so make sure that no one blesses him!<verse eid="PSA 109:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 109:18"/>He often cursed other people, also; cause the terrible things that he wanted to happen to others to happen to him and enter his body as water does, as olive oil soaks into a person’s bones when it is rubbed on his skin.<verse eid="PSA 109:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 109:19"/>Cause those terrible things to cling to him like his clothes and be around him like the belt that he wears every day.<verse eid="PSA 109:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 109:20"/>Yahweh, I wish that you will punish all my enemies that way, those who say evil things about me.<verse eid="PSA 109:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 109:21"/>But Yahweh, my God, do good things for me in order that I may honor you; rescue me from my enemies because you faithfully love me as you promised.<verse eid="PSA 109:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 109:22"/>I request you to do this because I am poor and needy and my inner being is full of pain.<verse eid="PSA 109:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 109:23"/>I think that my time to remain alive is as short as an evening shadow that will soon disappear. I will be blown away as a locust is blown by the wind.<verse eid="PSA 109:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 109:24"/>My knees are weak because I have fasted very often, and my body has become very thin.<verse eid="PSA 109:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 109:25"/>The people who accuse me make fun of me; when they see me, they insult me by shaking their heads at me.<verse eid="PSA 109:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 109:26"/>Yahweh, my God, help me! Because you faithfully love me, rescue me!<verse eid="PSA 109:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 109:27"/>When you save me, cause my enemies to know that you are the one who has done it!<verse eid="PSA 109:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 109:28"/>They may curse me, but I ask that you bless me. Cause those who persecute me to be defeated and disgraced, but cause me to be glad!<verse eid="PSA 109:28"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="29" style="v" sid="PSA 109:29"/>Cause those who accuse me to be completely disgraced; cause other people to see that they are disgraced as easily as they see the clothes that they wear!<verse eid="PSA 109:29"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="30" style="v" sid="PSA 109:30"/>But I will thank Yahweh very much; I will praise him when I am among the crowd of people who are worshiping him.<verse eid="PSA 109:30"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="31" style="v" sid="PSA 109:31"/>I will do that because he defends poor people like me and because he saves us from those who have said that we must die.<verse eid="PSA 109:31"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 109"/>
<chapter number="110" style="c" sid="PSA 110"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 110:1"/>A psalm written by David. Yahweh said to my lord the king, “Sit here, close to me, in the place of highest honor until I completely defeat your enemies and make them like a stool for your feet!”<verse eid="PSA 110:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 110:2"/>Yahweh will extend your power as king from Jerusalem to other lands; you will rule over all your enemies.<verse eid="PSA 110:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 110:3"/>On the day that you lead your armies into battle, many of your people will volunteer to join your army. Your youthful strength will act for you like the dew that waters the earth early in the morning.”<verse eid="PSA 110:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 110:4"/>Yahweh has made a solemn promise and he will never change his mind; he has said to the king, “You will be a priest forever like Melchizedek.”<verse eid="PSA 110:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 110:5"/>The Lord stands at your right side; when he becomes angry, he will defeat many kings.<verse eid="PSA 110:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 110:6"/>He will judge and punish the people of many nations; many bodies of the killed enemy soldiers will lie on the ground. He will crush kings all over the earth.<verse eid="PSA 110:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 110:7"/>But the king will drink from the stream alongside the road; he will be refreshed after defeating his enemies.<verse eid="PSA 110:7"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 110"/>
<chapter number="111" style="c" sid="PSA 111"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 111:1"/>Praise Yahweh! I will thank Yahweh with my entire inner being every time that those who do what is right come together.<verse eid="PSA 111:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 111:2"/>The things that Yahweh has done are wonderful! All those who are delighted with those things desire to study them.<verse eid="PSA 111:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 111:3"/>Because he is a great king and does wonderful things, people greatly honor him and respect him; the righteous things that he does will endure forever.<verse eid="PSA 111:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 111:4"/>He has done wonderful things that people will always remember; Yahweh always acts kindly and mercifully.<verse eid="PSA 111:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 111:5"/>He provides food for those who have an awesome respect for him; he never forgets the covenant that he made with our ancestors.<verse eid="PSA 111:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 111:6"/>By enabling his people to capture the lands that belonged to other people groups, he has shown to us, his people, that he is very powerful.<verse eid="PSA 111:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 111:7"/>He does everything fairly, as he has promised us, and we can depend on him to help us when he commands us to do things.<verse eid="PSA 111:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 111:8"/>What he commands must be obeyed forever; and he acted in a true and righteous manner when he gave us those commands.<verse eid="PSA 111:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 111:9"/>He rescued us, his people, from being slaves in Egypt, and he made a covenant with us that will last forever. He is holy and awesome!<verse eid="PSA 111:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 111:10"/>Having an awesome respect for Yahweh is the way to become wise. All those who obey his commands will know what is good for them to decide to do. We should praise him forever!<verse eid="PSA 111:10"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 111"/>
<chapter number="112" style="c" sid="PSA 112"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 112:1"/>Praise Yahweh! How fortunate are those who have an awesome respect for him, those who happily obey his commands.<verse eid="PSA 112:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 112:2"/>Their children will prosper in their land; God will bless their descedants.<verse eid="PSA 112:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 112:3"/>Their families will be wealthy, and their righteous deeds will endure forever.<verse eid="PSA 112:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 112:4"/>For those who honor God, it is as if a light were shining on them in the darkness, on those who are kind, merciful and righteous.<verse eid="PSA 112:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 112:5"/>Things will go well for those who generously lend money to others and who conduct their businesses honestly.<verse eid="PSA 112:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 112:6"/>Righteous people will not be overwhelmed because of their troubles; other people will always treasure their memories of them.<verse eid="PSA 112:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 112:7"/>They are not afraid when they receive bad news; they confidently trust in Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 112:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 112:8"/>They are confident and not afraid because they know that they will see God defeat their enemies.<verse eid="PSA 112:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 112:9"/>They give things generously to poor people; their kind deeds will endure forever, and they will be exalted and honored.<verse eid="PSA 112:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 112:10"/>Wicked people see those things and are angry; they gnash their teeth angrily, but they will disappear and die. The wicked things that they want to do will never happen.<verse eid="PSA 112:10"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 112"/>
<chapter number="113" style="c" sid="PSA 113"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 113:1"/>Praise Yahweh! You people who serve Yahweh, praise him! Praise him!<verse eid="PSA 113:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 113:2"/>Everyone should praise Yahweh now and forever!<verse eid="PSA 113:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 113:3"/>People who live in the east and people who live in the west, everyone, should praise Yahweh!<verse eid="PSA 113:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 113:4"/>Yahweh rules over all the nations, and high in the heavens he shows that his glory is very great.<verse eid="PSA 113:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 113:5"/>There is no one who is like Yahweh, our God, who lives in the highest heaven<verse eid="PSA 113:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 113:6"/>and looks far down through the heavens and sees the people on the earth.<verse eid="PSA 113:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 113:7"/>He lifts poor people up so that they no longer sit in the dirt; he lifts needy people up so that they no longer sit on heaps of ashes<verse eid="PSA 113:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 113:8"/>and causes them to be honored by sitting next to leaders, leaders who rule his own people.<verse eid="PSA 113:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 113:9"/>He also enables women who have no children to live in their houses as happy as mothers with children. Praise Yahweh!<verse eid="PSA 113:9"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 113"/>
<chapter number="114" style="c" sid="PSA 114"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 114:1"/>When the Israelite people left Egypt, when the descendants of Jacob left people who spoke a foreign language,<verse eid="PSA 114:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 114:2"/>the land of Judah became the place where people worshiped God; and Israel became the land that he ruled over.<verse eid="PSA 114:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 114:3"/>When they came to the Sea of Reeds, it was as though the water saw them and ran away! When they came to the Jordan River, the water in the river stopped flowing so that the Israelites could cross it.<verse eid="PSA 114:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 114:4"/>When they came to Mount Sinai and there was a big earthquake, it was as though the mountains skipped like goats and the hills jumped around like lambs.<verse eid="PSA 114:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 114:5"/>If someone asks, “What happened at the Sea of Reeds that caused the water to run away? What happened that caused the water in the Jordan River to stop flowing?<verse eid="PSA 114:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 114:6"/>What happened that caused the mountains to skip like goats and caused the hills to jump around like lambs?”<verse eid="PSA 114:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 114:7"/>Indeed, all the earth will tremble before the Lord! Everyone will tremble in the presence of the God whom Jacob worshiped!<verse eid="PSA 114:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 114:8"/>He is the one who caused pools of water to flow from a rock for the Israelite people to drink, and he is the one who caused a spring to flow from a solid rock cliff!<verse eid="PSA 114:8"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 114"/>
<chapter number="115" style="c" sid="PSA 115"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 115:1"/>A psalm written by David; Yahweh, people should praise you alone; they must praise you, not us, because you faithfully love us and always do what you have promised to do.<verse eid="PSA 115:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 115:2"/>It is not right that other people groups should say about us, “They claim that their God is very powerful, but if that is true, why does he not help them?”<verse eid="PSA 115:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 115:3"/>Our God is in heaven, and he does whatever he wants!<verse eid="PSA 115:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 115:4"/>But their idols are only statues made of silver and gold, things that humans have made.<verse eid="PSA 115:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 115:5"/>Their idols have mouths, but they cannot say anything; they have eyes, but they cannot see anything.<verse eid="PSA 115:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 115:6"/>They have ears, but they cannot hear anything; they have noses, but they cannot smell anything.<verse eid="PSA 115:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 115:7"/>They have hands, but they cannot feel anything; they have feet, but they cannot walk, and they cannot even make any sounds in their throats!<verse eid="PSA 115:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 115:8"/>The people who make those idols are as powerless as those idols, and those who trust in those idols can accomplish nothing, just like their idols!<verse eid="PSA 115:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 115:9"/>You, my fellow Israelite people, trust in Yahweh! He is the one who helps you and protects you like a shield.<verse eid="PSA 115:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 115:10"/>You priests, descendants of Aaron, trust in Yahweh! He is the one who helps you and protects you like a shield.<verse eid="PSA 115:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 115:11"/>All you who have a reverential respect for Yahweh, trust in him! He is the one who helps you and protects you like a shield.<verse eid="PSA 115:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 115:12"/>Yahweh has not forgotten us; he will bless us Israelite people! He will bless the priests,<verse eid="PSA 115:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 115:13"/>and he will bless all those who have a reverential respect for him; he will bless important people and people who are considered to be unimportant, everyone!<verse eid="PSA 115:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 115:14"/>I wish that Yahweh may give many children to you, my fellow Israelite people, and to your descendants.<verse eid="PSA 115:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 115:15"/>I wish that Yahweh, the one who made heaven and the earth, may bless all of you!<verse eid="PSA 115:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 115:16"/>The highest heavens belong to Yahweh, but he gave everything that is on the earth to us people.<verse eid="PSA 115:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 115:17"/>Dead people are not able to praise Yahweh; when they descend into the place where dead people are, they are unable to speak and cannot praise him.<verse eid="PSA 115:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 115:18"/>But we who are alive will thank him, now and forever. Praise Yahweh!<verse eid="PSA 115:18"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 115"/>
<chapter number="116" style="c" sid="PSA 116"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 116:1"/>I love Yahweh because he hears me when I cry to him for help.<verse eid="PSA 116:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 116:2"/>He listens to me, so I will call out to him all during my life.<verse eid="PSA 116:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 116:3"/>Everything around me caused me to think that I would die; I was very afraid that I would die and go to the place where dead people are. I was very distressed and afraid.<verse eid="PSA 116:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 116:4"/>But then I called out to Yahweh, saying, “Yahweh, I plead with you to save me!”<verse eid="PSA 116:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 116:5"/>Yahweh is kind and does what is right; he is our God, and he acts mercifully to us.<verse eid="PSA 116:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 116:6"/>He protects those who are helpless; when I thought that I would die, he saved me.<verse eid="PSA 116:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 116:7"/>I must encourage myself because Yahweh has done very good things for me.<verse eid="PSA 116:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 116:8"/>Yahweh has saved me from dying and has kept me from troubles that would cause me to cry. He has kept me from disaster.<verse eid="PSA 116:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 116:9"/>So here on the earth where people are still alive, I live, knowing that Yahweh is directing me.<verse eid="PSA 116:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 116:10"/>I continued to believe in Yahweh, even when I said, “I am greatly afflicted.”<verse eid="PSA 116:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 116:11"/>Even when I was distressed and said, “I cannot trust anyone,” I continued to trust in Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 116:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 116:12"/>So now I will tell you what I will offer to Yahweh because of all the good things that he has done for me.<verse eid="PSA 116:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 116:13"/>I will offer to him a cup of wine to thank him for saving me.<verse eid="PSA 116:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 116:14"/>When I am together with many people who belong to Yahweh, I will give to him the offerings that I solemnly promised to give to him.<verse eid="PSA 116:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 116:15"/>Yahweh is very grieved when one of his people dies.<verse eid="PSA 116:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 116:16"/>I am one of those who serves Yahweh; I serve him like my mother did. He has ended my troubles.<verse eid="PSA 116:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 116:17"/>So I will offer to him a sacrifice to thank him, and I will pray to him.<verse eid="PSA 116:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 116:18"/>(18-19) When I am together with many of the people who belong to Yahweh in the courtyard outside his temple in Jerusalem, I will give to him the offerings that I solemnly promised to give to him. Praise Yahweh!<verse eid="PSA 116:18"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 116"/>
<chapter number="117" style="c" sid="PSA 117"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 117:1"/>You people of all nations, praise Yahweh! All you people groups, praise him<verse eid="PSA 117:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 117:2"/>because he faithfully loves us as he promised to do, and he will forever do for us what he promised that he would do. Praise Yahweh!<verse eid="PSA 117:2"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 117"/>
<chapter number="118" style="c" sid="PSA 118"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 118:1"/>Tell Yahweh that you thank him very much for the good things that he has done for you! He faithfully loves us, his people, forever.<verse eid="PSA 118:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 118:2"/>You Israelite people should repeatedly shout, “He faithfully loves us, his people, forever!”<verse eid="PSA 118:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 118:3"/>You priests who are descendants of Aaron should repeatedly shout, “He faithfully loves us, his people, forever!”<verse eid="PSA 118:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 118:4"/>All you who revere him should repeatedly shout, “He faithfully loves us, his people, forever!”<verse eid="PSA 118:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 118:5"/>When I was distressed, I called out to Yahweh, and he answered me and set me free from my worries.<verse eid="PSA 118:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 118:6"/>Yahweh is on my side, so I will not be afraid of anything. No one can do anything that will prevent God from blessing me forever.<verse eid="PSA 118:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 118:7"/>Yes, Yahweh is on my side, so I will look triumphantly at my enemies while he defeats them.<verse eid="PSA 118:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 118:8"/>It is better to trust in Yahweh than to depend on people.<verse eid="PSA 118:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 118:9"/>It is better to trust Yahweh to protect us than to trust that influential people will protect us.<verse eid="PSA 118:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 118:10"/>Armies of many nations surrounded us, but Yahweh enabled us to defeat them by his power.<verse eid="PSA 118:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 118:11"/>They completely surrounded us, but we defeated them all by Yahweh’s power.<verse eid="PSA 118:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 118:12"/>They swarmed around me like angry bees; they were like a fire that flares up in a thornbush, but we defeated them by Yahweh’s power.<verse eid="PSA 118:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 118:13"/>Our enemies attacked us fiercely and almost defeated us, but Yahweh helped us.<verse eid="PSA 118:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 118:14"/>Yahweh is the one who makes me strong, and he is the one about whom I always sing; he has saved us from my enemies.<verse eid="PSA 118:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 118:15"/>Listen to the joyful songs of victory being sung in the tents of the people who honor God! They sing, “Yahweh has defeated our enemies by his mighty power;<verse eid="PSA 118:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 118:16"/>he has raised his strong right arm to show he is happy over defeating his enemies. Yahweh has completely defeated them!”<verse eid="PSA 118:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 118:17"/>I will not be killed in battle; I will live to proclaim the great things that Yahweh has done.<verse eid="PSA 118:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 118:18"/>Yahweh has punished me severely, but he has not allowed me to die.<verse eid="PSA 118:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 118:19"/>You gatekeepers, open for me the gates of the temple so that I may enter and thank Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 118:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 118:20"/>Those are the gates through which we enter the temple to worship Yahweh; those who honor God enter through those gates.<verse eid="PSA 118:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 118:21"/>Yahweh, I thank you that you answered my prayer and that you saved me from my enemies.<verse eid="PSA 118:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 118:22"/>Yahweh’s chosen king is like a stone that the builders rejected when they were building a house, but that stone became the cornerstone.<verse eid="PSA 118:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 118:23"/>This was done by Yahweh, and it is a wonderful thing for us to see.<verse eid="PSA 118:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 118:24"/>This is the day on which we remember that Yahweh acted powerfully to defeat our enemies; we will rejoice and be glad today.<verse eid="PSA 118:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 118:25"/>Yahweh, we plead with you to keep rescuing us from our enemies. Yahweh, please help us accomplish what we want to do.<verse eid="PSA 118:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 118:26"/>Yahweh, bless the one who will come with your power. From the temple we bless all of you.<verse eid="PSA 118:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 118:27"/>Yahweh is God, and he has caused his light to come to us. Come, bring animal sacrifice and tie it to the horns of the altar.<verse eid="PSA 118:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 118:28"/>Yahweh, you are the God whom I worship, and I will praise you! You are my God, and I will tell everyone that you are great!<verse eid="PSA 118:28"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="29" style="v" sid="PSA 118:29"/>Thank Yahweh because he does good things for us! He will faithfully love us forever as he has promised.<verse eid="PSA 118:29"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 118"/>
<chapter number="119" style="c" sid="PSA 119"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 119:1"/>How fortunate are those about whom no one can say truthfully that they have done things that are wrong, those who always obey the laws of Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 119:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 119:2"/>How fortunate are those who obey his weighty commands, those who request him with their entire inner beings to help them to do that.<verse eid="PSA 119:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 119:3"/>They do not do things that are wrong; they behave as Yahweh wants them to.<verse eid="PSA 119:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 119:4"/>Yahweh, you have given us your principles of behavior, and you told us to obey them faithfully.<verse eid="PSA 119:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 119:5"/>I want so much to faithfully keep everything that you command.<verse eid="PSA 119:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 119:6"/>If I did that, I would not be ashamed when I thought about your commands.<verse eid="PSA 119:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 119:7"/>When I learn all of your just regulations, I will praise you with a pure inner being.<verse eid="PSA 119:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 119:8"/>I will obey all your statutes; do not desert me!<verse eid="PSA 119:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 119:9"/>I know how a young person can live in a pure way; it is by obeying your commands.<verse eid="PSA 119:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 119:10"/>I try to serve you with my entire inner being; do not allow me to wander away from what you have commanded.<verse eid="PSA 119:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 119:11"/>I have memorized your commands so that I will not sin against you.<verse eid="PSA 119:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 119:12"/>Yahweh, I praise you; teach me your statutes.<verse eid="PSA 119:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 119:13"/>I have announced to the people all the things that you have commanded us to do.<verse eid="PSA 119:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 119:14"/>I delight in obeying your requirements; I enjoy that more than being very rich.<verse eid="PSA 119:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 119:15"/>I will study everything you have commanded, and I will pay attention to how you have shown me to live.<verse eid="PSA 119:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 119:16"/>I will be happy to obey your statutes, and I will not forget your words.<verse eid="PSA 119:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 119:17"/>Do good things for me, the one who serves you, so that I may continue to live and obey your words during all my life.<verse eid="PSA 119:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 119:18"/>Help me to understand with my mind, to know the wonderful things that are written in your laws.<verse eid="PSA 119:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 119:19"/>I am living here on the earth for only a short time; do not keep me from understanding.<verse eid="PSA 119:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 119:20"/>In my inner being I strongly desire to know your decrees all the time.<verse eid="PSA 119:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 119:21"/>You rebuke those who are proud; you curse those who disobey your commands.<verse eid="PSA 119:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 119:22"/>Do not allow them to continue to insult and scorn me; I request this because I have obeyed your requirements.<verse eid="PSA 119:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 119:23"/>Rulers gather together and plan ways to harm me, but I will meditate on what you have commanded.<verse eid="PSA 119:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 119:24"/>I am delighted with your requirements; it is as though they were my advisors.<verse eid="PSA 119:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 119:25"/>I think that I will soon die; save my life as you have promised me that you would.<verse eid="PSA 119:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 119:26"/>When I told you about all the things I did, you answered me; teach me your statutes.<verse eid="PSA 119:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 119:27"/>Help me to understand how you want me to behave, and then I will meditate on your amazing instructions.<verse eid="PSA 119:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 119:28"/>I am very sad, with the result that I have no strength; enable me to be strong again as you promised me that you would do.<verse eid="PSA 119:28"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="29" style="v" sid="PSA 119:29"/>Prevent me from telling lies, and be kind to me by teaching me your laws.<verse eid="PSA 119:29"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="30" style="v" sid="PSA 119:30"/>I have decided that I will faithfully obey you; I am determined to follow your commands.<verse eid="PSA 119:30"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="31" style="v" sid="PSA 119:31"/>Yahweh, I try to carefully cling to your requirements; do not abandon me or let me be disgraced.<verse eid="PSA 119:31"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="32" style="v" sid="PSA 119:32"/>I will eagerly obey your commands because you have helped me understand better and better what you want me to do.<verse eid="PSA 119:32"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="33" style="v" sid="PSA 119:33"/>Yahweh, teach me the meaning of your statutes, and then I will completely obey them.<verse eid="PSA 119:33"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="34" style="v" sid="PSA 119:34"/>Help me to understand your laws so that I may obey them with all my inner being.<verse eid="PSA 119:34"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="35" style="v" sid="PSA 119:35"/>I am happy with your commands, so lead me along the paths that you have chosen for me.<verse eid="PSA 119:35"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="36" style="v" sid="PSA 119:36"/>Cause me to want to do what you command and not to want to become rich.<verse eid="PSA 119:36"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="37" style="v" sid="PSA 119:37"/>Do not allow me to look at things that are worthless; make me able to live as you want me to live.<verse eid="PSA 119:37"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="38" style="v" sid="PSA 119:38"/>Because I am one who serves you, do what you promised to do for me, which is what you also promise to do for all those who honor you.<verse eid="PSA 119:38"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="39" style="v" sid="PSA 119:39"/>I become afraid when my enemies insult me; stop them! But you are right when you punish my enemies.<verse eid="PSA 119:39"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="40" style="v" sid="PSA 119:40"/>I very much desire to obey your principles of behavior; because you are righteous, allow me to continue to live.<verse eid="PSA 119:40"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="41" style="v" sid="PSA 119:41"/>Yahweh, show me that you faithfully love me, and rescue me as you promised you would.<verse eid="PSA 119:41"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="42" style="v" sid="PSA 119:42"/>After you do that, I will be able to reply to those who insult me because I trust in your word.<verse eid="PSA 119:42"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="43" style="v" sid="PSA 119:43"/>Never prevent me from speaking your truth because I have confidence in your regulations.<verse eid="PSA 119:43"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="44" style="v" sid="PSA 119:44"/>I will always obey your laws forever and ever.<verse eid="PSA 119:44"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="45" style="v" sid="PSA 119:45"/>I will always be safe because I have tried to obey your principles of behavior.<verse eid="PSA 119:45"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="46" style="v" sid="PSA 119:46"/>I will tell to kings what you require, and because they are unable to prove me wrong, they will not cause me to be ashamed.<verse eid="PSA 119:46"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="47" style="v" sid="PSA 119:47"/>I am delighted to obey your commands, and I love them.<verse eid="PSA 119:47"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="48" style="v" sid="PSA 119:48"/>I respect your commandments, and I love them; I will meditate on everything you require us to do.<verse eid="PSA 119:48"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="49" style="v" sid="PSA 119:49"/>Do not forget what you said you would do for me, the one who serves you, because what you have said has caused me to confidently expect good things from you.<verse eid="PSA 119:49"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="50" style="v" sid="PSA 119:50"/>When I have been suffering, you comforted me; you did what you promised me, and that kept me alive.<verse eid="PSA 119:50"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="51" style="v" sid="PSA 119:51"/>Proud people are always making fun of me, but I do not turn away from obeying your laws.<verse eid="PSA 119:51"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="52" style="v" sid="PSA 119:52"/>Yahweh, when I think about your regulations that you gave to us long ago, I am comforted.<verse eid="PSA 119:52"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="53" style="v" sid="PSA 119:53"/>When I see wicked people disregard your laws, I become very angry.<verse eid="PSA 119:53"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="54" style="v" sid="PSA 119:54"/>While I have been living here on the earth for a short time, I have written songs about your statutes.<verse eid="PSA 119:54"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="55" style="v" sid="PSA 119:55"/>Yahweh, during the night I think about you, and so I obey your laws.<verse eid="PSA 119:55"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="56" style="v" sid="PSA 119:56"/>What I have always done is to obey your principles of behavior.<verse eid="PSA 119:56"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="57" style="v" sid="PSA 119:57"/>Yahweh, you are the one whom I have chosen, and I promise to obey your words.<verse eid="PSA 119:57"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="58" style="v" sid="PSA 119:58"/>With all my inner being I plead with you to be good to me; act kindly to me as you promised that you would do.<verse eid="PSA 119:58"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="59" style="v" sid="PSA 119:59"/>I have thought about my behavior, and I have decided to return to obeying your requirements.<verse eid="PSA 119:59"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="60" style="v" sid="PSA 119:60"/>I hurry to obey your commands; I do not delay at all.<verse eid="PSA 119:60"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="61" style="v" sid="PSA 119:61"/>Wicked people have tried to seize me as a hunter tries to catch an animal with a net, but I do not forget your laws.<verse eid="PSA 119:61"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="62" style="v" sid="PSA 119:62"/>In the middle of the night I awake, and I praise you for your commands because they are fair.<verse eid="PSA 119:62"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="63" style="v" sid="PSA 119:63"/>I am a friend of all those who have an awesome respect for you, those who obey your principles of behavior.<verse eid="PSA 119:63"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="64" style="v" sid="PSA 119:64"/>Yahweh, you faithfully love people all over the earth; teach me your statutes.<verse eid="PSA 119:64"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="65" style="v" sid="PSA 119:65"/>Yahweh, you have done good things for me as you promised that you would do.<verse eid="PSA 119:65"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="66" style="v" sid="PSA 119:66"/>Teach me to think carefully before I decide what to do, and teach me other things that I need to know because I believe that it is right for us to obey your commands.<verse eid="PSA 119:66"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="67" style="v" sid="PSA 119:67"/>Before you afflicted me, I did things that were wrong, but now I obey your words.<verse eid="PSA 119:67"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="68" style="v" sid="PSA 119:68"/>You are very good, and what you do is good; teach me your statutes.<verse eid="PSA 119:68"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="69" style="v" sid="PSA 119:69"/>Proud people have told many lies about me, but as for me, I obey your principles of behavior.<verse eid="PSA 119:69"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="70" style="v" sid="PSA 119:70"/>Those people are stubborn, but as for me, I am delighted with your laws.<verse eid="PSA 119:70"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="71" style="v" sid="PSA 119:71"/>It was good for me that you afflicted me because the result was that I learned your statutes.<verse eid="PSA 119:71"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="72" style="v" sid="PSA 119:72"/>The laws that you give to us are worth more to me than gold, more than thousands of pieces of gold and silver.<verse eid="PSA 119:72"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="73" style="v" sid="PSA 119:73"/>You created me and formed my body; help me to be wise so that I may learn your commands.<verse eid="PSA 119:73"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="74" style="v" sid="PSA 119:74"/>Those who have an awesome respect for you will see what you have done for me, because they have confidence in the promises of your word.<verse eid="PSA 119:74"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="75" style="v" sid="PSA 119:75"/>Yahweh, I know that your regulations are right and that you have made me suffer because you love me without end.<verse eid="PSA 119:75"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="76" style="v" sid="PSA 119:76"/>Comfort me by showing that you faithfully love me as you said to me that you would do.<verse eid="PSA 119:76"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="77" style="v" sid="PSA 119:77"/>Act mercifully to me so that I may continue to live because I am delighted with your laws.<verse eid="PSA 119:77"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="78" style="v" sid="PSA 119:78"/>Cause the proud people who falsely accuse me to be shamed; but as for me, I will continue meditating on what you have commanded I should do.<verse eid="PSA 119:78"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="79" style="v" sid="PSA 119:79"/>Cause those who have an awesome respect for you to come back to me so that they may learn what you command.<verse eid="PSA 119:79"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="80" style="v" sid="PSA 119:80"/>Enable me to perfectly obey your statutes so that I may not be ashamed because of not doing that.<verse eid="PSA 119:80"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="81" style="v" sid="PSA 119:81"/>I am waiting for you to save me from my enemies; I confidently expect that you will tell me what you will do.<verse eid="PSA 119:81"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="82" style="v" sid="PSA 119:82"/>My eyes are tired from waiting a long time for you to do what you promised that you would do, and I ask, “When will you help me?”<verse eid="PSA 119:82"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="83" style="v" sid="PSA 119:83"/>I have become as useless as a wineskin that is shriveled from hanging a long time in the smoke inside a house, but I have not forgotten your statutes.<verse eid="PSA 119:83"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="84" style="v" sid="PSA 119:84"/>How long must I wait? When will you punish those who persecute me?<verse eid="PSA 119:84"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="85" style="v" sid="PSA 119:85"/>It is as though proud people, those who do not obey your laws, have dug deep pits for me to fall into.<verse eid="PSA 119:85"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="86" style="v" sid="PSA 119:86"/>All your commands are trustworthy; but people are persecuting me by telling lies about me, so please help me.<verse eid="PSA 119:86"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="87" style="v" sid="PSA 119:87"/>Those people almost killed me, but I have not stopped obeying your principles of behavior.<verse eid="PSA 119:87"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="88" style="v" sid="PSA 119:88"/>Because you faithfully love me, allow me to continue to live so that I may continue to obey your requirements that you have spoken.<verse eid="PSA 119:88"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="89" style="v" sid="PSA 119:89"/>Yahweh, your word will last forever; it is firmly fixed in heaven.<verse eid="PSA 119:89"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="90" style="v" sid="PSA 119:90"/>You will faithfully continue to act for people who are not yet born; you have put the earth in its place, and it remains firmly there.<verse eid="PSA 119:90"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="91" style="v" sid="PSA 119:91"/>To this day, all things on the earth remain because you decided that they should remain; everything on the earth serves you.<verse eid="PSA 119:91"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="92" style="v" sid="PSA 119:92"/>If I had not been delighted in obeying your laws, I would have died because of what I was suffering.<verse eid="PSA 119:92"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="93" style="v" sid="PSA 119:93"/>I will never forget your principles of behavior because as a result of my obeying them, you have enabled me to continue to live.<verse eid="PSA 119:93"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="94" style="v" sid="PSA 119:94"/>I belong to you; save me from my enemies because I have tried to obey your principles of behavior.<verse eid="PSA 119:94"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="95" style="v" sid="PSA 119:95"/>Wicked men are waiting to kill me, but I will think about your requirements.<verse eid="PSA 119:95"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="96" style="v" sid="PSA 119:96"/>I have learned that there is a limit for everything, but your commands have no limit.<verse eid="PSA 119:96"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="97" style="v" sid="PSA 119:97"/>I love your laws very much. I meditate on them all during the day.<verse eid="PSA 119:97"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="98" style="v" sid="PSA 119:98"/>Because I know your commands and because I think about them all the time, I have become wiser than my enemies.<verse eid="PSA 119:98"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="99" style="v" sid="PSA 119:99"/>I understand more than my teachers do because I meditate on what you command.<verse eid="PSA 119:99"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="100" style="v" sid="PSA 119:100"/>I understand more than many old people do because I obey your principles of behavior.<verse eid="PSA 119:100"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="101" style="v" sid="PSA 119:101"/>I have avoided all evil behavior so that I may obey your words.<verse eid="PSA 119:101"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="102" style="v" sid="PSA 119:102"/>I have not refused to obey them because you have taught me while I have studied them.<verse eid="PSA 119:102"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="103" style="v" sid="PSA 119:103"/>When I read your words, they are like honey that I eat; yes, they are even sweeter than honey.<verse eid="PSA 119:103"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="104" style="v" sid="PSA 119:104"/>Because I have learned your principles of behavior, I am able to understand many things; therefore I hate all evil things that some people do.<verse eid="PSA 119:104"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="105" style="v" sid="PSA 119:105"/>Your word is a lamp to guide me; it is like a light that shows me where to walk.<verse eid="PSA 119:105"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="106" style="v" sid="PSA 119:106"/>I have solemnly promised, and I am solemnly promising it again, that I will always obey your regulations; they are all fair.<verse eid="PSA 119:106"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="107" style="v" sid="PSA 119:107"/>Yahweh, I am suffering very much; cause me to be strong again as you have promised to do.<verse eid="PSA 119:107"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="108" style="v" sid="PSA 119:108"/>Yahweh, when I thank you while I pray, it is like a sacrifice to you; please accept it, and teach me your regulations.<verse eid="PSA 119:108"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="109" style="v" sid="PSA 119:109"/>My enemies are often trying to kill me, but I do not forget your laws.<verse eid="PSA 119:109"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="110" style="v" sid="PSA 119:110"/>Wicked people have tried to seize me as a hunter tries to catch little animals with a trap, but I have not disobeyed your principles of behavior.<verse eid="PSA 119:110"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="111" style="v" sid="PSA 119:111"/>I have your requirements forever; because of them, I am joyful in my inner being.<verse eid="PSA 119:111"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="112" style="v" sid="PSA 119:112"/>I have decided to always obey your commands, every one of them.<verse eid="PSA 119:112"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="113" style="v" sid="PSA 119:113"/>I hate people who only say they love you, but I love your laws.<verse eid="PSA 119:113"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="114" style="v" sid="PSA 119:114"/>You are like a place where I can hide from my enemies, and you are like a shield behind which I am protected from them; I trust in your promises.<verse eid="PSA 119:114"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="115" style="v" sid="PSA 119:115"/>You evil people, go away from me so than I may obey my God’s commands!<verse eid="PSA 119:115"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="116" style="v" sid="PSA 119:116"/>Enable me to be strong as you promised that you would do, so that I may continue to live. I am confidently expecting that you will restore me; do not disappoint me.<verse eid="PSA 119:116"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="117" style="v" sid="PSA 119:117"/>Hold me up so that I may be safe and always pay attention to your commands.<verse eid="PSA 119:117"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="118" style="v" sid="PSA 119:118"/>You reject all those who disobey your statutes; because they make deceitful plans and they do not keep their word.<verse eid="PSA 119:118"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="119" style="v" sid="PSA 119:119"/>You get rid of all the wicked people on the earth as people get rid of trash; therefore I love your requirements.<verse eid="PSA 119:119"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="120" style="v" sid="PSA 119:120"/>I tremble because I am afraid of you; I am afraid because you punish those who do not obey your regulations.<verse eid="PSA 119:120"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="121" style="v" sid="PSA 119:121"/>But I have done what is right and fair; so do not allow people to oppress me.<verse eid="PSA 119:121"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="122" style="v" sid="PSA 119:122"/>Be responsible for doing good things for me, and do not allow proud people to oppress me.<verse eid="PSA 119:122"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="123" style="v" sid="PSA 119:123"/>My eyes are tired from waiting a long time for you to rescue me, for you to save me as you promised that you would.<verse eid="PSA 119:123"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="124" style="v" sid="PSA 119:124"/>Do something for me to show that you faithfully love me, and teach me your statutes.<verse eid="PSA 119:124"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="125" style="v" sid="PSA 119:125"/>I am one who serves you; enable me to understand what you want me to know so that I may learn your requirements.<verse eid="PSA 119:125"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="126" style="v" sid="PSA 119:126"/>Yahweh, now is the time for you to punish people because they have disobeyed your laws.<verse eid="PSA 119:126"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="127" style="v" sid="PSA 119:127"/>Truly, I love your commands more than I love gold; I love them more than I love very pure gold.<verse eid="PSA 119:127"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="128" style="v" sid="PSA 119:128"/>So I conduct my life by your principles of behavior, and I hate all the evil things that some people do.<verse eid="PSA 119:128"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="129" style="v" sid="PSA 119:129"/>Your requirements are wonderful, so I obey them with all my inner being.<verse eid="PSA 119:129"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="130" style="v" sid="PSA 119:130"/>When someone explains your words, it is as though they are lighting a light; what they say causes even people who have not learned your laws to be wise.<verse eid="PSA 119:130"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="131" style="v" sid="PSA 119:131"/>I eagerly desire to know your commands as a dog pants with its mouth open, wanting to be fed.<verse eid="PSA 119:131"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="132" style="v" sid="PSA 119:132"/>Listen to me and act kindly to me as you do to all those who love you.<verse eid="PSA 119:132"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="133" style="v" sid="PSA 119:133"/>Guide me as you promised; do not allow evil people to control what I do.<verse eid="PSA 119:133"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="134" style="v" sid="PSA 119:134"/>Rescue me from those who oppress me so that I may obey your principles of behavior.<verse eid="PSA 119:134"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="135" style="v" sid="PSA 119:135"/>Act kindly toward me and teach me your statutes.<verse eid="PSA 119:135"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="136" style="v" sid="PSA 119:136"/>I cry very much because many people do not obey your laws.<verse eid="PSA 119:136"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="137" style="v" sid="PSA 119:137"/>Yahweh, you are righteous and your regulations are just.<verse eid="PSA 119:137"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="138" style="v" sid="PSA 119:138"/>You did what was right when you gave us the laws of your covenant promise, and you can be trusted when you made those promises to us.<verse eid="PSA 119:138"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="139" style="v" sid="PSA 119:139"/>I am furious because my enemies disregard your words.<verse eid="PSA 119:139"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="140" style="v" sid="PSA 119:140"/>I have found that your promises are dependable, and I love them.<verse eid="PSA 119:140"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="141" style="v" sid="PSA 119:141"/>I am not important, and people despise me, but I do not forget your principles of behavior.<verse eid="PSA 119:141"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="142" style="v" sid="PSA 119:142"/>You are righteous and you will be righteous forever, and your laws will never be changed.<verse eid="PSA 119:142"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="143" style="v" sid="PSA 119:143"/>I constantly have troubles and I am worried, but your commands cause me to be happy.<verse eid="PSA 119:143"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="144" style="v" sid="PSA 119:144"/>Your requirements are always fair; help me to understand them so that I may continue to live.<verse eid="PSA 119:144"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="145" style="v" sid="PSA 119:145"/>Yahweh, with all my inner being I call out to you; answer me and I will obey your statutes.<verse eid="PSA 119:145"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="146" style="v" sid="PSA 119:146"/>I call out to you, “Save me, and I will keep your commandments.”<verse eid="PSA 119:146"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="147" style="v" sid="PSA 119:147"/>Each morning I arise before dawn and call to you to help me; I confidently expect you to do what you have promised.<verse eid="PSA 119:147"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="148" style="v" sid="PSA 119:148"/>All during the night I am awake, and I meditate on your commands and your promises.<verse eid="PSA 119:148"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="149" style="v" sid="PSA 119:149"/>Yahweh, because you faithfully love me, listen to me while I pray; keep me safe because I keep your regulations.<verse eid="PSA 119:149"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="150" style="v" sid="PSA 119:150"/>Those evil people who oppress me are coming closer to me; they do not pay any attention to your laws.<verse eid="PSA 119:150"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="151" style="v" sid="PSA 119:151"/>But Yahweh, you are near to me, and I know that your commands will never be changed.<verse eid="PSA 119:151"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="152" style="v" sid="PSA 119:152"/>Long ago I found out about your requirements, and I know that you intended them to last forever.<verse eid="PSA 119:152"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="153" style="v" sid="PSA 119:153"/>Look at me, see that I am suffering very much, and heal me because I do not forget your laws.<verse eid="PSA 119:153"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="154" style="v" sid="PSA 119:154"/>Defend me when others accuse me and rescue me from them; allow me to continue to live as you promised that you would.<verse eid="PSA 119:154"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="155" style="v" sid="PSA 119:155"/>Wicked people do not obey your statutes, so you will certainly not save them.<verse eid="PSA 119:155"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="156" style="v" sid="PSA 119:156"/>Yahweh, you have been merciful by helping me in many ways; allow me to continue to live as you have done until now.<verse eid="PSA 119:156"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="157" style="v" sid="PSA 119:157"/>Many people are my enemies; many people cause me to suffer, but I do not neglect your commands.<verse eid="PSA 119:157"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="158" style="v" sid="PSA 119:158"/>When I look at those who are not faithful to you, I am disgusted because they do not obey your requirements.<verse eid="PSA 119:158"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="159" style="v" sid="PSA 119:159"/>Yahweh, notice that I love your principles of behavior; because you faithfully love me, allow me to continue to live.<verse eid="PSA 119:159"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="160" style="v" sid="PSA 119:160"/>I can rely on everything that you have said; all your regulations will endure forever.<verse eid="PSA 119:160"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="161" style="v" sid="PSA 119:161"/>Rulers persecute me for no reason, but in my inner being I have a very awesome respect for your words.<verse eid="PSA 119:161"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="162" style="v" sid="PSA 119:162"/>I am happy about your words, as happy as someone who has found a great treasure.<verse eid="PSA 119:162"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="163" style="v" sid="PSA 119:163"/>I thoroughly hate all lies but I love your laws.<verse eid="PSA 119:163"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="164" style="v" sid="PSA 119:164"/>I praise you seven times a day for your commandments because they are all just.<verse eid="PSA 119:164"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="165" style="v" sid="PSA 119:165"/>Things go well for those who love your laws; nothing will make them abandon your laws.<verse eid="PSA 119:165"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="166" style="v" sid="PSA 119:166"/>Yahweh, I confidently expect that you will rescue me from my troubles, and I obey your commands.<verse eid="PSA 119:166"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="167" style="v" sid="PSA 119:167"/>I obey what you require us to do; I love it all very much.<verse eid="PSA 119:167"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="168" style="v" sid="PSA 119:168"/>I obey your principles of behavior, and you see everything that I do.<verse eid="PSA 119:168"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="169" style="v" sid="PSA 119:169"/>Yahweh, listen while I pray for you to help me; help me to understand your words.<verse eid="PSA 119:169"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="170" style="v" sid="PSA 119:170"/>Hear me while I pray, and rescue me as you said you would.<verse eid="PSA 119:170"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="171" style="v" sid="PSA 119:171"/>I will always praise you because you teach me your rules.<verse eid="PSA 119:171"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="172" style="v" sid="PSA 119:172"/>I will sing about your words because all your commands are just.<verse eid="PSA 119:172"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="173" style="v" sid="PSA 119:173"/>I request you to always be ready to help me because I have chosen to obey your principles of behavior.<verse eid="PSA 119:173"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="174" style="v" sid="PSA 119:174"/>Yahweh, I eagerly desire for you to rescue me from my enemies; I am delighted with your laws.<verse eid="PSA 119:174"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="175" style="v" sid="PSA 119:175"/>Allow me to continue to live in order that I can continue to praise you so that your regulations will continue to help me.<verse eid="PSA 119:175"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="176" style="v" sid="PSA 119:176"/>I have sinned and turned away from you like a sheep that has left its flock; search for me because I have not forgotten your commands.<verse eid="PSA 119:176"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 119"/>
<chapter number="120" style="c" sid="PSA 120"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 120:1"/>A psalm written for people going up to the temple to worship; I cried out to Yahweh when I was distressed and he responded to me.<verse eid="PSA 120:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 120:2"/>{I prayed,} “Yahweh, save me from those who lie to me and try to deceive me!”<verse eid="PSA 120:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 120:3"/>You who deceive other people, Yahweh will certainly punish you!<verse eid="PSA 120:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 120:4"/>When Yahweh punishes you, it will be as if soldiers were shooting sharp arrows at you as well as throwing hot coals from the wood of a broom tree.<verse eid="PSA 120:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 120:5"/>It is terrible for me because {it has been like I have lived far from Israel}. For it was as though I was sojourning in the region of Meshech or living among those who live in the tents of the region of Kedar.<verse eid="PSA 120:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 120:6"/>I lived for a long time among people who hate to live with others peacefully.<verse eid="PSA 120:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 120:7"/>I want to live with others peacefully. But every time I talk about living together peacefully, they talk about wanting to start a war.<verse eid="PSA 120:7"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 120"/>
<chapter number="121" style="c" sid="PSA 121"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 121:1"/>A psalm written for people going up to the temple to worship; I look up toward the tops of the hills and I think, “Who will help me?”<verse eid="PSA 121:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 121:2"/>{Then I remember,} “Yahweh is the one who will help me. He is the one who made the whole world.”<verse eid="PSA 121:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 121:3"/>{Then someone said to me,} “God will keep your from being harmed, he will always be ready to protect you.<verse eid="PSA 121:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 121:4"/>Surely Yahweh, who protects the Israelites, is always ready to protect you.<verse eid="PSA 121:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 121:5"/>Yahweh guards you. He is like the shade of a tree that protects you,<verse eid="PSA 121:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 121:6"/>so that the sun will not harm you during the day, and the moon will not harm you during the night.<verse eid="PSA 121:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 121:7"/>Yahweh will guard you from all kinds of harm. He will keep you safe.<verse eid="PSA 121:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 121:8"/>Yahweh will protect you from the time that you leave your house in the morning until you return to your house in the evening. He will protect you now and he will protect you forever.”<verse eid="PSA 121:8"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 121"/>
<chapter number="122" style="c" sid="PSA 122"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 122:1"/>A psalm written by David for people going up to the temple to worship. I was glad when people said to me, “We should go to the temple of Yahweh in Jerusalem!”<verse eid="PSA 122:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 122:2"/>O Jerusalem, we are standing inside your gates.<verse eid="PSA 122:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 122:3"/>Jerusalem was built to be a city that protects its inhabitants.<verse eid="PSA 122:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 122:4"/>It is a city that people who belong to Yahweh can go up to. He has commanded them to do this, so that they can praise him.<verse eid="PSA 122:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 122:5"/>In that city are the thrones, from where the kings judged the people, from where the descendants of King David ruled.<verse eid="PSA 122:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 122:6"/>Pray that the people of Jerusalem might live peacefully! May the people who love you live prosperously!<verse eid="PSA 122:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 122:7"/>May those who live inside of the walls of the city live peacefully. May those who live in the fortresses live securely.<verse eid="PSA 122:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 122:8"/>For the sake of my relatives and friends, I will pray that those who live in the city might live peacefully.<verse eid="PSA 122:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 122:9"/>And because I love the temple of Yahweh our God, I desire that Yahweh will do good things for the people who live in Jerusalem.<verse eid="PSA 122:9"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 122"/>
<chapter number="123" style="c" sid="PSA 123"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 123:1"/>A psalm written for people going up to the temple to worship; Yahweh, I look up toward you, up to heaven, from where you rule.<verse eid="PSA 123:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 123:2"/>As servants ask their masters for what they need and as maids ask their mistresses for what they need, we ask you, Yahweh our God, for what we need, until you act mercifully toward us.<verse eid="PSA 123:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 123:3"/>Yahweh, act very mercifully toward us because our enemies have acted very contemptuously toward us.<verse eid="PSA 123:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 123:4"/>Arrogant people have made fun of us for a long time, and proud people have oppressed us and have acted as though we were worthless.<verse eid="PSA 123:4"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 123"/>
<chapter number="124" style="c" sid="PSA 124"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 124:1"/>A psalm written by David for people going up to the temple to worship. You Israelite people, answer this question: What would have happened to us if Yahweh had not been helping us?<verse eid="PSA 124:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 124:2"/>When our enemies attacked us, if Yahweh had not been fighting for us,<verse eid="PSA 124:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 124:3"/>we would have all been killed because they were very angry with us!<verse eid="PSA 124:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 124:4"/>They would have been like a flood of water sweeping us away; it would have been as though the water had covered us,<verse eid="PSA 124:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 124:5"/>and we would all have drowned in the flood.<verse eid="PSA 124:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 124:6"/>But we praise Yahweh because he has not allowed our enemies to destroy us.<verse eid="PSA 124:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 124:7"/>We have escaped from our enemies as a bird escapes from the trap that hunters have set; it is as though the trap that our enemies set for us was broken and we have escaped from it!<verse eid="PSA 124:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 124:8"/>Yahweh is the one who helps us; he is the one who made heaven and the earth.<verse eid="PSA 124:8"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 124"/>
<chapter number="125" style="c" sid="PSA 125"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 125:1"/>A psalm written for people going up to the temple to worship. Those who trust in Yahweh are like Mount Zion, which cannot be shaken or moved out of its place.<verse eid="PSA 125:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 125:2"/>As the hills that surround Jerusalem protect it, so Yahweh protects us, his people, and he will protect us forever.<verse eid="PSA 125:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 125:3"/>Wicked people should not be allowed to rule over the land where righteous people live. If they did that, those righteous people would think of doing wrong themselves.<verse eid="PSA 125:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 125:4"/>Yahweh, do good things to those who do good things to others and to those who sincerely obey your commands.<verse eid="PSA 125:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 125:5"/>But when you punish the Israelites who no longer obey you, you will punish them the same as you punish all the other evildoers. I wish that things may go well for people in Israel!<verse eid="PSA 125:5"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 125"/>
<chapter number="126" style="c" sid="PSA 126"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 126:1"/>A psalm written for people going up to the temple to worship. When Yahweh made Jerusalem prosperous again, it was wonderful; it seemed as though we were dreaming.<verse eid="PSA 126:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 126:2"/>We were extremely happy, and we continued shouting joyfully. Then the other people groups said about us, “Yahweh has done great things for them!”<verse eid="PSA 126:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 126:3"/>We said, “Yes, Yahweh truly has done great things for us, and we are very happy.”<verse eid="PSA 126:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 126:4"/>Restore us, O Yahweh, like the rains that fill the streams in the southern Judean wilderness. Enable our nation to become great again like it was before.<verse eid="PSA 126:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 126:5"/>We cried when we planted seeds because it was hard work preparing the soil that had not been plowed for many years; now we want to shout joyfully because we are gathering a big harvest.<verse eid="PSA 126:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 126:6"/>Those who cried as they carried the bags of seeds to the fields will shout joyfully when they bring the crops to their houses at harvest time.<verse eid="PSA 126:6"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 126"/>
<chapter number="127" style="c" sid="PSA 127"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 127:1"/>A psalm written by Solomon for people going up to the temple to worship. If people are building a house without Yahweh helping them, they are building it in vain. Similarly, if Yahweh does not protect a city, it is useless for guards to stay awake at night.<verse eid="PSA 127:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 127:2"/>It is also useless to arise very early and go to sleep late at night so that you can work hard all day to earn money to buy food because Yahweh gives food to those whom he loves even while they sleep.<verse eid="PSA 127:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 127:3"/>Children are a gift that comes to parents from Yahweh; they are a reward from him.<verse eid="PSA 127:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 127:4"/>If a man has sons while he is still young, when they grow up, they will be able to help him defend his family as a soldier can defend himself if he has a bow and arrows in his hand.<verse eid="PSA 127:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 127:5"/>How fortunate is a man who has many sons; he is like a soldier who has many arrows in his quiver. If a man with his many grown sons is taken by his enemies to the place where they decide matters, his enemies will never be able to defeat that man because his sons will help to defend him.<verse eid="PSA 127:5"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 127"/>
<chapter number="128" style="c" sid="PSA 128"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 128:1"/>A psalm written for those going up to the temple to worship. How fortunate are you who have an awesome respect for him and do what he wants you to do.<verse eid="PSA 128:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 128:2"/>You will be able to enjoy the food you provide yourself with; you will be fortunate and prosperous.<verse eid="PSA 128:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 128:3"/>Your wife will be like a grapevine that bears many grapes; she will give birth to many children. Your children who sit around your table; you will be like a strong olive tree that has many shoots growing up around it.<verse eid="PSA 128:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 128:4"/>Like that, Yahweh will bless every man who has an awesome respect for him.<verse eid="PSA 128:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 128:5"/>I wish that God in his temple on Mount Zion may help you greatly, and that you will see the people of Jerusalem prospering every day that you live!<verse eid="PSA 128:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 128:6"/>I wish that you may live many years and that you may have grandchildren and be able to see them. I wish that things may go well for people in Israel!<verse eid="PSA 128:6"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 128"/>
<chapter number="129" style="c" sid="PSA 129"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 129:1"/>A psalm written for people going up to the temple to worship. I say that my enemies have afflicted me ever since I was young. Now I ask you, my fellow Israelites, to repeat those same words:<verse eid="PSA 129:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 129:2"/>“Our enemies have afflicted us since our nation began, but they have not defeated us!<verse eid="PSA 129:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 129:3"/>Our enemies struck us with whips that cut into our backs as a farmer uses a plow to cuts deep furrows into the ground.”<verse eid="PSA 129:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 129:4"/>But Yahweh is righteous, and he has freed us from being slaves to wicked people.<verse eid="PSA 129:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 129:5"/>I wish that they may all be shamed because we will defeat them—all of Jerusalem’s enemies.<verse eid="PSA 129:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 129:6"/>I hope that they may be of no value, like grass that grows on the roofs of houses, that dries up and does not grow tall;<verse eid="PSA 129:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 129:7"/>no one wants to cut it and tie it up as bundles and carry it away.<verse eid="PSA 129:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 129:8"/>People who pass by and see men harvesting grain usually greet them by saying to them, “We wish that Yahweh may bless you!” But this will not happen to the enemies of Israel. We, acting as Yahweh’s representatives, bless you, our fellow Israelites!<verse eid="PSA 129:8"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 129"/>
<chapter number="130" style="c" sid="PSA 130"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 130:1"/>A psalm written for people going up to the temple to worship. Yahweh, I have great troubles, so I call out to you.<verse eid="PSA 130:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 130:2"/>Yahweh, hear me while I call out to you to have mercy on me!<verse eid="PSA 130:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 130:3"/>Yahweh, if you kept a record of the sins that we have committed, not one of us would escape from being condemned and punished!<verse eid="PSA 130:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 130:4"/>But you forgive us, with the result that we have an awesome respect for you.<verse eid="PSA 130:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 130:5"/>Yahweh has said that he would help me; I trust what he said, and I wait eagerly for him to do that.<verse eid="PSA 130:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 130:6"/>I wait for Yahweh to help me more than watchmen wait for the morning to come; yes, I wait more eagerly than they do!<verse eid="PSA 130:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 130:7"/>You, my fellow Israelites, confidently expect that Yahweh will bless us. He will bless us because he has mercy on us, and he is very willing to save us.<verse eid="PSA 130:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 130:8"/>It is he who will save us Israelite people from being punished for all the sins that we have committed.<verse eid="PSA 130:8"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 130"/>
<chapter number="131" style="c" sid="PSA 131"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 131:1"/>A psalm written by David for people going up to the temple to worship. Yahweh, I am not proud; I do not deserve to achieve impressive things in life. I do not worry about problems that are too difficult for me to solve.<verse eid="PSA 131:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 131:2"/>Instead, I am calm and peaceful in my inner being like a small child who no longer nurses but is happy to be with its mother. In the same way, I am peaceful within my inner being.<verse eid="PSA 131:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 131:3"/>You, my fellow Israelites, confidently expect that Yahweh will do good things for you now and forever!<verse eid="PSA 131:3"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 131"/>
<chapter number="132" style="c" sid="PSA 132"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 132:1"/>A song to sing along the road up to Jerusalem. Yahweh, do not forget King David and all the hardships he endured!<verse eid="PSA 132:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 132:2"/>He made a solemn promise to you, the mighty God whom our ancestor Jacob worshiped.<verse eid="PSA 132:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 132:3"/>He said, “I will not go home, I will not rest on my bed,<verse eid="PSA 132:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 132:4"/>and I will not sleep at all<verse eid="PSA 132:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 132:5"/>until I build a place for Yahweh, a home for the mighty God whom Jacob worshiped.”<verse eid="PSA 132:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 132:6"/>In Ephrathah we heard where the sacred chest was. So we went and found it near the city of Kiriath Jearim, and we took it to Jerusalem.<verse eid="PSA 132:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 132:7"/>Later we said, “Let us go to the sacred tent of Yahweh in Jerusalem; let us worship there in front of the throne where he is sitting.”<verse eid="PSA 132:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 132:8"/>Yahweh, come to the place where you live eternally, to the place where your sacred chest is, to the place that shows that you are very powerful.<verse eid="PSA 132:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 132:9"/>I want that the righteous behavior of your priests will always be evident, and that your people will always shout joyfully.<verse eid="PSA 132:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 132:10"/>You chose David to serve you as king of Israel; do not reject him!<verse eid="PSA 132:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 132:11"/>Yahweh, you made a solemn promise to David, a promise that you will not break. You said, “I will cause your descendants to rule as kings like you.<verse eid="PSA 132:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 132:12"/>If they obey my covenant with them and obey all the commands that I will give them, the line of kings descended from you will never end.”<verse eid="PSA 132:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 132:13"/>Yahweh has chosen Jerusalem; that is where he wants to rule from.<verse eid="PSA 132:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 132:14"/>He said, “This is the city where I will live forever; this is the place where I want to stay.<verse eid="PSA 132:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 132:15"/>I will give to the people of Jerusalem all that they need; I will give enough food to satisfy even the poor people there.<verse eid="PSA 132:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 132:16"/>I will cause the priests to behave in a manner worthy of ones whom I have saved; and all my people who live there will shout joyfully.<verse eid="PSA 132:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 132:17"/>There in Jerusalem I will cause one of David’s descendants to become a great king; he also will be my chosen king, It is there that I will make David’s line of descendants continue.<verse eid="PSA 132:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 132:18"/>I will defeat his enemies and cause them to be very ashamed; but the crown that my king wears will always shine.”<verse eid="PSA 132:18"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 132"/>
<chapter number="133" style="c" sid="PSA 133"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 133:1"/>A psalm written for people going up to the temple to worship. It is very good and very pleasant for God’s people to gather together in peace.<verse eid="PSA 133:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 133:2"/>It is as delightful as the precious oil that ran down from the high priest Aaron’s head onto his beard when Moses anointed him, that ran down onto the collar of his robes.<verse eid="PSA 133:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 133:3"/>Gathering together in peace is as delightful as the dew that falls on Mount Hermon and the dew that falls on Mount Zion. Yahweh has promised to bless his people there in Jerusalem by making their nation last forever.<verse eid="PSA 133:3"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 133"/>
<chapter number="134" style="c" sid="PSA 134"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 134:1"/>A psalm written for people going up to the temple to worship. All you people who serve Yahweh, who stand up and serve him at night in his temple, come and praise him!<verse eid="PSA 134:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 134:2"/>Lift up your hands to pray to him in the temple and praise him!<verse eid="PSA 134:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 134:3"/>I hope that Yahweh, who created heaven and the earth, may bless you from where he lives in the temple on Mount Zion!<verse eid="PSA 134:3"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 134"/>
<chapter number="135" style="c" sid="PSA 135"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 135:1"/>Praise Yahweh! You who worship Yahweh, praise him!<verse eid="PSA 135:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 135:2"/>You who stand at the temple of Yahweh our God in its courtyards, ready to serve him, praise him !<verse eid="PSA 135:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 135:3"/>Praise Yahweh because he does good things for us; sing to him because it is a joyful thing to do so.<verse eid="PSA 135:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 135:4"/>He has chosen us, the descendants of Jacob; he has chosen us Israelites to belong to him.<verse eid="PSA 135:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 135:5"/>I say these things because I know that Yahweh is great; he is greater than all the gods.<verse eid="PSA 135:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 135:6"/>Yahweh does whatever he desires to do in heaven, on the earth, and in the seas, down to the bottom of the seas.<verse eid="PSA 135:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 135:7"/>He is the one who causes clouds to appear from very distant places on the earth; he makes lightning bolts to flash with the rain, and he brings the winds from the places where he stores them.<verse eid="PSA 135:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 135:8"/>He is the one who killed all the firstborn males in Egypt, the firstborn of people and of animals.<verse eid="PSA 135:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 135:9"/>There he performed many kinds of miracles to punish the king and all his officials.<verse eid="PSA 135:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 135:10"/>He attacked many nations and killed the powerful kings who ruled them:<verse eid="PSA 135:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 135:11"/>Sihon, the king of the Amor people group, Og, the king of Bashan, and all the other kings in the land of Canaan.<verse eid="PSA 135:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 135:12"/>Yahweh gave us their land, so that it would belong to us, his people Israel, forever.<verse eid="PSA 135:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 135:13"/>Yahweh, your name will endure forever, and people who are not yet born will remember the great things that you have done.<verse eid="PSA 135:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 135:14"/>Yahweh declares that we, his people, are innocent, and he acts mercifully toward us.<verse eid="PSA 135:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 135:15"/>But the idols that the other people groups worship are only statues made of silver and gold, things that humans have made.<verse eid="PSA 135:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 135:16"/>Their idols have mouths, but they cannot say anything; they have eyes, but they cannot see anything.<verse eid="PSA 135:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 135:17"/>They have ears, but they cannot hear anything, and they are not even able to breathe.<verse eid="PSA 135:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 135:18"/>The people who make those idols are as powerless as those idols, and those who trust in those idols can accomplish no more than their idols can!<verse eid="PSA 135:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 135:19"/>My fellow Israelites, praise Yahweh! You priests who are descended from Aaron, praise Yahweh!<verse eid="PSA 135:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 135:20"/>You men who are descended from Levi, you who assist the priests, praise Yahweh! All you who have a reverential respect for Yahweh, praise him!<verse eid="PSA 135:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 135:21"/>Praise Yahweh in the temple on Mount Zion in Jerusalem where he lives! Praise Yahweh!<verse eid="PSA 135:21"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 135"/>
<chapter number="136" style="c" sid="PSA 136"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 136:1"/>Thank Yahweh because he does good things for us; he will love us forever as he has promised.<verse eid="PSA 136:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 136:2"/>Thank God, the one who is greater than all other gods; he will love us forever as he has promised.<verse eid="PSA 136:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 136:3"/>Thank the Lord who is greater than all other lords; he will love us forever as he has promised.<verse eid="PSA 136:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 136:4"/>He is the only one who performs great miracles; he will love us forever as he has promised.<verse eid="PSA 136:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 136:5"/>He is the one who, by being very wise, created the heavens; he will love us forever as he has promised.<verse eid="PSA 136:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 136:6"/>He is the one who caused the ground to rise up above the deep waters; he will love us forever as he has promised.<verse eid="PSA 136:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 136:7"/>He is the one who created great lights in the sky; he will love us forever as he has promised.<verse eid="PSA 136:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 136:8"/>He created the sun to shine in the daytime; he will love us forever as he has promised.<verse eid="PSA 136:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 136:9"/>He created the moon and stars to shine during the nighttime; he will love us forever as he has promised.<verse eid="PSA 136:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 136:10"/>He is the one who killed the firstborn males in Egypt; he will love us forever as he has promised.<verse eid="PSA 136:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 136:11"/>He led the Israelite people out of Egypt; he will love us forever as he has promised.<verse eid="PSA 136:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 136:12"/>With his strong hand he led them out; he will love us forever as he has promised.<verse eid="PSA 136:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 136:13"/>He is the one who caused the Sea of Reeds to divide; he will love us forever as he has promised.<verse eid="PSA 136:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 136:14"/>He enabled the Israelite people to walk through it on dry land; he will love us forever as he has promised.<verse eid="PSA 136:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 136:15"/>But he caused the king of Egypt and his army to drown in it; he will love us forever as he has promised.<verse eid="PSA 136:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 136:16"/>He is the one who led his people safely through the wilderness; he will love us forever as he has promised.<verse eid="PSA 136:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 136:17"/>He killed powerful kings; he will love us forever as he has promised.<verse eid="PSA 136:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 136:18"/>He killed kings who were famous; he will love us forever as he has promised.<verse eid="PSA 136:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 136:19"/>He killed Sihon, the king of the Amor people group; he will love us forever as he has promised.<verse eid="PSA 136:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 136:20"/>He killed Og, the king of the region of Bashan; he will love us forever as he has promised.<verse eid="PSA 136:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 136:21"/>He gave their lands to us, his people; he will love us forever as he has promised.<verse eid="PSA 136:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 136:22"/>He gave those lands to us people of Israel, who serve him; he will love us forever as he has promised.<verse eid="PSA 136:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 136:23"/>He is the one who did not forget about us when our enemies had defeated us; he will love us forever as he has promised.<verse eid="PSA 136:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 136:24"/>He rescued us from our enemies; he will love us forever as he has promised.<verse eid="PSA 136:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 136:25"/>He is the one who gives food to all living creatures; he will love us forever as he has promised.<verse eid="PSA 136:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 136:26"/>So thank God, who lives in heaven because he will love us forever as he has promised.!<verse eid="PSA 136:26"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 136"/>
<chapter number="137" style="c" sid="PSA 137"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 137:1"/>When we had been taken to Babylonia far from Jerusalem, we sat down by the rivers there, and we cried when we thought about the temple on Mount Zion in Jerusalem.<verse eid="PSA 137:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 137:2"/>On the willow trees alongside the rivers we hung our harps because we did not want to play them anymore and because we were very sad.<verse eid="PSA 137:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 137:3"/>The soldiers who had captured us and taken us to Babylonia forced us to sing for them; they told us to entertain them; they said, “Sing for us one of the songs that you previously sang in Jerusalem!”<verse eid="PSA 137:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 137:4"/>But we thought to ourselves, “We are sad because we have been punished by Yahweh and brought to this foreign land; we cannot sing songs about Yahweh while we are here!”<verse eid="PSA 137:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 137:5"/>If I forget about Jerusalem, I hope that my right hand will wither so that I will be unable to play my harp!<verse eid="PSA 137:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 137:6"/>I hope that I will not be able to sing again if I forget about Jerusalem, if I do not consider that Jerusalem causes me to be more joyful than anything else does.<verse eid="PSA 137:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 137:7"/>Yahweh, punish the people of the Edom people group for what they did on the day that the army of Babylon captured Jerusalem. Do not forget that they said, “Tear down all the buildings! Destroy them completely! Leave only the foundations!”<verse eid="PSA 137:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 137:8"/>You people of Babylon, you will certainly be destroyed! How fortunate are those who punish you for what you did to us;<verse eid="PSA 137:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 137:9"/>How fortunate are those who take your babies and smash them to pieces on the rocks.<verse eid="PSA 137:9"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 137"/>
<chapter number="138" style="c" sid="PSA 138"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 138:1"/>A psalm written by David. Yahweh, I thank you with all my inner being. I sing to praise you, even though many people worship idols.<verse eid="PSA 138:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 138:2"/>When I look toward your sacred temple, I bow down and thank you because you faithfully love us and do all that you have promised. You have given cause for people everywhere to honor you and what you have said more than anything else.<verse eid="PSA 138:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 138:3"/>When I called out to you, you answered me; you enabled me to be strong and brave.<verse eid="PSA 138:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 138:4"/>Yahweh, someday all the kings of this earth will praise you because they will have heard what you have said.<verse eid="PSA 138:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 138:5"/>They will sing about what you have done; they will sing and say that you are very great.<verse eid="PSA 138:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 138:6"/>Yahweh, you are supreme, but you take care of people who are considered to be unimportant. However, you do not show yourself to proud people as faithful.<verse eid="PSA 138:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 138:7"/>When I am in the middle of many troubles, you save me. With your hand you rescue me from my enemies who are angry at me.<verse eid="PSA 138:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 138:8"/>Yahweh, you will do for me everything that you promised; you faithfully love us forever. Finish what you started to do for us, your Israelite people!<verse eid="PSA 138:8"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 138"/>
<chapter number="139" style="c" sid="PSA 139"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 139:1"/>A psalm written by David for the choir director. Yahweh, you have examined what is in my inner being, and you know everything about me.<verse eid="PSA 139:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 139:2"/>You know when I sit down and when I stand up. Even though you are far away from me, you know what I am thinking.<verse eid="PSA 139:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 139:3"/>From the time that I rise in the morning until I lie down to sleep at night, you know everything that I do.<verse eid="PSA 139:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 139:4"/>Yahweh, even before I say anything, you know everything that I am going to say!<verse eid="PSA 139:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 139:5"/>You protect me on all sides; you put your hand on me to protect me with your power.<verse eid="PSA 139:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 139:6"/>I am not able to understand that you know everything about me. That is too hard for me to really understand.<verse eid="PSA 139:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 139:7"/>Where could I go to escape from your Spirit? Where could I go to get away from you?<verse eid="PSA 139:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 139:8"/>If I go up to heaven, you will be there. If I lie down in the place where the dead people are, you will be there.<verse eid="PSA 139:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 139:9"/>If the sun could carry me across the sky, if I flew west and made a place to live on an island in the ocean,<verse eid="PSA 139:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 139:10"/>you would be there also to lead me by your hand, and you would help me.<verse eid="PSA 139:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 139:11"/>I could wish for the darkness to hide me, or I could wish for the light around me to become darkness.<verse eid="PSA 139:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 139:12"/>But even if that happened, you would still see me. For you the night is as bright as the daytime, because daylight and darkness are no different to you.<verse eid="PSA 139:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 139:13"/>You created all the parts of my body; you put the parts of my body together when I was still in my mother’s womb.<verse eid="PSA 139:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 139:14"/>I praise you because you made my body very awesomely and wonderfully. Everything that you do is amazing! I certainly know that very well.<verse eid="PSA 139:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 139:15"/>When my body was being formed, while it was being put together where no one else could see it, you saw it!<verse eid="PSA 139:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 139:16"/>You saw me before I was born. You wrote in your book the number of days that you had decided that I would live. You did that before any of those days had even started!<verse eid="PSA 139:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 139:17"/>God, what you think about me is very valuable. There are a huge amount of things that you think about.<verse eid="PSA 139:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 139:18"/>If I could count them, I would see that they are more than the grains of sand at the seashore. When I awake, I am still with you.<verse eid="PSA 139:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 139:19"/>God, I wish that you would kill the wicked people! I wish that violent men would all leave me.<verse eid="PSA 139:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 139:20"/>They say wicked things about you; they slander your name.<verse eid="PSA 139:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 139:21"/>Yahweh, I certainly hate those who hate you! I despise those who rebel against you.<verse eid="PSA 139:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 139:22"/>I hate them completely, and I consider that they are my enemies.<verse eid="PSA 139:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 139:23"/>God, search my inner being; find out what I am thinking!<verse eid="PSA 139:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 139:24"/>Find out whether there is anything evil in my inner being, and lead me along the road that leads to my being with you forever.<verse eid="PSA 139:24"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 139"/>
<chapter number="140" style="c" sid="PSA 140"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 140:1"/>A psalm written by David. Yahweh, rescue me from being attacked by evil men; even more, keep me safe from being attacked by violent people.<verse eid="PSA 140:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 140:2"/>They are always planning to do evil things, and they are always encouraging people to start quarrels.<verse eid="PSA 140:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 140:3"/>By what they say, they injure people as poisonous snakes do.<verse eid="PSA 140:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 140:4"/>Yahweh, protect me from the power of wicked people. Keep me safe from violent men who plan to ruin me.<verse eid="PSA 140:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 140:5"/>It is as though proud people have set a trap for me; it is as though they have spread their nets to catch me; it is as though they have put these things along the road to catch me.<verse eid="PSA 140:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 140:6"/>I say to you, “Yahweh, you are my God. Listen to me while I cry out to you to help me.”<verse eid="PSA 140:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 140:7"/>Yahweh, my Lord, you are the one who strongly defends me; you have protected me during battles as though you had put a helmet on my head.<verse eid="PSA 140:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 140:8"/>Yahweh, do not give to wicked people the things that they desire, and do not allow them to do the evil things that they plan to do.<verse eid="PSA 140:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 140:9"/>Do not allow my enemies to become proud; cause the evil things that they say they will do to me to happen to them instead.<verse eid="PSA 140:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 140:10"/>Cause burning coals to fall on their heads! Cause them to be thrown into deep pits from which they cannot climb out!<verse eid="PSA 140:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 140:11"/>Do not allow those who slander others to succeed; cause evil things to happen to violent men and destroy them!<verse eid="PSA 140:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 140:12"/>Yahweh, I know that you will defend those who are oppressed, and that you will do what is just.<verse eid="PSA 140:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 140:13"/>Righteous people will surely thank you, and they will live in your presence.<verse eid="PSA 140:13"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 140"/>
<chapter number="141" style="c" sid="PSA 141"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 141:1"/>A psalm written by David. Yahweh, I call out to you; please help me quickly! Listen to me when I am calling to you.<verse eid="PSA 141:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 141:2"/>Accept my prayer as though it were incense being burned as an offering to you. Accept me while I lift up my hands to pray to you, just as you accept sacrifices that are offered to you in the evening.<verse eid="PSA 141:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 141:3"/>Yahweh, do not allow me to say things that are wrong; guard what I say as a sentry guards a door.<verse eid="PSA 141:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 141:4"/>Prevent me from wanting to do anything that is wrong and from joining with wicked men when they want to do evil deeds. Do not even allow me to share in eating delightful food with them!<verse eid="PSA 141:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 141:5"/>It is all right if righteous people strike me or rebuke me because they are trying to act kindly toward me to teach me to do what is right; if they do that, it will be as if someone honored me by anointing my head with olive oil; but I am always praying that you will punish the wicked because of the wicked deeds that they do.<verse eid="PSA 141:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 141:6"/>When their rulers are thrown down from the top of rocky cliffs, they will know that what I am saying here is good.<verse eid="PSA 141:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 141:7"/>They will know one day that their bodies will lie scattered on the ground in the place of the dead, just as one scatters clods of earth when he plows a field.<verse eid="PSA 141:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 141:8"/>But Yahweh God, I continue to request that you help me. I ask you to protect me; do not allow me to die now!<verse eid="PSA 141:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 141:9"/>It is as though people have set traps for me; protect me from falling into those traps. It is as though they have spread nets to catch me; keep me from being caught in those nets.<verse eid="PSA 141:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 141:10"/>I wish that wicked people may fall into the traps they have set to catch me while I escape from them.<verse eid="PSA 141:10"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 141"/>
<chapter number="142" style="c" sid="PSA 142"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 142:1"/>A psalm that David prayed when he was hiding in a cave. Yahweh, I cry out to you; I plead for you to help me.<verse eid="PSA 142:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 142:2"/>I am bringing to you all my problems; I am telling you all my troubles.<verse eid="PSA 142:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 142:3"/>When I am very discouraged, you know what I should do. Wherever I walk, it is as though my enemies have hidden traps for me to fall into.<verse eid="PSA 142:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 142:4"/>I look around, but there is no one who sees me, no one who will protect me, and no one who cares about what happens to me.<verse eid="PSA 142:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 142:5"/>So Yahweh, I cry out to you to help me; you are the one who protects me; you are all that I need while I am alive.<verse eid="PSA 142:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 142:6"/>Listen to me while I cry out to you for help because I am very distressed. Rescue me because those who make me suffer are very strong; I cannot escape from them.<verse eid="PSA 142:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 142:7"/>Free me from my troubles so that I may thank you. If you do that, when I am with others who live rightly, I will praise you for having been very good to me.<verse eid="PSA 142:7"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 142"/>
<chapter number="143" style="c" sid="PSA 143"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 143:1"/>A psalm written by David. Yahweh, hear me while I pray to you! Because you are righteous and because you faithfully do what you have promised, listen to what I am pleading for you to do for me.<verse eid="PSA 143:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 143:2"/>I am one who worships you; do not judge me because you do not consider anyone to be completely innocent.<verse eid="PSA 143:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 143:3"/>My enemies have pursued me; they have completely defeated me. It is as though they have put me in a dark prison where I have nothing good to hope for.<verse eid="PSA 143:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 143:4"/>So I am very discouraged in my inner being; I am very dismayed.<verse eid="PSA 143:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 143:5"/>I remember what has happened previously; I meditate on all the things that you have done; I consider all the great deeds that you have performed.<verse eid="PSA 143:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 143:6"/>I lift up my hands to you while I pray; I want very much to be with you as much as I would thirst for water in a vast wilderness.<verse eid="PSA 143:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 143:7"/>Yahweh, I am very discouraged, so please answer me right now! Do not keep away from me because if you do that, I will soon be among those who descend to where the dead people are.<verse eid="PSA 143:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 143:8"/>Every morning cause me to remember that you faithfully love me because I trust in you. I pray to you; show me the things that I should do.<verse eid="PSA 143:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 143:9"/>Yahweh, I have gone to you for you to protect me, so rescue me from my enemies.<verse eid="PSA 143:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 143:10"/>You are my God; teach me to do what you want me to do. I want your good Spirit to show me the right things to do.<verse eid="PSA 143:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 143:11"/>Yahweh, restore me when I am close to dying as you promised to do because you are righteous!<verse eid="PSA 143:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 143:12"/>I am one who serves you; so because you faithfully love me as you promised to do, kill my enemies and get rid of all those who oppress me.<verse eid="PSA 143:12"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 143"/>
<chapter number="144" style="c" sid="PSA 144"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 144:1"/>Written by David; I praise Yahweh, who is like a huge rock on which I am safe! He trains my hands so that I can use them to fight battles; he trains my fingers so that I can shoot arrows in a war.<verse eid="PSA 144:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 144:2"/>He is the one who protects me as he promised; he is like a fortress in which I am safe, he protects me as shields protect soldiers, and he gives me refuge. He defeats other nations and then puts them under my power.<verse eid="PSA 144:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 144:3"/>Yahweh, we people are so insignificant! Why do you notice us? It is amazing to me that you pay attention to humans.<verse eid="PSA 144:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 144:4"/>The time that we live is as short as a puff of wind; our time to live disappears as a shadow does.<verse eid="PSA 144:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 144:5"/>Yahweh, tear open the sky and come down! Touch the mountains so that smoke may pour out from them!<verse eid="PSA 144:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 144:6"/>Cause lightning to flash with the result that your enemies will run away! Shoot your arrows at them and cause them to run away in panic.<verse eid="PSA 144:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 144:7"/>It is as though my enemies are like a flood around me; reach your hand down from heaven and rescue me from them. They are men from foreign countries<verse eid="PSA 144:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 144:8"/>who always tell lies. Even when they swear to tell the truth, they tell lies.<verse eid="PSA 144:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 144:9"/>God, I will sing a new song to you, and I will play my ten-stringed harp while I sing to you.<verse eid="PSA 144:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 144:10"/>You enable kings to defeat their enemies; you rescue those who serve you as I did.<verse eid="PSA 144:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 144:11"/>So I ask you to save me from being killed by the swords that those evil people carry. Rescue me from the power of those men from foreign countries who always tell lies. Even when they swear to tell the truth, they tell lies.<verse eid="PSA 144:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 144:12"/>I wish that our sons may all grow to full adulthood; I wish that our daughters may grow up to be as straight and tall as the pillars that stand in the corners of palaces.<verse eid="PSA 144:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 144:13"/>I wish that our barns may be full of many different crops. I wish that the sheep in our fields may give birth to tens of thousands of baby lambs.<verse eid="PSA 144:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 144:14"/>I wish that our cattle may give birth to many calves without having any miscarriages or deaths when they are born. I wish that there may not be any time when the people in our streets cry out in distress because foreign armies are invading.<verse eid="PSA 144:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 144:15"/>If good things like that happen to a nation, the people will be very fortunate. How fortunate are those who worship Yahweh as God!<verse eid="PSA 144:15"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 144"/>
<chapter number="145" style="c" sid="PSA 145"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 145:1"/>A psalm written by David to praise God. My God and King, I will proclaim that you are very great; I will praise you now and forever.<verse eid="PSA 145:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 145:2"/>Every day I will praise you; Yes, I will praise you forever.<verse eid="PSA 145:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 145:3"/>Yahweh, you are great, and you ought to be praised very much; we cannot fully realize how great you are.<verse eid="PSA 145:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 145:4"/>Parents will tell their children the things that you have done; they will tell their children about your mighty deeds.<verse eid="PSA 145:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 145:5"/>I will think about how you are very glorious and majestic, and I will meditate on all your wonderful deeds.<verse eid="PSA 145:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 145:6"/>People will speak about your powerful and awesome deeds, and I will proclaim that you are very great.<verse eid="PSA 145:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 145:7"/>People will remember and proclaim that you are very good to us, and they will sing joyfully that you always act justly.<verse eid="PSA 145:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 145:8"/>Yahweh, you act kindly and mercifully toward us; you do not quickly become angry; you faithfully love us very much as you have promised to do.<verse eid="PSA 145:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 145:9"/>Yahweh, you are good to everyone, and you act mercifully to everything that you have made.<verse eid="PSA 145:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 145:10"/>Yahweh, all the creatures that you made will thank you, and all your people will praise you.<verse eid="PSA 145:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 145:11"/>They will tell others that you rule very gloriously as our king and that you are very powerful.<verse eid="PSA 145:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 145:12"/>They will do that so that everyone will know about your powerful deeds and that you rule over us gloriously.<verse eid="PSA 145:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 145:13"/>You will never stop being king; you will rule throughout all generations.<verse eid="PSA 145:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 145:14"/>Yahweh, you help all those who are discouraged, and you lift up all those who have lost hope.<verse eid="PSA 145:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 145:15"/>All of the creatures that you made expect that you will provide food for them, and you give them food when they need it.<verse eid="PSA 145:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 145:16"/>You give food to all living creatures generously, and you cause them to be satisfied.<verse eid="PSA 145:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 145:17"/>Everything that Yahweh does, he does justly; all that he does, he does mercifully.<verse eid="PSA 145:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 145:18"/>Yahweh comes near to all those who call out to him, to those who call to him sincerely.<verse eid="PSA 145:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 145:19"/>To all those who have an awesome respect for him he gives what they need. He hears them when they cry out to him and saves them.<verse eid="PSA 145:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 145:20"/>Yahweh protects all those who love him, but he will get rid of all the wicked people.<verse eid="PSA 145:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 145:21"/>I will always praise Yahweh; I wish that all people everywhere may praise him forever, for he does everything perfectly.<verse eid="PSA 145:21"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 145"/>
<chapter number="146" style="c" sid="PSA 146"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 146:1"/>Praise Yahweh. With my whole inner being I will praise Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 146:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 146:2"/>I will praise Yahweh as long as I am alive; I will sing to praise my God all the rest of my life.<verse eid="PSA 146:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 146:3"/>You people, do not trust in your leaders; do not trust humans because they cannot save.<verse eid="PSA 146:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 146:4"/>When they die, their corpses decay and become soil again. After they die, they can no longer do the things that they planned to do.<verse eid="PSA 146:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 146:5"/>But how fortunate are those whom God helps, the God whom Jacob worshiped. These are the people who confidently expect Yahweh, their God, to help them.<verse eid="PSA 146:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 146:6"/>He is the one who created the heavens and the earth, the oceans and all the creatures that are in them. He always does what he has promised to do.<verse eid="PSA 146:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 146:7"/>He decides matters fairly for those who are treated unfairly, and he provides food for those who are hungry. He frees those who are in prison.<verse eid="PSA 146:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 146:8"/>Yahweh enables those who are blind to see again. He lifts up those who have fallen down. He loves the righteous people.<verse eid="PSA 146:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 146:9"/>Yahweh takes care of those from other countries who live in our land, and he helps widows and orphans. But he stops wicked people from what they are doing.<verse eid="PSA 146:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 146:10"/>Yahweh will continue to be our king forever; you people of Israel, your God will rule forever! Praise Yahweh!<verse eid="PSA 146:10"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 146"/>
<chapter number="147" style="c" sid="PSA 147"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 147:1"/>Praise Yahweh! It is good to sing praises to our God. It is a delightful thing to do and the right thing to do.<verse eid="PSA 147:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 147:2"/>Jerusalem was destroyed, but Yahweh is enabling us to build Jerusalem again. He is bringing back the people who were taken to other lands.<verse eid="PSA 147:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 147:3"/>He enables those who were very discouraged to be encouraged again; it is as though they have wounds and he bandages them.<verse eid="PSA 147:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 147:4"/>He has determined how many stars there will be and gives names to all of them.<verse eid="PSA 147:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 147:5"/>Yahweh is great and very powerful, and no one can measure how much he understands.<verse eid="PSA 147:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 147:6"/>Yahweh lifts up those who have been oppressed, and he throws the wicked down to the ground.<verse eid="PSA 147:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 147:7"/>Thank Yahweh while you are singing to him to praise him; on the harps, play music to our God.<verse eid="PSA 147:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 147:8"/>He covers the sky with clouds, and then he sends rain to the earth and causes grass to grow on the hills.<verse eid="PSA 147:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 147:9"/>He gives to animals the food that they need; he gives food to young crows when they cry out because they are hungry.<verse eid="PSA 147:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 147:10"/>He is not impressed with strong horses or with men who can run fast.<verse eid="PSA 147:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 147:11"/>Instead, what pleases him are those who have an awesome respect for him, those who confidently expect him to continue to love them as he promised to do.<verse eid="PSA 147:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 147:12"/>You people of Jerusalem, praise Yahweh! Praise your God!<verse eid="PSA 147:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 147:13"/>He guards your city by keeping its gates strong. He blesses the people who live there.<verse eid="PSA 147:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 147:14"/>He causes your people to become wealthy. He gives you plenty of very good wheat to eat.<verse eid="PSA 147:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 147:15"/>He commands things to happen throughout the earth; his words quickly reach the place to which he sends them.<verse eid="PSA 147:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 147:16"/>He sends snow to cover the ground like a white wool blanket, and he scatters frost on the ground as wind scatters ashes.<verse eid="PSA 147:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 147:17"/>He sends hail down like pebbles; when that happens, it is very difficult to endure because the air becomes very cold.<verse eid="PSA 147:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 147:18"/>But he commands the wind to blow, and it blows. Then the hail melts and the water flows into the streams.<verse eid="PSA 147:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 147:19"/>He sends his message to the descendants of Jacob; he tells to his Israelite people the things that he has decreed and what he has decided.<verse eid="PSA 147:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 147:20"/>He has not done that for any other nation; the other nations do not know his laws. Praise Yahweh!<verse eid="PSA 147:20"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 147"/>
<chapter number="148" style="c" sid="PSA 148"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 148:1"/>Praise Yahweh! Praise him, you angels who are in the heavens; praise him, you angels up in the sky!<verse eid="PSA 148:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 148:2"/>All you angels who belong to him, praise him! All you who are in the armies of Yahweh, praise him!<verse eid="PSA 148:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 148:3"/>Sun and moon, you also must praise him! You shining stars, you praise him!<verse eid="PSA 148:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 148:4"/>You highest heavens, praise him! You waters that are high above the sky, praise him!<verse eid="PSA 148:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 148:5"/>I want all of these to praise Yahweh because by commanding that they exist, he created them.<verse eid="PSA 148:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 148:6"/>He set them in place; he commanded that they should be there forever. They cannot disobey that command!<verse eid="PSA 148:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 148:7"/>Everything on the earth, praise Yahweh! You huge creatures and everything else that is deep in the ocean,<verse eid="PSA 148:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 148:8"/>fire and hail, snow and frost, and strong winds that obey what he commands, I tell all of you to praise Yahweh!<verse eid="PSA 148:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 148:9"/>Hills and mountains, fruit trees and cedar trees,<verse eid="PSA 148:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 148:10"/>all the wild animals and all tame animals, reptiles and other things that creep on the ground, and all the birds, I tell all of you to praise Yahweh!<verse eid="PSA 148:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 148:11"/>You kings on this earth and all the people that you rule, you princes and all other rulers,<verse eid="PSA 148:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 148:12"/>you young men and young women, you old people and children, everyone, praise Yahweh!<verse eid="PSA 148:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 148:13"/>I want them all to praise Yahweh because he is greater than anyone else. His power controls everything on the earth and in the heavens.<verse eid="PSA 148:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 148:14"/>He caused us, his people, to be strong so that we Israelite people who are very precious to him should praise him, So praise Yahweh!<verse eid="PSA 148:14"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 148"/>
<chapter number="149" style="c" sid="PSA 149"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 149:1"/>Praise Yahweh! Sing a new song to Yahweh; praise him whenever his faithful people gather together!<verse eid="PSA 149:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 149:2"/>You Israelite people, be glad because of what God, who created you, has done for you! You people of Jerusalem, rejoice because of what God, your king, has done for you!<verse eid="PSA 149:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 149:3"/>Praise Yahweh by dancing, by beating tambourines, and by playing harps to praise him!<verse eid="PSA 149:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 149:4"/>Yahweh is pleased with his people; he honors humble people by helping them to defeat their enemies.<verse eid="PSA 149:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 149:5"/>Because they have won battles, God’s people should rejoice and sing joyfully all during the night!<verse eid="PSA 149:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 149:6"/>They should shout loudly to praise God; but they should also hold sharp swords in their hands,<verse eid="PSA 149:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 149:7"/>ready to use them to defeat the soldiers of nations that do not worship God and to punish the people of those nations.<verse eid="PSA 149:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 149:8"/>They will fasten their kings and other leaders with iron chains.<verse eid="PSA 149:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 149:9"/>They will judge and punish the people of those nations as God wrote should be done. Everyone else will honor God’s faithful people for doing that! Praise Yahweh!<verse eid="PSA 149:9"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 149"/>
<chapter number="150" style="c" sid="PSA 150"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 150:1"/>Praise Yahweh! Praise God in his temple! Praise him who is in his fortress in heaven!<verse eid="PSA 150:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 150:2"/>Praise him for the mighty deeds that he has performed; praise him because he is very great!<verse eid="PSA 150:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 150:3"/>Praise him by blowing trumpets loudly; praise him by playing harps and small stringed instruments!<verse eid="PSA 150:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 150:4"/>Praise him by beating drums and by dancing. Praise him by playing stringed instruments and by playing flutes!<verse eid="PSA 150:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 150:5"/>Praise him by clashing cymbals; praise him by clashing very loud cymbals!<verse eid="PSA 150:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 150:6"/>I want all living creatures to praise Yahweh! Praise Yahweh!<verse eid="PSA 150:6"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 150"/>
</usx>